title: hot peppers
directions: Boil 20 minutes for quarts and 10 minutes for pints until capped.

title: apple pie
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes.
Serve with whipped cream or ice cream.

title: squash casserole
directions: Boil squash until done, then mash.
Fry bacon until crisp and break in small pieces.
Saute onions in bacon drippings.
Add all ingredients together and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: squash puppies
directions: Cook squash in water for 20 minutes, or until tender.
Drain, mash and drain again.
Combine squash and the next 5 ingredients. Drop by scant tablespoons into hot oil; fry for 5 minutes.
Yields about 2 1/2
dozen.
These are great with fresh garden vegetables.

title: caramel pecan cheesecake
directions: Mix together the cream cheese, sugar and vanilla.
Add the eggs; mix.
Set aside.

title: every day meat loaf
directions: In a bowl thoroughly mix meat and seasonings together.
Put in pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Arrange potatoes in layers in 1 1/2-quart baking dish. Sprinkle each layer with onion, salt and pepper.
Dot with butter. Add hot milk.
Bake, uncovered, about 1 1/4 hours. Yields 4 servings.

title: veg-all casserole
directions: Mix all together and top with crumbs and margarine.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: baked cheese
directions: Press 4 triangles of crescent rolls on bottom of glass pie plate, pressing seams together.
Spread 1/2 of apricot preserves on top.

title: apricot mold
directions: Mix
Jell-O
and
water.
Add
apricot	juice.	Let set slightly, then beat in baby apricots and sour cream.
Blend in by hand the sliced apricots minus the juice.

title: tropical cheese pie
directions: Mix together cream cheese and sugar until fluffy.
Add drained pineapple.
Mix well.
Add Cool Whip and mix well.
Put in crust and chill.

title: corn salad
directions: Mix together the first 4 ingredients.
Combine mayonnaise, mustard and lemon juice; add to corn mixture.
Season with salt and pepper to taste.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: pepper steak
directions: Cut steak in 1-inch strips.
Brown with shortening in skillet. Add onions and salt.
Saute until onions are tender.
Stir in broth and soy sauce.
Cover, reduce heat and simmer 10 minutes or until meat is tender.
Add bell pepper.
Cover and simmer 5 minutes.
Combine water and cornstarch.
Mix well.
Stir cornstarch mixture into steak mixture.
Cook, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens.
Add tomatoes; stir constantly until tomatoes are hot.
Serve over rice.

title: ground beef soup
directions: Simmer meat with onion and garlic.
In a large pot, combine all of the vegetables, seasoning and meat mixture.
Add enough water to cover the vegetables.
Bring to a boil and simmer until the potatoes are done.

title: cream of crab soup
directions: Combine all but crabmeat in large soup pot.
Stir well.
Add crabmeat and simmer until blended, stirring occasionally.
Do not boil!!!

title: freezer pickles
directions: Cut up all vegetables.
Mix the sugar, vinegar, salt and celery seed together and pour over vegetables.
Cover and refrigerate for 24 hours.
Then pack in freezer cartons and freeze.
Serve when needed.

title: bran muffins
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake at 375° or 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Can
refrigerate	dough
up
to
6 weeks in a sealed container.	Serves 4 to 5 dozen.

title: honey barbecued chicken
directions: Melt butter in small saucepan.
Blend in remaining ingredients and simmer 2 to 3 minutes.
Cool.
This makes 1 1/2 cups sauce. Pour sauce over chicken halves in shallow pan.
Allow to marinate a few hours before cooking.
Place chicken halves cavity down on grill.
Cook slowly 40 to 45 minutes, basting frequently with sauce.
Turn and cook meat side down for 10 more minutes.

title: spumoni cookies
directions: Melt and cool chocolate.
Mix margarine, sugar, vanilla and egg.
Stir in flour and salt.
Divide dough into 3 equal parts. Mix pistachio nuts and food color into 1 part.
Mix chocolate into 1 part.
Mix cherries into remaining part.
Line bottom and ends of 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan with aluminum foil allowing ends to extend 5-inches over each end of pan.
Press nut dough evenly in bottom of pan.
Press chocolate dough on nut dough.
Press cherry dough on chocolate dough.
Cover dough with extended ends of foil. Refrigerate at least 2 hours.
Heat oven to 375°.
Remove foil and dough from pan.
Remove foil.
Cut dough crosswise into 1/4-inch slices and cut slices in half.
Place 1-inch apart on cookie sheet.
Bake 10 minutes or until set.
Remove immediately.

title: peanut butter kiss cookies
directions: Mix together peanut butter, shortening and margarine or butter. Mix remaining ingredients together with other ingredients and chill the dough slightly.
Roll into sugar and then into 1-inch balls. Place 2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Take out of oven and place 1 Hershey's Kiss on each cookie.
Let them cool, then enjoy.

title: salami-and-eggplant pie
directions: In a 12-inch skillet over medium heat in 1/4 cup of hot oil, cook eggplant, a few slices at a time, until tender.

title: batter for frying
directions: Beat until smooth; dip and fry.
May be used for onion rings, shrimp, fish fillets, etc.

title: sandies
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add water and vanilla.
Mix well.
Add flour and pecans.
Chill 3 or 4 hours.

title: zucchini appetizers
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients together.
Spread in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake until golden brown, about 25 minutes.
Cut into 1 x 2-inch pieces.
Makes about 4 dozen servings.

title: fruit salad
directions: Chill fruit before preparing.
Cut fruit into chunks.
Mix well with instant pudding.
Stir well and chill before serving.

title: cheese crispies
directions: Cream oleo until fluffy.
Slowly mix in flour.
Stir in cheese and cereal.
Shape into balls.
Put on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until lightly browned.
Serve warm or cold.

title: holiday cranberry relish
directions: Wash oranges; do not peel. Cut oranges into quarters, removing seeds and any tough membranes.
Set aside.
Grind frozen cranberries in food processor 1/2 cup at a time to be sure all cranberries are ground.
Add prepared orange quarters one at a time until thoroughly ground.
Put cranberry-orange mixture into large bowl.
Stir in 1 1/2 cups sugar thoroughly.
Add coconut and walnuts, mixing together thoroughly.
Serve in glass/crystal bowl for eye appeal.

title: cucumber party sandwiches
directions: Mix softened cream cheese and dry salad mixture together. Spread over rye bread.
Top with slice of cucumber.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: beer batter
directions: Mix first three ingredients together.
Beat egg until lemon color, pour into mixture and add beer.
More flour may be used if thicker texture is wanted.
Mix together until well blended.

title: pineapple pudding
directions: Mix pineapple, condensed milk, lemon juice and vanilla.
Line an 8 x 8-inch dish with vanilla wafers.
Pour mixture over wafers. Continue layers until all mixture is used.
Refrigerate for several hours or overnight.

title: swordfish with thyme apple sauce
directions: Prepare Thyme Apple Sauce; keep warm.
Set oven control to broil.
Place fish steaks on rack sprayed with nonstick cooking spray in broiler pan; brush with 1 tablespoon lemon juice.
Broil about 4 inches from heat
3 minutes.
Turn; brush with remaining lemon juice.
Broil until fish flakes easily with fork, 3 to 5 minutes longer.
Serve with Thyme Apple Sauce.
Makes 4 servings.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Cook spaghetti and onion in chicken broth.
Add other ingredients.
Mix well.
Put Velveeta cheese on top and cover. Melt in oven at about 350° until cheese melts.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Cook macaroni and cheese as directed.
Add eggs to this and spread into casserole dish.
Bake 10 minutes at 375°.
Take out of oven and top with tomato sauce, mushrooms, onions, pepper, oregano and basil.
Top with pepperoni and cheese.
Bake 10 minutes more. Let cool a few minutes.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together and place in loaf pan or dish. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: pinwheels
directions: *Fry's brand is good.

title: bob's potato salad
directions: Peel and boil potatoes, hard-boil eggs, chop celery, onion, parsley and olives and microwave bacon crisp.
In large bowl, add chopped ingredients and olive oil; mix.
Cool and chop eggs; add to chopped ingredients.
Add potatoes.
Chop and add bacon.
Add mayonnaise and mustard.
Mix thoroughly; refrigerate.

title: lemon cheese jello salad
directions: Dissolve jello in 1/2 cup boiling water.
Add sugar and pineapple and let partly gel.
Add Cool Whip, cheese and nuts. Mix and chill until jelled.

title: senator russell sweet potato souffle
directions: Mix
potatoes, vanilla, sugar, eggs and oleo thoroughly and pour into buttered casserole dish.
Mix brown sugar, nuts, flour and oleo and sprinkle on top of potato mixture.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: sausage and apple appetizers
directions: In a large skillet, melt butter over medium-high heat.
Add onion and saute, stirring constantly, until onion is golden.
Stir in apple jelly and brown sugar.
Add sausages and reduce heat to medium-low.
Cook, stirring occasionally, 20 minutes or until mixture begins to thicken.
Add apples; partially cover pan and cook 10 minutes or until apples are tender.
Combine cornstarch and water and stir into mixture in pan.
Cook 2 to 3 minutes more or until mixture thickens.
Serve warm.
Yields about 30 appetizers.

title: dill pickles
directions: Mix and boil the ingredients.
Put cucumbers and dill in jar. Pour boiling brine over cukes.
Put lids on and seal.
Have jars in hot water and let sit for 3 hours after pouring brine over. May add onions, if desired.

title: zabaione(dessert)
directions: Combine egg yolks and sugar in top part of double boiler. Beat egg beater until light lemon color and well blended.
Add Marsala, beat again, until well blended.
Put boiling water in lower part of double boiler.
Cook about 5 minutes or until slightly thick and creamy (while cooking, beat constantly).
Serve warm or can be cooled and served cold plain or over angel food cake slices.

title: lemon-dilled brussels sprouts and water chestnuts
directions: Bring water and salt to boiling in a large saucepan.
Add sprouts.
Cover and return to boiling.
Lower heat.
Simmer, covered, until sprouts are tender, about 12 to 15 minutes.
Drain. Return to saucepan.

title: strata
directions: Cut the crust from the bread. Then butter bottom side and place in 9 x 13 pan. Sprinkle cheese and cooked and drained sausage over bread. Mix eggs, milk and other seasonings. Beat well; pour over bread, sausage and cheese. Cover and refrigerate overnight. Bake at 325° for 50 to 55 minutes. Cool 10 minutes and cut.

title: peanut brittle
directions: In a heavy 4-quart boiler, combine sugar, water, salt and corn syrup.

Mix well. Cook over high heat, stirring constantly, until mixture begins to boil. Add peanuts; continue boiling and stirring until peanuts begin to "pop" and mixture begins to scorch. Continue to cook 1 minute more, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Stir in soda.
Pour onto a cookie sheet that has been sprayed with nonstick spray.
Spread quickly. When hard, break into pieces.

title: india relish
directions: Remove seeds from peppers. Put peppers, tomatoes, cucumbers and onion through food chopper, using coarse blade. Stir salt into vegetables in a colander and force out as much brine as possible. Chop cabbage very fine.

Combine all vegetables. Add sugar, vinegar and spices. Mix well and heat to boiling. Boil 3 minutes. Pack into sterilized jars to within 1/2 inch of top. Put on caps; screw bands firmly tight. Process in boiling water bath 5 minutes. Yields 8 pints.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Place in a 3-quart casserole and top with 1 cup buttered bread crumbs.
Bake in a 350° oven until crumbs are browned, 15 to 20 minutes.

title: granny's coconut cake
directions: Mix
all
ingredients together.
Pour into three 8-inch cake pans.
Bake in 350° oven for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: granny smith taffy apple salad
directions: Mix flour, sugar, pineapple juice, egg and vinegar together. Cook and stir over medium heat until thick.
Refrigerate mixture. When cool, add pineapple and apples.
Fold in Cool Whip and 3/4 cup peanuts.
Put into serving bowl.
Top with remaining peanuts. Chill before serving.

title: venison burgers
directions: Mix all ingredients; form into thick patties.
Cook on barbecue grill or broil in oven, 10 minutes on each side (less for rare burgers).
Serve on hot hamburger buns.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: french dressing
directions: Place ingredients in blender.
Blend at slow speed.
Slowly add 1 cup liquid oil.
Mix well.
Store in glass in refrigerator.

title: broccoli rice casserole
directions: Saute oleo and onion, then add rice.
Brown 5 minutes.
Add boiling water; let absorb.
Prepare in large pan the broccoli. Add mushroom soup, the milk and Cheez Whiz, then heat.
Stir in rice mixture.
Pour into a large buttered casserole; top with bread crumbs or crushed potato chips.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes, uncovered.

title: marble chiffon cake
directions: Boil
1/4 cup of water and add cocoa and 1/4 cup sugar. Stir until smooth, then cool.

title: ice cream
directions: Mix all ingredients together and make sure it's thoroughly blended.
Freeze in ice cream freezer until frozen.
Makes about 1/2 gallon.

title: broccoli pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease 10-inch glass pie plate.
Combine cheese, chicken, broccoli and onion in plate.
Combine remaining ingredients with electric mixer.
Mix on high until smooth.
Pour in pie shell.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool and serve.

title: shotgun sauce
directions: Melt ingredients together in saucepan.
Slowly bring to boil until slightly thickened.
Serve over poultry (especially pheasant).

title: german chocolate cake
directions: Heat chocolate and 2 tablespoons of milk in saucepan over low heat, stirring until chocolate is melted. Beat sugar into cream cheese; add remaining milk and chocolate mixture until smooth. Fold in whipped topping, blending until smooth. Spoon into crust. Freeze until firm, about 4 hours. Garnish with chocolate curls, if desired.

title: onion casserole
directions: In large skillet, melt butter over medium heat and saute onions and mushrooms until tender.
Place in 2-quart casserole. Sprinkle shredded cheese on top.
Combine soup, milk and soy sauce and pour over cheese.
Place bread on top and top with slices of Swiss cheese.
Cover and refrigerate 4 hours or overnight.
Bake, loosely covered, at 375° for 30 minutes.
Uncover and bake 15 minutes more.

title: belvey's fruit salad
directions: Over medium heat, cook the pudding, pineapple juice and mandarin orange juice until it comes to a boil and turns clear.

title: whole grain blueberry muffins
directions: Mix all dry ingredients thoroughly, including blueberries. Make a well in the center and add egg, milk and oil.
Mix only until dry ingredients are moist.
Fill greased muffin pans half full and bake at 375° for about 15 minutes.
Makes about 12 muffins.

title: apple dumplings
directions: Boil first 4 ingredients for 5 minutes; set aside.
Combine Crisco, baking powder, salt and flour.
Add milk.
Roll out dough. Cut into 8 squares.
Place cored apple in center of each pastry. Seal pastry.
Place in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour syrup over top of dumplings.
Bake at 375° for 35 minutes, basting frequently.

title: chocolate brownie cake
directions: Cook pudding on stove.
When cooked, stir in cake mix until well blended.
Pour in a 9 x 12 x 2-inch pan.
Sprinkle chips and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: pam's rice and artichoke salad
directions: Cook rice according to package directions. Cool. Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well and refrigerate.
For a main dish, try some small boiled shrimp or cooked, chopped chicken.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: grandma fran's incredibly delicious and easy cheese kugel
directions: Combine farmer cheese, cottage cheese, sour cream, eggs and sugar.
Mix well.
Add noodles and mix.
Melt margarine in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan in the oven.
Pour noodle mixture into pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until golden brown.

title: hot fudge peanut butter pie
directions: Mix ingredients with mixer until creamy.
Add confectioners sugar and fold in Cool Whip.
Pour into pie shells.
Makes 2.

title: mud hens
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
Grease and flour a 9 X 13 inch baking pan.
Cream butter and sugar together until fluffy. Add 1 egg and yolk from second egg, reserving white in a small bowl. Add flour, baking powder and salt.
Mix thoroughly.
Spread in pan.
Sprinkle with nuts.
Beat reserved egg white until frothy. Add brown sugar and beat until almost stiff.
Spread over dough. Bake 30 minutes.
Cut while hot.
Makes about 3 dozen.

title: south of the border casserole
directions: Brown meat drain well.
Add sauce, pepper, and salt to taste. Add corn and beans.
Pour into 9 x 13 pan.
Mix corn bread, spread on top.
Bake at 350 degrees until done.
Corn bread will be brown.
May sprinkle top with grated cheese if desired.

title: cheese and bacon flan
directions: Fry bacon and cut into small pieces.
Place in a 9-inch pastry crust and add grated cheese.
Beat eggs, milk and cream together; add seasonings and pour over cheese and bacon.
Bake at 350° for about 50 minutes or until set.

title: potato pancakes
directions: Beat eggs in large bowl; beat in flour.
Add onion, salt and pepper.
Stir in potatoes and parsley.
Heat margarine in heavy skillet.

title: shortening bread cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Roll, cut and bake at 350°. Frost with favorite frosting.

title: old-fashioned chocolate fudge
directions: Combine sugar, cocoa, cream,
milk, syrup and salt in a deep pan and heat.
Stir
until	sugar is completely dissolved and the mixture boils.
Boil
until
the
test
for
soft ball stage is reached (when little
of
mixture
is dropped in cold water). Remove from burner	and add butter and vanilla.
Cool until only warm; beat until
thick
and
creamy.
Add nuts, if used and pour into buttered pan.

title: pineapple salad
directions: Make jello as directed on package.
Cool to room temperature. Add pineapple and cheese.
Stir well.
Chill and serve.

title: taco sauce
directions: Cut vegetables up fine.
Put all ingredients in dishpan and bring to a boil.
Put in jars and place in pressure cooker.
Raise pressure to 5 pounds and shut off.

title: orange slice cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar in mixing bowl.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each.
Dissolve soda in buttermilk and add to the first mixture.
In another bowl, add flour, dates, candy, nuts and coconut; stir to coat the fruit and candy.
Fold into previous mixture.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan and bake for 2 1/2 hours in 250° oven.
If using small loaf pans, bake at 300° for 1 hour or until done.

title: rock candy
directions: Boil water and food coloring.
Add sugar to boiling water, stir always for 10 to 15 minutes.
Remove from heat and cool for 1/2 hour, stirring sometimes.
When cooled, pour into glass 1/2-inch from top.
Put wooden stick (popsicle stick is fine) in solution. Place glass in safe place to allow the crystal candy to grow.
It takes about 1 week for candy to be ready to eat.
Run hot water over outside of glass to loosen.
Pull out and eat.
Real good.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken until tender.
Bone; put in baking dish.
Add celery soup, milk and margarine.
Mix stuffing mix with broth from chicken.
Spread over mixture.
Sprinkle grated cheese over this. Bake until bubbly at 375°.

title: chocolate sin
directions: Combine the semi-sweet chocolate pieces and rum in the top of a double boiler.
Set over lightly simmering water and stir occasionally until the chocolate is melted and blended with the rum.
Set aside to cool.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Parcook macaroni.
Cook milk until it boils.
Add American cheese.
In a food processor, blend eggs.
Add cornstarch and blend until smooth.
Add egg mixture to the milk.
When the sauce is cooked, add Parmesan cheese.
Mix well and pour over macaroni. Bake in a 350° oven until it boils or gets lightly brown on top. Take out of oven and let stand for about 30 minutes while it thickens.

title: coffee blond brownies
directions: Heat brown sugar and butter in a medium size saucepan over medium-low heat until the butter melts.
Dissolve the coffee in the hot water and stir into the butter mixture.
Let cool to room temperature.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Butter an 11 x 8-inch baking pan.
When butter mixture is cool, beat in eggs and vanilla.
Sift the flour, baking powder and salt together and stir into the butter mixture (by hand).
Stir in the pecans and chocolate. Spread the mixture evenly in pan.
Bake until lightly browned, 25 to 30 minutes.
Do not over bake.
Cool completely and cut into 2-inch squares.

title: cheese-chili oven omelet
directions: Layer cheese, chilies and Jack cheese in greased, square baking dish, 8 x 8 x 2-inch.
Beat milk, flour, salt and eggs. Pour over cheese mixture.
Cool, uncovered, in 350° oven until set in center and top is golden brown, about 40 minutes.
Let stand 10 minutes before cutting.
Add tomato sauce.
Serve with omelet. Makes 8 servings.

title: chicken parmesan
directions: Beat egg.
Coat chicken in egg, then into bread crumbs.
Brown on both sides.
Pour 1/3 Chicken Tonight into baking dish.
Add chicken.
Pour remaining Chicken Tonight over chicken.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 425° for 25 minutes.
Cook noodles according to package directions.
Serve chicken over noodles.

title: weight watchers cheesecake
directions: Blend Knox and Equal.
Boil pineapple juice; sprinkle Knox over hot juice and let dissolve about 1 minute.
Put cottage cheese into electric blender; add juice and vanilla.
Blend until smooth.
Stir in pineapple.
Place in 8-inch pie plate.
Chill.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Add potatoes to 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix next 6 ingredients and pour over potatoes.
Mix cornflakes and melted butter.
Sprinkle over potato mixture.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: chocolate chip bars
directions: Cream sugar and margarine.
Add eggs and vanilla; mix well. Mix in flour, soda and salt.
Stir in chocolate chips and nuts. Spread into 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: havarti cheese hors d'oeuvres
directions: Sprinkle dill over cheese.
Divide crescent rolls into 2 sections.
Roll each lightly to close openings.
Wrap cheese with dough by placing it on one half and topping it with the other. Pinch sides together to seal the cheese well.
Bake at 350°.

title: yellow pickled eggs
directions: Slowly blend vinegar into mustard and add water, sugar, salt and celery seed. Simmer 10 minutes.
Cool and pour over shelled hard-boiled eggs and sliced onions.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.

title: marinade for chicken on grill
directions: Mix and pour over boned chicken breasts.
Marinate 5 to 6 hours, then grill.

title: boston cream pie loaf
directions: Slice pound cake into 3 layers using a long serrated knife. Place bottom layer on serving platter. Spread evenly with 1 cup pudding. Top with middle cake layer and spread remaining pudding. Top with remaining cake layer, cut side down. Spread with ice cream topping, pushing it gently over edges so topping drips down sides of cake. Serve immediately or refrigerate up to 3 days. Serves 12.

title: brownies
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan and bake 30 minutes in 350° oven.
Makes 32 brownies.

title: two egg treasure cake
directions: Sift flour, sugar, baking powder and salt into bowl.
Drop in Crisco and add 2/3 cup of the milk and vanilla.
Beat two minutes; scrape bowl.
Lastly add unbeaten eggs and the remaining milk. Pour into 2 (8-inch) layer cake pans.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes at 375°, moderately hot oven.

title: dump cake
directions: Grease and flour a 10 x 13-inch pan.
Add pineapple first, then cherries.
Sprinkle dry cake mix over the top.
Sprinkle on coconut and nuts.
Melt butter and pour over.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/4 hours.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs; add oil, sugar, zucchini and vanilla.
Add in dry ingredients.
Add 1/2 to 1 cup nuts and 1/2 to 1 cup raisins (optional; either or both).
Pour into 2 greased loaf pans. Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Enjoy.

title: speedy scalloped potatoes
directions: Sprinkle flour, salt and pepper over potatoes. Dot with butter. Add milk. Bake, uncovered, at 325° for 2 hours. Serves 3.

title: corn casserole
directions: Cook rice as directed.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake in casserole dish at 375° until bubbly.

title: homemade canned spaghetti sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients, except tomato paste, and cook 1 hour.
Add the tomato paste and cook for 1 more hour.
Cook slowly and stir often.
Ladle into hot jars and seal.
Process in hot water bath for about 15 minutes.

title: salmon mousse
directions: Drain salmon, remove skin and bones and flake. Set aside. Beat all other ingredients until smooth.
Add salmon and refrigerate until set, approximately 1 hour.
Serve with crackers. Freezes well.

title: carrot cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar together.
Add eggs.
Combine dry ingredients and add to creamed mixture.
Add extracts and nuts, if desired.
Drop by spoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes, until light brown.

title: praline-topped squash
directions: Combine squash, butter, salt and pepper in saucepan.
Cook until squash is hot, stirring frequently.
Remove from heat.
Mix in beaten egg.
Pour into greased casserole dish.

title: vidalia onion pie
directions: Crush soda crackers.
Saute onions in margarine.
Pour margarine from onions.
Add eggs and milk to onions in a bowl. Mix margarine with cracker crumbs, then into pie dish.
Add onion mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes or until lightly brown.
Cover with grated cheese after baked; return and bake a few minutes or until cheese is melted.

title: pecan pie
directions: Combine sugar, Karo, butter or margarine and salt.
Add slightly beaten eggs.
Stir in pecans and vanilla; pour into pie shell.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes, then at 350° until done.

title: special marinade(original recipe)
directions: Combine ingredients.
Stores well in refrigerator.
Leave lemon/lime hulls on top.
Pour over chicken.
Marinate overnight. Grill.

title: chicken with almonds
directions: Cut chicken into 1-inch pieces.
Set aside.
In small bowl blend soy sauce into cornstarch; stir in red pepper.
Set aside. Preheat a wok or large skillet over high heat; add cooking oil. Stir-fry green peppers and green onions in hot oil 2 minutes or until crisp-tender.
Remove from wok.
Add almonds to wok.
(Add more oil, if necessary.)
Add half of the chicken to hot wok or skillet; stir-fry 2 minutes.
Remove from wok.
Stir-fry remaining chicken 2 minutes.
Return all chicken to wok or skillet.
Stir soy mixture; stir into chicken.
Cook and stir until thickened and bubbly.
Stir in vegetables; cover and cook 1 minute more.
Serve at once.
Serve over hot cooked rice, if desired.

title: famous lemon cake
directions: Cream butter or oleo with sugar until light and fluffy.
In a separate bowl, beat egg yolks until light and lemon colored. Blend with creamed mixture.
Sift together cake flour, baking powder and salt.
Re-sift 3 times.
Add the sifted ingredients in thirds, alternating with milk.
Beat the batter thoroughly after each addition.
Add vanilla, lemon rind and juice and beat 2 minutes.
Bake at 325° in Bundt pan for 1 hour or until tests done.
May bake in angel food pan or large ring mold or in 3 greased 9-inch layer pans at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: pretzel jello salad
directions: Mix crushed pretzels, butter and 3 tablespoons sugar together. Spread in 9 x 13-inch glass dish.
Bake until brown, approximately 10 minutes.
Mix cream cheese, 1 cup sugar and Cool Whip until well blended and spread over cooled pretzel mixture. Mix jello, water and strawberries together.
Chill until thickened, then pour over cream cheese mixture.
Chill until stiff.

title: fruit topping
directions: Mix together, chill and serve.

title: mexican crock-pot
directions: Brown and drain beef; add taco seasoning.
Mix remaining ingredients in crock-pot and cook on low.
Serve over Fritos.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Shape into 1 teaspoon size balls. Roll in granulated sugar.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Add Hershey's Kisses and bake for 2 more minutes.

title: apple crumble
directions: Mix apples, cinnamon, nutmeg and lemon juice.
Place in an 8 1/4-inch round baking dish.
With pastry blender, cut butter into sugar and flour.
Sprinkle on apples.
Cook in microwave for 6 minutes.
Turn baking dish and cook for another 4 minutes.
Let stand for 5 minutes.
Serve with cream, ice cream or Cool Whip.

title: delicious chicken salad
directions: Sprinkle chicken breast pieces with salt.
Heat water, lemon juice and soy sauce in large skillet to simmering.
Add chicken. Cover and simmer 10 minutes, turning chicken once, until chicken is cooked through.
Do not overcook chicken or it will become dry. Remove chicken from pan onto cutting board.
Allow to cool so you can handle it.

title: chilaquiles
directions: Cut up tortillas in triangle shapes; deep fry them until golden brown.
Drain out the oil; pour in chopped onion and mix until onion is well cooked.
Then mix the cheese into the chilaquiles.
When serving, sprinkle more cheese on top.
Makes 8 servings.

title: lo-cal buttermilk dressing
directions: Combine in bowl; stir well.
Cover and chill.
Makes 1 1/2 cups.
Contains 12 calories per tablespoon.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Combine soup broth and milk. Melt margarine and combine with stuffing mix. Layer half the stuffing mix in baking dish, pour soup mixture on top, then layer chicken on top of soup. Put remaining stuffing on top. Bake at 350° about 30 minutes or until it is heated through.

title: drunken wieners(appetizer)
directions: Put in crock-pot and cook for 4 hours.
Add pineapple and cook another 1/2 hour.

title: layered lettuce salad
directions: Mix together mayonnaise, milk and lemon juice.	Shred lettuce in bottom of 9 x 12 oblong casserole.
Cook and drain 2 carrots and add peas.
Layer all ingredients as desired on top of lettuce, sprinkling with onion salt.
Spread mayonnaise mixture on top of all (like icing) and cover to edges.
Add cheese and Bac*Os on top. Saran Wrap tightly.
Chill.

title: sweet and sour pot roast
directions: Sear roast on both sides in heavy roasting pan.
Remove meat and sear onions in cooking oil in roasting pan.
Remove onions and place roast back in roasting pan, top with green pepper rings and onion slices.
Add beer, vinegar, brown sugar, bay leaves, allspice and peppercorns.
Cover and cook over low heat 2 1/2 hours or until tender.
Mix salt, flour, vegetable oil, half and half and currant jelly.
Add to juices in pan after roast has been removed to hot platter.
Serve gravy in bowl alongside carved roast.

title: butter pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add eggs, then vanilla.
Combine dry ingredients and mix in alternately with milk.
Stir in butter flavoring.
Bake in Bundt pan at 350° for about 50 minutes in well-greased pan.

title: baja fish and rice
directions: Cook and stir onion, celery and garlic in oil in large skillet over medium heat until tender.
Add uncooked rice; cook and stir about 5 minutes or until rice browns slightly.
Add tomatoes and juice, lemon pepper, salt and red pepper.

title: apple cake
directions: Beat the oil, sugar, eggs, vanilla and cinnamon.
Add dry ingredients and beat. Add to batter the apples and nuts.
Bake in a greased and floured tube pan at 325° for 1 hour.

title: mushroom soup
directions: Wash and peel 1 quart mushrooms and cut into dice. Stir the broth into them.
Thicken with the flour creamed with the butter, salt and pepper.
At the last moment, add a bit of whipped cream and croutons.

title: kailani's favorite weenies
directions: In saucepan, combine all ingredients except weenies.
Heat thoroughly.
Add weenies and simmer for 20 minutes.

title: fresh mushroom pate
directions: Saute mushrooms in butter until liquid is absorbed.
In food processor, using steel blade, combine cream cheese, wine, lemon juice, garlic powder and Tabasco until smooth.
Add mushrooms and process until blended.
Pour into a small bowl which has been lined with plastic wrap.
Chill at least 4 hours.
Unmold onto serving dish.
Garnish with mushroom slices.
Serve with crackers, zucchini and yellow squash slices.

title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: Cook water, jello, sugar and cornstarch.
When thickens, remove from heat and cool.
Pour over strawberries in pie shell and congeal in refrigerator.

title: jerry sowell's hot sauce
directions: Bring all ingredients, except Wesson oil, to a boil and simmer for 2 to 3 hours.
Store in refrigerator.
Just prior to use, pour 4 to 5 tablespoons Wesson oil into pot with sauce and heat. Stores in the refrigerator, without oil, for up to 1 year.

title: sweet 'n sour sauce
directions: Blend all ingredients together.
Place chicken wings in 9 x 13-inch casserole dish. Pour sauce over wings.
Do not cover. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Remove from oven.
Cool for approximately 10 minutes before serving.
(Sauce will thicken as chicken wings cool slightly.)
Great sauce for chicken wings. Finger lickin' good!!!

title: doughnuts
directions: Beat eggs lightly; add all ingredients and mix to form a dough.
Roll out 1/3-inch thick or a little more.
Cut out donuts. Fry in hot Crisco or cooking oil.

title: spice fruited cake(great for the holidays)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 3 x 8 x 3 3/4-inch aluminum loaf pans.
Set aside 6 cherries and 2 pineapple rings for decoration.
Finely chop remaining cherries and pineapple. Combine in large bowl all ingredients, except lemon juice and powdered sugar.
Mix at medium speed for 2 minutes.
Pour into prepared pans.
Bake for 45 to 55 minutes.
Cake is done when toothpick comes out clean.
Remove from pans.
Mix lemon juice and powdered sugar; drizzle over cool cake.
Decorate with cherries and pineapple.

title: broccoli au gratin
directions: Cook broccoli according to package directions and drain.
Place broccoli in 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Blend together soup, sour cream, cheese and onion.
Spoon on top of broccoli.
Cube bread. Toss cubes in melted butter.
Top casserole with buttered cubes. Bake in preheated 350° oven for 20 to 30 minutes.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: fruit pie crumb topping
directions: Blend ingredients and place on top of fruit pie instead of top crust.
Bake your pie as usual.

title: gingerbread cookies
directions: Mix sugar and butter together.
Add molasses, milk, vanilla and eggs.
Mix until blended.
By hand, mix in flour, baking soda, ginger, cinnamon, allspice and salt until well blended.
Cover and refrigerate for 2 hours.

title: pumpkin-chocolate chip cookies
directions: Combine pumpkin, sugar, oil and egg.
Stir together flour, baking powder, cinnamon and salt.
Add to pumpkin mixture along with dissolved soda and mix well.
Stir in chips, nuts and vanilla.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto lightly greased cookie sheet. Bake in 375° oven for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: mini pizzas
directions: Brown ground beef.
Roll out biscuits and place on pizza pan. Add spaghetti sauce and ground beef.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: smothered yellow squash
directions: Wash squash; cut off tips and trim dark spots.
Do not peel unless needed.
Spray heavy pan with Pam.
Saute bacon (or ham) and onion.
Add sliced squash.
Cook on a low flame until squash is tender, stirring occasionally.
After all squash are tender, remove lid and turn on a high fire to cook all the water out. Stir from the bottom of the pan very often.
When all of the water is cooked out, squash is done.
(Add salt and pepper to taste while cooking.)

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Separate dough into 4 long rectangles. Place rectangles crosswise in ungreased 15 x 10 x 1-inch baking pan.
Press over bottom; seal perforations.
Bake 14 to 19 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool completely.

title: ham 'n cheese pinwheels
directions: In small mixer bowl, beat cream cheese until smooth.
Stir in horseradish and chives.
Spread each meat slice with about 1 tablespoon cheese mixture.
Top with 1 slice cheese; spread with another tablespoon cheese mixture.
Roll up.
Chill before serving; slice each roll into 5 slices.
Put a toothpick in each piece, or use your fingers.
Refrigerate leftovers.
Makes about 4 dozen appetizers.

title: chicken liver pate
directions: Put chicken livers into a saucepan with the chopped slices of bacon.
Add onions, garlic, bay leaves, thyme, salt, pepper and chicken stock.
Cover the pan and cook over low heat, stirring occasionally, for 15 minutes.
Remove the bay leaves.
Pour the mixture into a blender; add brandy.
Blend to a smooth paste; do not underblend.
Chill overnight.

title: spaghetti pie
directions: Boil noodles; while hot, stir in Parmesan cheese and beaten egg.
Mix.
Coat a 9-inch pie pan or 8 or 9-inch square baking dish with Pam.
Line with noodle mixture; microwave 2 minutes.

title: crumble topping
directions: Combine flour, sugar and cinnamon.
Cut in butter until crumbly and sprinkle on pie.

title: tuna loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients.
Spread evenly in a regular size loaf pan (sprayed with Pam).
Bake 30 to 40 minutes.

title: golden glow salad
directions: Combine jello and boiling water.
Leave on warm stove.
Add marshmallows and stir until they melt.
Add 7-Up and drained pineapple.
Put in a long glass pan.
Let set in refrigerator until firm.

title: broccoli-potato soup
directions: Saute onion in margarine.
Cook potatoes in water and bouillon until tender.
Remove 1 cup potatoes and pour rest into blender with the cooked, chopped broccoli.
Blend.
Add cheese and diced potatoes (1 cup).

title: roasted peanuts
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Place raw nuts on cookie sheets; don't pile them on.
Place in oven; immediately turn oven off.
Leave nuts in oven until oven is cold.

title: pork chops paprikash
directions: Place meat on flat surface and pound with mallet to flatten. Sprinkle meat on both sides with salt, pepper and paprika.
Heat butter in skillet.
Brown meat over high heat for about 3 minutes on each side.
Transfer meat to platter.
Pour excess fat from skillet and cook onion until wilted.
Add wine and stir to dissolve brown particles.
Add chicken broth and simmer about 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and stir in sour cream.
Pour sauce over meat and sprinkle with parsley.
Good with rice or buttered noodles.

title: mom's orange julius
directions: Combine orange juice, milk, water, sugar and vanilla in a blender.
Add ice cubes, a few at a time, until smooth.
Serve immediately.
Serves 4 to 6 people.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Combine all ingredients and pour into two 9-inch round cake pans. Bake in a preheated 350° oven for 25 minutes or until cake tests done.

title: coconut pound cake
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sugar and margarine.
Beat well.
Add milk and flour alternately.
Mix well.
Add to coconut and vanilla.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.

title: chili(donnie's mother's recipe)
directions: Brown meat and drain.
Add onion and brown.
Add all other ingredients and water.
Cook 2 or 3 hours.
Thicken with cornstarch.

title: party cheese ball
directions: Combine cheese, mayonnaise, sherry flavoring, Worcestershire sauce and spices.
Blend until smooth.
Cover and chill until firm.
Shape cheese mixture in a ball. Roll ball in chopped nuts. Cover and chill.
Makes a 5-inch ball.
At holidays, I add a few green olives with pimentos for color.

title: parmesan potatoes
directions: Mix dry ingredients in bag and mix well.
Shake potatoes, few at a time, until coated.
Place in casserole dish sprayed with Pam.
Dot with 1 stick of margarine and bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.

title: spoon corn bread
directions: Combine all ingredients and pour into greased baking dish (11 x 7 x 1 3/4-inch).
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Add cheese on top and bake 10 minutes longer.

title: poor man's cake
directions: Boil sugar, shortening,
water and raisins together for 5 minutes.
After
mixture
cools,
add
sugar,
salt, cloves, cinnamon, nutmeg and
flour.
Pour
into greased, floured pan. Bake in 350° oven for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: salmon steaks with dill sauce
directions: In skillet, combine broth, lemon juice, cucumber, onion and dill; add salmon.
Cover.
Cook
over
low heat 10 minutes or until done.
Remove salmon to platter; keep warm.

title: keith's potato soup
directions: Boil the potatoes, carrots, onion and celery until tender. Drain water.
Add broccoli and cauliflower.
Add milk to desired consistency.
Add salt and pepper.
Simmer.

title: sweet and sour sausage
directions: Mix liquid and cornstarch in saucepan.
Cook 10 minutes over low heat until thick.
Add pineapple chunks and sausage which has been cut into bite-size chunks.
Simmer 15 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: All ingredients should be at room temperature.
Add cream cheese and margarine; mix well.
Add sugar, then eggs (1 at a time while mixer is on); mix well.
Add Presto cake flour (1/3 at a time while mixer is on).
Add vanilla; mix well.
Grease tube pan.
Cook at 375° for 50 to 55 minutes.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Pour confectioners sugar over whole 3 cups of strawberries. Leave 1 hour.
Crush 1 cup strawberries and cook with 1 cup water for 2 minutes.
Then pour through sifter.
Mix cornstarch and granulated sugar and stir into berry juice.
Cook until clear, stirring constantly.
After juice has cooled, add 1/2 box strawberry jello.

title: old fashioned chocolate pudding
directions: Scald milk.
Mix all dry ingredients and dissolve with a little of the milk.
Add egg yolk and mix well.
Add the remaining milk and cook in double boiler until thickened, about 15 minutes. Cool; add vanilla and beaten egg white.

title: chunky cheese spaghetti
directions: Cook chicken in oil (about 5 to 8 minutes).
Remove chicken from pan; drain all but 1 tablespoon oil.
Add next 5 ingredients; cook and stir over medium heat until tender.
Add chicken and spaghetti sauce.
Cook until thoroughly heated.
Add 1 cup of cheese; cook just until cheese melts.
Pour over cooked spaghetti; sprinkle with remaining 1 cup of cheese and parsley. Yield:
4 to 6 servings.

title: baked mushroom rice
directions: In saucepan, melt butter and saute onion until clear. Transfer to 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Add rice, undiluted consomme and drained mushrooms.
Cover.
Bake at 275° for 1 hour, stirring occasionally.

title: smoked sausage supper
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving liquid.
Set aside.
Heat oil and cook sausage, onion, pepper and celery until vegetables are crisp-tender.
Add tomatoes, broth, garlic, brown sugar and pepper; cover and simmer for 5 minutes.
Blend cornstarch and pineapple juice; stir into skillet.
Cook until thick.
Stir in pineapple chunks.
Serve over rice.
Makes 6 servings.

title: yellow squash casserole
directions: Combine squash and water in a 1-quart saucepan.
Cover and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 15 minutes or until tender.
Drain well and mash squash.
Add milk, cheese, 1/2 cup breadcrumbs, onion, margarine, bouillon and pepper, stirring until well combined.
Pour into a 1-quart casserole; top with remaining breadcrumbs and paprika.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Makes 6 (1/2 cup size) servings.

title: alabama pecan pie
directions: Put all together and mix well with electric beater.
Put in uncooked pie shell and cook slowly, about 1 hour at 300°.
Serve with whipped cream, if desired.

title: crybaby cookies
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add molasses and eggs.
Sift dry ingredients.
Combine with coconut, raisins and nuts.
Add flour mixture alternately with milk to shortening mixture.
Drop by tablespoon on greased baking sheet.
Bake at 375° approximately 10 minutes.
Makes 200 cookies.

title: clam dip
directions: Mix ingredients until smooth and well blended.
If this mixture is not thin enough, add more liquid.

title: ginger-pecan muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 425°. Coat 12 nonstick muffin cups lightly with vegetable cooking oil spray.
In a bowl, combine flour, ground pecans, 1/4 cup sugar, ginger, baking powder and salt. In a second bowl, combine milk, egg, orange peel, orange juice, vanilla and melted butter.
Whisk together.
Form a well in the center of the flour mixture. Add the liquids, stirring together until just moist. (Do not overmix batter.)

title: strawberry salad with nuts
directions: Mix the water, pineapple and sugar together in a saucepan. Bring to a boil and add Jell-O.
Refrigerate until it begins to congeal.
Then fold in whipped cream, pecans and cream cheese. Put in prepared dish or mold and chill.

title: apple kuchen
directions: *Confectioners sugar and water or milk combined to drizzle consistency.

title: seven layer dinner
directions: In a large casserole, layer the ingredients in the order listed. Cover and bake at 375° for 2 hours.
Serves 6.

title: wassail
directions: Into large pot, add cider, juice from orange and orange slices and red hots.
Heat until red hots are melted.
A good hot drink for the holidays.

title: cherry-topped cheese cake
directions: Crumble crackers.
Mix with melted oleo and press into a 3-inch deep 8-inch pie pan.
Beat softened cream cheese until fluffy.
Gradually blend in 1/2 cup sugar, lemon juice, lemon peel, vanilla and salt.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Pour filling into crumb crust.
Bake at 325° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: rhubarb pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour, nutmeg.
Cut in butter.
Add eggs and lemon.
Put rhubarb in unbaked pie shell and pour egg mixture over rhubarb.
Bake at 450°.

title: orange-cream fruit salad
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients well.
Add the remaining ingredients and refrigerate.
Best served when cold.

title: oven fried cheesy italian chicken
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Heat margarine in 9 x 13-inch pan in oven until melted.
Mix together remaining ingredients, except chicken. Coat chicken with mixture.
Place, skin sides down, in pan.
(I remove skin, optional.)
Bake 35 minutes.
Turn and bake about 15 minutes more or until done.

title: fruit drop cookies
directions: Mix well the shortening, sugar and eggs; stir in sour milk. Sift dry ingredients together and stir in.
Stir in pecans, cherries and dates.
Chill at least 1 hour.

title: dirt pudding
directions: Mix cream cheese, butter & confectioners sugar on low speed. Add cool whip and pudding.
Gradually pour in milk while blending. Add vanilla and continue to blend until pudding is smooth.
Crush cookies.
Layer cookies and pudding in bowl.
Top with remaining oreos.
Add flowers, gummy worms, etc. for decorations.
Serve chilled.

title: pineapple coconut cake
directions: Bake cake according to directions on package.
Mix pineapple with 1 cup sugar, boil 5 minutes after it comes to a boil.
Pour hot mixture over the hot cake; let cool.
Mix vanilla pudding with milk.
Add Cool Whip.
Mix and put on cake; sprinkle coconut on top.

title: butterfinger dessert
directions: Mix both cracker crumbs and save 2/3 cup.
Add oleo.
Pat into a 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Mix together pudding, milk and ice cream. Spread over crumbs.
Top with Cool Whip.
Sprinkle remaining 2/3 cup crumbs, then grated candy bar.
Refrigerate.
Makes 20 bars.

title: chili
directions: Brown ground beef.
As meat is browning, add chopped onion to meat.
After meat has browned, drain off excess fat.
Add remaining ingredients, except the chili beans to meat.
Simmer on low for 30 minutes.
Drain juice of beans and add to chili.
Cook 10 additional minutes on low and serve.

title: grandma coopey's chili
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
Combine all ingredients and let simmer for several hours.
Serves 16 to 20 people.

title: peanut butter drops cookie
directions: Blend together and form into balls.
Cool in refrigerator. Roll in melted chocolate (dot chocolate).
Melt chocolate with a little water.
Could also use chocolate almond bark, but do not add water.

title: chocolate balls
directions: Melt butter.
Pour over cracker crumbs, sugar, nuts, peanut butter, vanilla and coconut.
Work with hands until soft.
Form in small balls.
Melt paraffin and chocolate in double boiler (over hot water).
Dip balls and chill.

title: chicken and dressing casserole
directions: Combine the cornbread, margarine and
broth.
Mix well. Place 1/2 of the mixture in a 9
x
13-inch
casserole
dish. Next, combine the chicken, onion, celery, mayonnaise and salt. Mix well.
Spread this mixture over
the
cornbread
mixture. Cover this with the remaining cornbread mixture.	Beat 2 eggs; add enough milk to them to make 1 cup
of
liquid.
Pour
this over the casserole.
Spread the cream of
mushroom
soup
over the top of the casserole.
Bake at 350°
for 35 to 40 minutes. Sprinkle with
Parmesan
cheese and	bake
an
additional
10 minutes.

title: amish sugar cookies
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients.
Beat well.
Add 2 eggs.
Sift together flour, soda and cream of tartar.
Add slowly to batter. Add vanilla.
Drop small balls on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Separate eggs and beat whites until stiff and set aside. Cream sugar, margarine, yolks and vanilla. Sift soda and flour together.
Add flour mixture and sour cream alternately and mix well.
Gently fold in egg whites.
Bake in greased, floured tube pan at 300° for about 2 hours.
Do not cook too fast, adjust oven.

title: zesty lasagna
directions: Brown meats together, drain.
Add garlic, basil, oregano, 1 tsp. salt, 1/4 tsp. pepper, onion, mushrooms, tomatoes & tomato paste.
Simmer uncovered 30 min. stirring occasionally.
While noodles are cooking, combine Ricotta, Parmesan, parsley, eggs, remaining salt & pepper.
Place half of noodles in 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Spread half each of Ricotta filling, mozzarella, then tomato sauce.
Repeat layers.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Let stand for 10 - 15 min. before serving.

title: greek green beans(single dish meal)
directions: Saute beef and onion until done.
In a large saucepan, combine tomato paste, green beans and zucchini.
Add meat mixture, salt and pepper.
Serves 5 to 8 according to the rest of your meal.

title: strawberry preserves from figs
directions: Mix dry gelatin and sugar; pour over figs and stir well.
Cook for 20 minutes or until thick.

title: baked soup
directions: Layer each item one on top of the other. You may do 2 or 3 layers of each item until it comes to top of casserole or roaster pan. Cover with cream of tomato soup. Bake in 325° oven for 3 hours.

title: fried sweet potatoes
directions: Cut sweet potatoes in thin slices.
Fry in vegetable oil until lightly browned.
Lightly salt.

title: snowball cake
directions: Crumble cake and cover bottom of a 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Set aside.

title: apple pizza cake
directions: Spread can of apple pie filling into dish.
Sprinkle with sugar and desired cinnamon.
Spread pineapple over apple mixture. Evenly distribute cake mix.
Sprinkle with nuts.
Melt butter and pour over cake mix.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes.

title: crab hors d'oeuvres
directions: Blend all ingredients together.
Spread on 12 English muffin halves.
Broil until lightly browned.
Cut; makes 40.
Can be frozen until ready to broil.

title: heavenly dessert
directions: Melt butter and blend with flour and chopped pecans.
Press into bottom of 9x13 pan and bake at 350 degrees for 20 minutes. Let cool.
Beat softened cream cheese with powdered sugar.
Fold in cool whip.
Spread over crust.
Place bananas over cream layer. Spread cherry pie filling over bananas.
Mix pudding according to package directions.
After pudding is almost set, spread over cherry filling.
Sprinkle pecans on top and cool in refrigerator. Makes 12 servings.

title: squash casserole
directions: Boil squash and onion until well done; season to taste. Drain and mash. Add 1/2 stick butter, 1/2 cup crackers, eggs and sugar. Place in baking dish. Melt remaining butter; pour over casserole then add rest of crackers. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes. Add cheese and bake an additional 5 minutes, until cheese is melted.

title: amy's chicken
directions: Use an 8 x 8-inch or 9-inch round casserole dish.
Layer chicken and sprinkle with garlic salt.
Place a layer of Swiss cheese on top.
Mix cream of chicken soup with wine, water or milk.
Pour over chicken.
Cover chicken with stuffing mix and dot with butter.
Microwave for 16 minutes or bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: low-fat buttermilk corn muffins
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients in a medium bowl, stirring well. Make a well in center of mixture.
Combine buttermilk, egg substitute and oil.
Add to dry ingredients, stirring just until dry ingredients are moistened.
Fold in corn.
Spoon batter into muffin pans coated with cooking spray, filling 2/3 full.
Bake at 425° for 18 to 20 minutes or until muffins are golden.
Remove muffins from pans immediately.

title: fruit tart
directions: Preheat the oven to 400°. In a large bowl, combine the flour, sugar and salt; mix well. In a small bowl, whisk together the oil and 2 tablespoons milk; pour into the flour mixture. Using a fork, mix until the dry ingredients are moistened. Using your fingers, press the dough evenly over the bottom and edge of a rimmed 12-inch pizza pan. With a fork, prick the dough all over, then bake for 10 to 12 minutes or until golden. Remove from the oven and allow to cool.

title: teriyaki beef bites
directions: Stir together liquid ingredients.
Add meat; pour combined mixture into a plastic bag.
Twist bag shut or secure.
Place bag in bowl; marinate in refrigerator at least 1/2 hour.
Drain meat pieces.
Place cubes in a 12 x 8 x 2-inch baking pan.
Bake at 475° for 6 to 8 minutes.
Serve with toothpicks.

title: brownies
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Melt chocolate with shortening over hot water and beat in sugar and eggs.
Add dry ingredients and mix thoroughly.
Stir in nuts.
Spread in well-greased square pan, 8 x 8 x 2-inches.
Bake in moderate oven at 350° until top has full crust, about 30 to 35 minutes.
When done, a slight imprint will be left when top is touched lightly with finger.
Cool and cut into squares before removing from pan. Makes 16 (2-inch) squares.

title: hash brown potatoes
directions: Sprinkle potatoes with salt and pepper.
Heat margarine in skillet.
Add potatoes; cook until brown, stirring frequently.

title: lemon cream cheese pie
directions: Whip
the cream cheese until smooth.
Blend milk, lemon juice and
egg
yolks.
Combine with the cream cheese and beat until smooth;
add
vanilla.
Pour
into
baked pastry shell. (Can use a vanilla wafer crust and sprinkle vanilla crumbs on top.)

title: louisiana joe
directions: Prepare cornbread as directed on package; cut in 6 pieces. In skillet, brown meat with onions, green pepper and garlic; drain.
Stir in tomatoes and tomato sauce.
Season with salt and pepper, if desired.
Simmer 15 minutes.
Serve over cornbread. Serves 6.

title: crock-pot stew
directions: Put all ingredients in crock-pot, cook on low for 3 to 4 hours.
Cook on high for 1 to 2 hours more.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: baked scallop
directions: Cut large scallops in half.
Combine scallops, cracker crumbs, margarine, catsup, salt, sugar and lemon pepper.
Place in shallow 1 1/2-quart casserole or other serving dish.
Drizzle top with butter.
Bake in moderate oven at 350° for 25 minutes.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Place under broiler if needed to brown.

title: cream of broccoli soup
directions: Chop vegetables (chop broccoli medium size).
Steam all until slightly tender; drain.
Place in 4-quart pot and add broth and milk.
Season to taste.
Bring to a boil and add the cheese.
Soup will thicken.
Tastes better made a day ahead.

title: chicken and noodles
directions: Stew chicken until tender.
Put salt, pepper and celery in chicken broth.
Bring to boiling point.
Add 1 package of noodles. Simmer until tender.

title: linda's peanut butter cookies
directions: Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: bean salad
directions: Drain and mix beans together, add remaining ingredients to beans.
Stir several times, let stand overnight.

title: good neighbor bread
directions: Dissolve dry milk in 3 1/2 cups warm water; stir in shortening, sugar and salt.
Dissolve yeast in 1/2 cup warm water; add to milk mixture.
Add 6 cups flour to make smooth batter.
Add 6 more cups.
Knead well on floured board.
Place in greased bowl. Let rise 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Punch down; let rise 1/2 hour.
Shape into 4 loaves.
Cover; let rise for 45 minutes, until light.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: seasoned oyster crackers
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour over oyster crackers that are in a box with wax paper liner.
Shake real good.
Enjoy!!

title: brisket
directions: Mix beer,
brown
sugar,
chili
sauce, flour and garlic until well blended.
Place brisket in roaster pan with fat side up after rubbing with salt and pepper.
Sprinkle onion over the top.
Pour flour mixture over brisket and bake at 325° for 4 to 6 hours. Marinate several times while baking.

title: best brownies
directions: Mix sugar and cocoa.
Add oil, eggs and vanilla.
Mix well. Add flour and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Let cool before serving.

title: moist apple cake
directions: Soak raisins in water for 2 minutes; drain.
Mix all ingredients together.
Sprinkle fruit and nuts with flour before adding to batter.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: sweet and sour beef stew
directions: In large saucepan, brown half the beef at a time in hot oil. Return all meat to pan. Stir in carrots, sliced onions, tomato sauce, 1/2 cup water, brown sugar, vinegar, Worcestershire sauce and salt. Cover and cook over low heat about 1 1/2 hours or until meat is tender. Blend 1 tablespoon cold water with cornstarch. Add to stew. Cook until mixture is thickened. Serve over noodles. Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: orange glazed carrots
directions: Cook carrots and drain.
In a small sauce pan combine sugar, cornstarch, salt and ginger.
Add orange juice.
Cook and stir until thickened and bubbly.
Cook and stir 1-2 minutes more.
Stir in butter.
Pour over hot carrots; stirring lightly to coat. Yield:
4-6 servings.

title: blueberry dumplings
directions: Wash blueberries well and place in a large pot.
Turn your burner on medium heat.
Put stick of butter in and the sugar. Prepare dumplings as indicated on Bisquick box (if your family likes dumplings, prepare a double batch).
Let the berries slowly come to a slight boil (stir often).
Spoon in the dumplings, turn down the heat and cover the pot for about ten minutes.
Remove the top and let cook until the dumplings are done.
Cut into a dumpling with a knife or fork to see if it is done in the center. If the juice is not thick, use a mixture of flour and water to thicken the liquid.
Serve over vanilla ice cream or eat by itself.
Enjoy.

title: lemon frosted gelatin
directions: Make gelatin according to package directions using just the 1 3/4 cups cold water.
When slightly set, add pineapple and oranges and pour into 8 x 10-inch pan. Chill until set.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix all ingredients, pour into sprayed bread pan (glass or tin).
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: christmas punch
directions: Dissolve gelatin in hot water.
Add cold water, lemonade concentrate and pineapple juice. Blend well. Before serving, add ginger ale and ice cubes.
Makes 35 to 40 (4 ounce) servings.

title: margarita
directions: Mix all ingredients in a blender.
Quarter a lime and rim glasses with juice.
Then dip into Margarita salt.
Drop lime into glass and pour drink over it.
Serves 4.

title: kraut salad
directions: Mix together and let set 12 hours in refrigerator in airtight container.

title: swordfish parmesan with lemon and garlic sauce
directions: Dip 1 side of swordfish in egg whites and then in the cheese. Pan-fry (nonstick skillet) swordfish, cheese side down, until golden brown.
Turn over and finish in a 325° oven, approximately 5 minutes.

title: seasoned oyster crackers
directions: Preheat oven to 275°.
Pour oyster crackers into a large bowl. Combine vegetable oil, Ranch dressing and seasonings in small bowl. Mix well.
Pour over crackers.
Toss until crackers are coated. Spread on flat cookie sheet.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes.
Cool.
Store in airtight container.

title: rice pudding #1
directions: Combine rice, water and salt in a 3-quart kettle.
Bring to a boil, cover and simmer on low heat for 14 minutes.
Add milk, sugar and butter.
Boil on medium heat for 20 minutes until thickened, stirring often.
Remove from heat and add vanilla. Pour into serving dish and sprinkle with cinnamon.
Delicious warm or cold.
Yield: 8 to 10 servings.

title: rum balls
directions: Combine ingredients and work into balls.
Roll in powdered sugar or nuts.
Store in tightly sealed containers.

title: pecan crust
directions: Mix and press above ingredients into baking dish.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
Can also be used for a Phili Cherry Pie crust.

title: pat's cowboy cookies
directions: Mix shortening, margarine, eggs, brown sugar and sugar together real good.
Add by hand the remaining ingredients.
Drop spoonfuls of batter onto greased sheet pans.
Bake at 325° for 7 to 10 minutes, until edges are turning brown.

title: baked macaroni and cheese
directions: In medium saucepan, combine cornstarch, salt and pepper; stir in milk until smooth.
Add margarine.
Stirring constantly, bring to a boil over medium-high heat and boil 1 minute.
Remove from heat.
Stir in cheese until melted.
Add elbow macaroni.
Turn into greased 2-quart casserole dish.
Sprinkle with bread crumbs. Bake, uncovered, in 375° oven for 25 minutes or until lightly browned.
Yield: 6 servings.

title: mandalay salad
directions: Clean, dry and tear spinach into bite size pieces.
Arrange in salad bowl and sprinkle with toasted sesame seed.
Mix oil and vinegar and pour over spinach.
Toss and serve.

title: strawberry squares
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Combine all ingredients (except jam).
Set 1/2 of mixture aside to be used as topping.
Press remaining mix into the bottom of an 11 3/4 x 7-inch pan.
Bake for 15 minutes. Remove pan and spread jam into pan.
Take remaining mixture and crumble over jam.
Put in oven for another 15 to 20 minutes (bar should be brown and jam will be bubbly) or until it looks done.

title: all-in-one-breakfast
directions: Saute onion and bell pepper.
Brown sausage.
Mix together in large casserole dish:
onion and pepper mixture, browned sausage, milk, bread and eggs.
Let stand overnight.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour or until golden brown.

title: egg custard
directions: Allow scalded milk to cool to warm; add to beaten eggs, sugar and vanilla.
Pour into Pyrex cups and bake at 325° for 50 minutes in enough water in pan to come to top of cups.

title: strawberry mousse
directions: Combine mashed berries, sugar and salt in a bowl and set aside.
Sprinkle the gelatin into the cold water; stir both into the 1/4 cup boiling water.
Let cool, then stir in the lemon juice.
Combine gelatin mixture with berries and refrigerate until chilled.
Whip the cream to soft-peak stage and fold into chilled fruit mixture.
Pour into a mold and freeze about 6 hours.
Unmold by running cool water over the mold.
Slide a chilled plate under the mold.
Turn mold over and let mousse slide onto plate.

title: hot alaskan salmon melts
directions: Drain salmon; remove skin and bones.
Mix with rest of ingredients.
Mound on English muffins.
Broil 3 to 4 minutes until cheese is melted.

title: puppy chow
directions: Melt first 3 ingredients in microwave until it will mix together good.
Add Rice Chex.
Mix until well covered.
In double brown grocery bag, add powdered sugar.
Add cooled Rice Chex and shake until covered good.
Spread out on paper towels to dry. Store in covered container.
Very good for T.V. snack.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Mix pretzels, sugar and margarine.
Press in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 8 minutes at 400°.
Cool.
Blend Cool Whip, cream cheese and sugar until smooth.
Spread over first layer.
Mix strawberries, jello and water until water cools.
Pour over 2nd layer.
Refrigerate.

title: wacky cake
directions: Use an 8 x 8-inch pan, ungreased.
Sift dry ingredients together in pan.
Make 3 holes in dry ingredients with a tablespoon.
Place vinegar in 1, vanilla in 1 and oil in the next one.
Pour cold water over all this.
Stir together with rubber scraper.
Stir well.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes in metal pan; for 35 to 40 minutes in glass pan.

title: annie's pumpkin roll
directions: In a large bowl, combine eggs and sugar, beating well.
Add pumpkin, mixing until blended.
In a separate bowl, combine flour, baking powder, spices and salt.
Add to egg mixture, mixing well. Spread batter into a greased and waxed paper lined 10 x 15-inch jelly roll pan.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Remove from pan. Cool for 15 minutes.
Place cake on a clean towel.
Cool for 10 more minutes.
Unroll cake and place on plastic wrap.
Evenly spread filling over cake.
Roll up cake.
Cover with plastic wrap. Place cake, seam side down and chill for at least 2 hours.
To serve, cut cake in even slices and garnish with mint leaves and orange slices, if desired.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: banana cake
directions: Cream oleo and sugar thoroughly.
Drop eggs in one at a time, beating well.
Add buttermilk mixed with soda.
Add bananas and flour last.
Bake in a moderate oven at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: crawfish etouffee
directions: Wash crawfish and cook for 2 to 3 minutes. Remove crawfish and set aside. Add onions, celery, bell pepper and seasonings; saute. Return crawfish tails to pan and add chicken broth. Stir and cook slowly, covered, for about 40 minutes. Serve on hot rice and sprinkle with parsley and green onion tops.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add yeast, buttermilk and shortening. Mix only until blended.
Let rise at least one hour.
Roll on floured surface and cut.
Bake at 400°.
Store uncooked dough in refrigerator.
Will keep for several days.
Makes 30 to 36 biscuits.

title: aunt abbie's ginger cookies
directions: Beat lard (or crisco) and sugar to a crumble. Add molasses, egg, cinnamon, cloves, ginger, milk and soda. Use enough flour to mold & roll into balls. Coat with sugar. Bake at 375 degrees.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Bake at 350° for 1 hour in 2 loaf pans.

title: corn cob wine
directions: Cut corn off cobs into 5 gallon crock.
Add cobs and the 3 gallons of water.
Let stand 3 days.
Strain.
To the strained corn water, add grape juice, sugar and yeast.
Stir well.
Cover and let work until bubbles disappear (about 2 weeks).
Strain and bottle.
Cap lightly at first, later cap tightly.

title: lasagna
directions: Cook lasagna noodles as directed on package; drain.
Brown hamburger in skillet; drain.
Add tomato paste, tomatoes, oregano and cottage cheese.
Butter a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Put a layer of noodles, a layer of sauce and a layer of Mozzarella cheese. Repeat and end with cheese on top.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 350°. It should be juicy with cheese melted and brown.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Boil carrots until just barely crunchy (do not overcook). Combine the remaining ingredients. Add carrots to the mixture. Mix well and refrigerate several hours, turning once in a while. Serve cold. Will keep at least a week in refrigerator.

title: texas fudge
directions: Drain peppers.
Seed, stem and chop.
Combine with grated cheese.
Sprinkle on bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour beaten eggs over cheese and pepper mixture.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes in a 350° oven.
Cool slightly, then cut into squares.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Thaw potatoes a little and spread in a 9 x 13-inch buttered casserole dish.
Mix and cream the sauteed onions, cream cheese and soup.
Pour mixture over potatoes and top with grated Cheddar cheese.
Bake at 350° to 400° for 45 minutes.

title: dole ambrosia
directions: Drain pineapple and oranges and use juice as a beverage. Combine fruits, nuts and marshmallows, mixing well.
Fold in yogurt.
Serves 4 to 6 people.

title: fried macaroni
directions: Cook spaghetti according to package directions; drain.
In a medium size skillet, melt shortening and butter.
Pour cornmeal into skillet and brown.
Add salt, then the cooked macaroni, mixing well.
Serve while hot.

title: cucumber salad
directions: Bring sugar, salt, vinegar and celery seed to a boil; let cool. Pour over cucumber, onion and bell peppers.
Let set for 3 hours. Put in containers and freeze.

title: banana zucchini bread
directions: In mixing bowl, beat eggs.
Blend in sugar and oil.
Add bananas and mix well.
Combine flour, baking powder, baking soda, cinnamon and salt.
Stir into egg mixture.
Stir in zucchini and pecans.
Pour into 2 greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Cool for 10 minutes.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: shephard's pie
directions: Cook ground beef, drain. Add onion, tomato sauce, salt and pepper. Simmer 10 minutes. Put in greased casserole dish. Put mashed potatoes on top of meat, sprinkle with cheese. Bake 350° 30 minutes or until golden brown.

title: spicy chicken with peanuts
directions: Combine beaten egg white, 1 teaspoon cornstarch and 1 tablespoon soy sauce; mix well.
Add chicken and refrigerate 1 hour or longer.
Combine onions and dried peppers (tips removed) or red pepper; set aside.
Combine sugar, 1 teaspoon cornstarch, remaining 1 tablespoon soy sauce, water and sherry; set aside.
Heat 1 cup peanut oil in wok to 275°.
Stir in chicken mixture.
Stir-fry until chicken turns white, about 1 minute.
Remove chicken to a colander and drain.
Heat 2 tablespoons oil in same wok over high heat.
Add onions, red pepper and cooked chicken; stir-fry 1 minute.
Add soy sauce mixture to chicken while stirring over high heat in wok until mixture is lightly glazed.
Add peanuts and mix well.
Serve over hot cooked rice if desired.
Serves 2.

title: buttery biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 525°.
Have margarine room temperature.
Use 1/4 stick to grease a 9-inch round pan.
Mix remaining 3/4 stick with the flour and milk.
Dough will be very stiff.
Mix the minimum amount of time possible.
Using two tablespoons, dip up rounded tablespoonfuls of dough and push the dough into the pan with back of other spoon.
Arrange all the balls of dough in the pan, put cold water into the mixing bowl, dip spoon in water and shake off excess water.
Using back of spoon, flatten and smooth each biscuit until they are uniform in size and thickness.
Bake 20 minutes.
Enjoy while hot!

title: brunch casserole
directions: Fry meat; crumble or cube.
Grease a 4-quart casserole dish. Arrange bread slices, broken into cubes, in bottom.
Beat eggs, milk, soup, cheese and meat; pour over bread and bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: cranberry orange muffins
directions: Chop cranberries, orange and 3 tablespoons sugar together in food chopper.
Cream shortening and 1/4 cup sugar; add well beaten egg.
Alternately mix the dry ingredients with the milk; add.
Add cranberry mixture and barely mix evenly.
Bake at 425° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: granny cake
directions: Mix together the flour, sugar and soda.
Add eggs and pineapple (juice and all).
Mix well.
Pour into ungreased cake pan (9 x 13-inch).
Mix brown sugar and nuts.
Sprinkle on top. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: carrot cake
directions: Grease and lightly flour 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
In a large mixing bowl, stir together flour, sugar, baking powder, baking soda, chopped walnuts and cinnamon.
Add carrots, oil and eggs.
Mix well until moistened.
Beat at medium speed for 2 minutes.
Pour into prepared pan.
Bake at 325° for 50 to 60 minutes or until wooden toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool thoroughly on wire rack.

title: pennsylvania dutch potato filling
directions: Mix together the potatoes and egg.
Soak bread in cold water and squeeze dry.
Fluff bread and mix gently with the potato mixture.
Blend in remaining ingredients and mix well.
Use for stuffing poultry or meat.
Will fill a
6 to 8 pound bird.

title: refrigerator slaw
directions: Alternate layers of cabbage and onion in large jar.
Top with 7/8 cup sugar.
Combine 2 teaspoons sugar, mustard, celery seed, salt, vinegar and salad oil.
Bring to boil.
Pour over cabbage. Cool.
Cover and refrigerate at least 3 days before serving.
The flavor improves with age.

title: casserole bread
directions: Soak yeast in 1 cup warm water for 5 minutes.
Pour milk over sugar, salt and shortening.
Stir until dissolved.
Add yeast mixture and all of flour.
Beat 2 minutes by hand.
Cover with greased wax paper and let rise 35 to 45 minutes.
Beat 1/2 minute and pour into greased 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle with garlic salt.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.
Remove from casserole and cool. Great with pasta!

title: slaw
directions: Grate cabbage into medium bowl.
Add vinegar, mayonnaise, sugar and pepper to taste.
Stir thoroughly.
Refrigerate before serving.
Serves 5 people.

title: oven fried potatoes
directions: Cut each potato in 8 wedges lengthwise.
Arrange peel side down in shallow baking dish.
Mix remaining ingredients and brush over potatoes.
Bake in 375° oven for 45 minutes or until tender. Baste occasionally.

title: cabbage salad
directions: In medium bowl mix cabbage, onion, sugar and vinegar.
Stir in remaining ingredients as listed.
Sprinkle with paprika. Refrigerate 1 hour.
Makes 8 servings.

title: pizza sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients and cook until thick.
Process pints 30 minutes and quarts 45 minutes in hot water bath.

title: coconut cream pie
directions: Mix egg yolks, cornstarch, flour, sugar and 1/3 cup milk. Pour into scalded milk all at once.
Stir over heat until thick. Add coconut, vanilla and butter.
Pour into prebaked pie shell. Cover with meringue.
Sprinkle with a little coconut.
Bake at 400° for 8 minutes.

title: christmas pie
directions: Peel, core and slice apples in bowl; add cranberries, dates and spices.
Stir in flour.
In saucepan, combine sugar and water. Bring to a boil. Reduce heat.
Stir in fruit mixture.
Simmer on low 10 minutes.
Cool slightly; stir in nuts.
Spread into prepared crust.
Enjoy!

title: ham and cheese biscuits
directions: Mix margarine, poppy seed, Worcestershire sauce, mustard and onion; spread on each side of roll.
Cut ham and cheese and place on rolls.
Bake at 350° until cheese melts.

title: shrimp elegante
directions: Peel shrimp, devein and butterfly.
Place in boiling salter water for 30 seconds.
Drain and place in a shallow broiling pan. Combine butter and olive oil in a large saucepan; place over medium heat until butter melts.
Add onion, garlic, parsley and oregano cook stirring occasionally, until onion is transparent. Add next 5 ingredients, stirring until bouillon dissolves.	Reduce heat to low and cook 5 minutes.
Pour over shrimp, cover and refrigerated for 2 hours.
Cook linguini; uncover shrimp and broil 4 minutes on low heat each side.
Serve over linguini and sprinkle with parmesan cheese if desired.
Serves 6.

title: blueberry cream cheese pie
directions: Thoroughly blend the cream cheese, sugar and vanilla.
Whip cream.
Fold into cheese mixture.
Pour into cooled pie shell. Chill.
Top with blueberry pie filling.
Chill for several hours before serving.

title: ratatouille
directions: Place eggplant, onion, garlic and oil in 2-quart casserole. Cook in microwave 5 minutes.
Cut green pepper into 1/2-inch strips.
Layer pepper and zucchini over eggplant mixture.
Add seasonings to tomatoes.
Cook in microwave on 8 to 10 minutes. Let stand 5 minutes before serving.

title: candy cake
directions: Mix pudding, Milnot, sugar and butter.
Bring to full boil, stirring with wooden spoon.
Lower temperature and boil for 3 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Stir in nuts and flavoring.
Continue stirring until it thickens.
It will lose its shiny look.
Drop on waxed paper by spoonful or pour into pan. Let cool.

title: banana split cake
directions: Combine sugar, 1 stick melted margarine and graham cracker crumbs; mix well and line a 9 x 12-inch dish.
Combine 2 sticks margarine, extract and powdered sugar and beat well in electric mixer for 15 minutes on medium speed.
Pour over crumbs.
Layer remaining ingredients, in order listed, over filling, garnishing top with extra strawberries.
Refrigerate several hours before cutting in 3-inch squares.

title: tuna ball
directions: Mix and form into ball and roll in parsley flakes. Refrigerate.

title: green bean bundle(serves 8)
directions: Wrap 1/2 slice bacon around 8 beans.
Place seam side down. Bake in 9 x 13-inch dish; pour on dressing.
Cover 3 hours or overnight.
Bake, uncovered, 40 minutes (be sure bacon is done) at 350°.

title: radish dip
directions: In a food processor or bowl, mix the cream cheese, butter, celery salt, Worcestershire and paprika until well blended and smooth. Fold in the radishes and onions until completely mixed. Chill. Makes about 2 cups. Serve on crackers or as a vegetable dip.

title: gourmet chicken
directions: Cover bottom of flat baking dish with chipped beef.
Wrap one piece of bacon around each chicken breast.
Lay on top of chipped beef.
Mix sour cream and soup.
Pour over chicken.
Refrigerate, covered, overnight.
Bake at 275° for 3 hours, uncovered.
A great make ahead dish for parties.
Serve with rice.

title: watergate salad
directions: Put pineapple, juice and all, in a bowl.
Pour dry pudding mix over pineapple and stir.
Add pecans, marshmallows and Cool Whip. Mix well.
Chill and serve.

title: zesty cabbage beef bake
directions: Cook ground meat and onion in a skillet until beef is browned. Drain off drippings and set aside.
Place cabbage in boiling, salted water to cover.
Return to a boil and cook 8 minutes. Drain well and set aside.
Stir garlic powder, salt and hot sauce into spaghetti sauce; set aside.
Layer rice and beef mixture in a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch dish.
Sprinkle beef lightly with salt. Place cabbage on top and spread with spaghetti sauce.
Spread cheese over sauce.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Makes 12 to 15 servings.

title: meringue nest with raspberry sorbet
directions: Whip first 4 ingredients together gradually adding in sugar. Beat with mixer until stiff peaks form.
Using an ice cream scoop, place meringue balls 1 inch apart on parchment paper on cookie sheet.
Using the back of ice cream scoop, make an indent, making the meringue resemble nests.
Bake in 275° oven for 1 hour.
Turn off oven and let dry in oven.
Serve nest with one scoop of raspberry sherbet in nest with fresh fruit sprinkled over.

title: fruit salad
directions: Slice bananas; sprinkle with lemon juice and set aside. In another bowl,
pour
pie
filling,
pineapple,
oranges and bananas.
Add strawberries last.
Mix, chill and eat.
This is an easy fruit salad which is also excellent tasting.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Grease and flour a 13 x 9-inch pan. Spread coconut, pecans and chocolate chips in bottom of pan. Prepare cake mix according to directions on package.
Pour batter over coconut, nuts and chips. Mix the oleo, cream cheese and powdered sugar.
Drop mixture on top of batter by teaspoonfuls. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Cake will be shaky but will set up as it cools.
