It looks like it has been in an earthquake, thus the name.
But do not bake longer than the recipe calls for.

title: cucumber and onion salad
directions: Mix all ingredients except cucumbers and onions in a small bowl.
Add cucumbers and onions.
Mix well.
Keep chilled in refrigerator until ready to serve.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: pecan pralines
directions: Cook the first 5 ingredients over low heat; stir until sugar dissolves.
Add the pecan halves.
Boil slowly, stirring often, until candy reaches soft ball stage.
Remove from heat.
Stir until it begins to thicken, then drop on waxed paper.

title: mrs. field's cookies
directions: Cream butter and both sugars together.
Add eggs and vanilla. Mix four, oatmeal, salt, baking powder and baking soda together. Mix together all ingredients and add chocolate chips or chopped nuts or raisins.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet.
Make golf ball sized cookies, 2 inches apart, and bake at 375° for 6 minutes. Makes 112 cookies.

title: pistachio cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into greased and floured tube pan.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: cream cheese flan
directions: Mix in blender first 5 ingredients.
Melt sugar with a few drops of water.
Pour melted sugar in pan and blended mixture on top.
Bake at 350° for about an hour or until you see it cooked in the center.
Turn onto a plate after it is slightly cool but not completely cold.

title: apricot meat loaf
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients.
Mix well and shape into loaf. Place in greased shallow pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Combine brown sugar and 1 teaspoon water in saucepan.
Heat until sugar melts, stirring occasionally.
Spread over hot meat loaf and bake 5 to 10 minutes longer.

title: chicken bake
directions: Shake chicken in flour with salt and pepper.
Then fry to golden brown.
Drain chicken.
Add all 3 cans soup and milk. Cover and let simmer for 45 minutes.
Serve over rice or noodles.

title: yogurt fluff
directions: Pour boiling water into blender.
Add Jello and blend at low speed until dissolved.

title: crab dip
directions: Thin the Philadelphia cheese with a little milk. Add remaining ingredients. Chill in refrigerator.

title: turkey with popcorn stuffing
directions: Blend all ingredients thoroughly and place in cavity of turkey. Roast in moderate oven at 325°.
You'll know when it's done when the popcorn blows the birds tail off....Gotcha.

title: decoration
directions: Place foam cups (white or decorated), wide mouth side down, on room temperature cookie sheet.
Preheat oven at 350°.
Place cookie sheet in oven for exactly 1 1/2 minutes.
Remove promptly.

title: pecan pie #2
directions: Mix all ingredients in order given.
Pour into a 9-inch unbaked pie shell.
Place pie on baking sheet in oven.
Bake at 300° for 30 minutes.

title: bacon muffins
directions: Cook bacon until crisp; drain and crumble.
Reserve 1/4 cup bacon drippings.
Combine flour, corn meal and sugar.
Add eggs, milk and bacon drippings; stir until moistened.
Stir in crumbled bacon.
Spoon batter into greased muffin pans and bake at 425° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Makes 12 muffins.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Mix and pour into heated skillet.
Bake at 425° for 30 to 40 minutes until browned and done in the middle.

title: 3 bean salad
directions: Drain beans and combine.
Add green pepper.
Combine sugar, vinegar and oil.
Pour over vegetables.
Add salt and pepper. Toss.
Chill overnight.
Before serving, toss to coat beans; drain.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: chicken in mustard-caper sauce
directions: Melt 1 tablespoon butter with oil in frying pan.
Brown chicken breasts that have been seasoned with salt and pepper and lightly floured.
Cover and cook on low until tender, 30 minutes. Remove chicken.
Add remaining 3 tablespoons of butter to the pan drippings.
Mix in wine, mustard, Worcestershire and capers; stir briskly to blend and heat until bubbly.
Stir in cream and heat; do not boil.
Pour over chicken and serve.
Makes 2 servings.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add one egg at a time.
Beat well. Add vanilla and almond.
Sift dry ingredients.
Add flour and milk alternately with ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: baked macaroni and cheese
directions: Melt margarine; stir in flour and milk.
Heat to boiling.
Add cut up cheese cubes.
Turn burner to low; add pepper.
Grease 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Pour macaroni into dish; add sauce and stir.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: oreo dirt pie
directions: Crumble 1/2 of cookies in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix cream cheese, sugar, Cool Whip and butter; set aside.
Mix pudding, milk and vanilla and mix with other mixture.
Pour on top of Oreo cookies and crumble rest of cookies on top.
Refrigerate several hours.

title: savory fresh mushrooms
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large skillet.
Cover and cook over medium heat 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Yields 4 servings (about 43 calories per serving).

title: champagne salad
directions: Cream the sugar and cream cheese.
Add strawberries, pineapple, bananas and pecans.
Mix well. Fold Cool Whip in.
Put in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch dish and freeze.
Thaw 1/2 hour before serving. Cut into squares.

title: bacon burgers
directions: Mix all ingredients, except bacon slices.
Shape mixture into 6 patties.
Crisscross two half slices of bacon on each patty. Grill for 5 to 7 minutes on each side.

title: macaroni and spam salad
directions: Cook macaroni and drain.
Chop onion, celery and Spam.
Add oil, vinegar, salt, pepper, mayonnaise and sweet peas.
Mix everything together.
Cover and place in refrigerator for several hours.

title: snack crackers
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients. Add crackers mix gently. Stir every 15 minutes for the first hour. Store in an airtight jar.

title: georgia apple pie
directions: Slice and cook for a few minutes, then combine other ingredients.
After preparing pastry, preheat oven to 425°.
Mix flour, sugar, nutmeg, cinnamon and salt.
Stir into apples.
Turn into 9-inch pastry lined plate.
Dot with butter or margarine. Cover with top crust that has slits.
Fold upper over lower crust. Seal edge.
Bake until crust is browned and filling bubbles through slits, about 40 minutes.

title: bubble bread
directions: Grease a Bundt pan.
Sprinkle with nuts.
Arrange frozen rolls in pan.
Mix dry ingredients and sprinkle into rolls.
Pour melted butter over all.
Let rise 8 hours.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Cover loosely with foil after 20 minutes.

title: ham barbecue
directions: Simmer 1/2 hour on low heat and stir. This is better made the day ahead and refrigerated.
Then heat sauce and shortly before serving, add 1 1/2 to 2 pounds chipped ham.
Cook just long enough to heat through.

title: joe's chewy chip cookies
directions: Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes on ungreased cookie sheet. Combine flour and soda; set aside.
Combine butter, sugar, brown sugar, pudding and vanilla; beat until smooth.
Add eggs. Gradually add flour mixture.
Add chips and nuts.
Remove from cookie sheet to rack; do not place on newspaper or towel to cool. This will remove moistness.
These cookies don't really brown on top.

title: chicken shwerma
directions: Combine salt, pepper, cumin, garlic, ginger, olive oil, and vinegar in a big bowl with the chicken breasts and marinate in refrigerator for at least 4 hours.

title: cauliflower saute with lemon
directions: Wash cauliflower and soak in salted cold water for 1 hour. Drain; cut into flowerets.
Cover with fresh, cold, salted water and cook slightly.
Flowerets should be firm.
Heat olive oil in a large skillet.
Add drained flowerets.
Saute quickly, turning to brown on all sides.
Place in serving dish; season with salt and pepper.
Add lemon juice.
Makes 4 servings.

title: cheese strata
directions: Layer the bread and cheese in a bread baking dish.
I use sharp or sprinkle on parmesan cheese.
Beat eggs until foamy Add milk and seasonings.
Beat together and pour over bread.
Let stand at least 2 hours.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix broccoli, bacon, onion and raisins together.
Add sugar and mayonnaise.
This works best with Hellmann's.
This can be made a day ahead.

title: mini pizzas
directions: Cook ground beef, then mix with egg, soup mix, salt and pepper.
Place mixture over sliced bread.
Place 1 teaspoon of spaghetti sauce over each slice.
Add cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Cook raisins in water; let cool.
Cream the sugar and shortening.
Add rest of ingredients.
Drop from spoon; bake in moderate oven (soft cookie).

title: broccoli supreme(serves 6 to 8)
directions: Cook broccoli according to package directions; drain.
Stir in next 4 ingredients.
Pour into greased 2-quart casserole. Sprinkle bread crumbs and almonds on top, if desired.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: spinach balls
directions: Cook and drain spinach.
Mix with other ingredients.
Line cookie sheet with foil and drop mix in balls.
Cook for 20 minutes at 350°.
Makes 6 to 8 dozen.
May be frozen until ready to cook and serve.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Dissolve soda in buttermilk.
Beat eggs and add sugar, oil, soda and salt.
Mix well and add flour, bananas and nuts.
Add vanilla after all is mixed well.
Pour in loaf pan.
Bake at 325° for 50 to 60 minutes, until done.

title: hot fudge sundae cake
directions: Mix in pan.
Sprinkle with 1 cup brown sugar and 1/4 cup cocoa. Pour 1 3/4 cups hot tap water over it.
Bake for 40 minutes at 350°.
Let stand 15 minutes.
Makes an 8-inch square cake.

title: cheese ball
directions: Add all ingredients except 1 1/2 cups nuts.
Roll into 2 balls, then roll balls in remaining nuts.
Place cherry on top. Chill.
Serve on crackers.

title: cheese balls
directions: Grate Cheddar and Old English cheeses.
Put grated cheeses and cream cheese in bowl and mix until smooth.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well and shape into 2 balls.
Chill.
Roll in chopped nuts or additional paprika.

title: sunday special
directions: Brown ground beef and onion; drain.
Spread in 9-inch square pan.
Spread soup, diluted with 1/2 can water, over mix.
Top with Tater Tots.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: grits casserole
directions: Put eggs in 1 cup measure and add enough milk to fill.
Add oleo and cheeses.
Crush some corn flakes and top casserole.
Bake at 350° for approximately 30 minutes.
Test for solidity.

title: quiche thing
directions: Beat eggs and milk together with salt and pepper.
In a 2-quart buttered dish, cover bottom of pan with bread. Then cover with layer of cheese.
Keep layering until pan is full.
Pour egg mixture over, pushing down to soak bread.
Let mixture stand for 2 hours.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serve with salad for lunch or supper.
Serve with bacon, sausage or ham for breakfast.

title: rancho beans
directions: Cook together butter, ground beef and chopped onions.
Mix together salt, Worcestershire sauce and prepared mustard.
Then mix together brown sugar, ketchup, pork and beans and kidney beans. Mix all together.
Bake in oven 1 1/2 to 2 hours at 350°.
Check after 1 1/2 hours.
Serves 10 (with other things).

title: peanut butter chocolate chip cookies
directions: Beat margarine, sugars and peanut butter together until light and fluffy.
Beat in eggs and vanilla.
Mix in flour, baking soda and salt.
Stir in chips.
Bake in ungreased cookie sheets 10 to 12 minutes at 350°.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown hamburger and drain grease.

Cook enough lasagna noodles to make two layers in your pan (11 x 14-inch probably 8 noodles). When noodles are done, run under cold water to keep from sticking. Put one layer of noodles in bottom of pan.
Mix ground beef and sauce.
Put a layer over the noodles.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Put another layer of noodles, then sauce and meat.
Sprinkle with cheese again.
Spread Mozzarella over top.
Bake, covered, with foil about 40 minutes at 350°.

title: spinach and artichoke casserole
directions: Melt cream cheese in margarine.
Thaw spinach.
Prepare as directed.
Pour margarine and cheese over spinach.
Mix well.
Add lemon, salt, pepper and Tabasco.
Line bottom of casserole with artichoke hearts.
Pour spinach on top.
Top with bread crumbs. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: broccoli corn bread
directions: Mix onion, eggs, cottage cheese, and broccoli.
Add corn bread (plain, not mixed by package instructions).
Bake in well greased skillet at 350° until brown and cooked in center.

title: lemon d-light
directions: Mix and press in a 9 x 13-inch pan the first 3 ingredients. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes. Cool.

title: nine bean soup
directions: Combine all dry beans; rinse.
Place in large pot.
Cover with water 2 inches above beans and soak overnight.
Drain beans.
Add 2 quarts water and next 6 ingredients.
Cover and bring to a boil. Reduce heat and simmer 2 hours or until beans are tender.
Add remaining ingredients.
Simmer 1 hour, stirring occasionally.

title: holiday cake
directions: Blend brown and white sugars, Crisco oil and salt together until whipped lightly.
Add eggs.
Add sifted flour and soda, alternating with milk.
Add cinnamon, nutmeg, vanilla, pecans and coconut.
Pour into lightly-greased and floured Bundt or tube pan. Bake 1 hour in a 350° oven.
This cake may be lightly sprinkled with confectioners sugar after baked.

title: swedish hash
directions: Brown meat and onions.
Add all remaining ingredients and mix well.
Pour into greased casserole dish and bake covered for 1 1/2 hours or until rice is done at 350°.

title: cream puffs(zavareni bulochki)
directions: In saucepan, boil water and butter with pinch of salt.
Take off flame when starts to boil and add flour slowly, stirring constantly with wooden spoon.
Return mixture to low flame and cook dough until it leaves sides of pan.
Stir constantly; cool. Beat in eggs 1 at a time well after each addition.
Bake in a 350° oven for 10 minutes, then lower to 300° to 325° and bake until golden brown.
Do not open oven door while baking.
Fill with your favorite filling.

title: texas barbecue sauce
directions: Saute minced onion in margarine. Add other ingredients and bring to a boil.
Simmer for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: cherry marshmallow cake
directions: Preheat oven 320 degrees.
Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, beat well.
Sift dry ingredients, and add to butter mixture.
Add milk and flavoring, mix well; and pour into 3 to 4 greased 9 inch cake pans.
Bake at 320 degrees until done.
Cool and ice with Cherry Marshmallow Icing.

title: alabama cornbread
directions: Beat eggs well and add to all ingredients. Preheat medium size iron skillet with oil.
Bake at 450° until done, about 30 minutes.

title: liz's famous lo-cal cole slaw
directions: Combine in a large salad bowl and toss with Cole Slaw Dressing.

title: no knead dinner rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in 1/4 cup of water.
Mix egg, sugar and oil. Follow by adding flour and cornmeal; put dough into greased muffin tins.
Dough can be kept in fridge up to 5 days.
Bake at 425° for 10 to 20 minutes.
Yields 2 dozen rolls.

title: chocolate upside-down cake
directions: Sift and then measure the flour. Sift again with baking powder, salt and 1/2 cup sugar. Blend shortening into the above ingredients until soft. Add the milk, vanilla and chopped nuts to the mixture. Mix well. Pour into greased 9-inch square baking dish. Combine the 1/2 cup sugar, brown sugar and cocoa. Sprinkle over the batter. Pour boiling water over the batter. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. May be topped with whipped cream or vanilla ice cream.

title: diabetic apple pie
directions: Thaw apple juice.
In a saucepan, combine apple juice and cornstarch and cook until thickened over medium heat, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and add butter and cinnamon; set aside to cool.

title: fruit smoothie
directions: Place 1/2 can of juice in blender.
Add bananas and blend until smooth.
Add strawberries, one at a time, until desired color is reached.
Serve in clear glasses.

title: butterscotch squares
directions: Mix and pour into pan on 350°.
Bake 20 minutes.

title: pineapple dream cake
directions: Blend all ingredients except confectioners sugar and milk, then beat at medium speed for 2 minutes.
Bake in a greased and floured 10-inch pan at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes until center springs back when touched lightly.
Cool right side up for about 15 minutes, then remove from pan.

title: peanut brittle (2)
directions: Cook sugar, corn syrup and water to 280°, medium crack stage. Add peanuts, cook about 3 minutes or until light brown.
Add baking soda, remove at once from heat. Add vanilla and butter.
As soon as foaming has subsided, pour into buttered shallow pan.

title: pork chops and wild rice
directions: Combine contents of box, soup, water and water chestnuts in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Trim any fat off pork chops and arrange on top of rice mixture.
Bake, uncovered, 1 hour and 20 minutes at 350°.

title: mom's cake
directions: Cream sugar, eggs, margarine and almond extract until smooth. Add dry ingredients to cream mixture.
Add milk.
Fold in cherries and nut meats.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or when tested, toothpick comes out clean.

title: dr. pepper chili
directions: Place ground beef in heavy pan with onion and garlic.
Cook, stirring with fork to break up meat, until slightly browned.
Add salt, tomato paste, Dr. Pepper and water.
Cover; simmer until meat is very tender and mixture is desired thickness.
Add chili beans.

title: for fresh berry pies
directions: Mix the cornstarch and sugar.
Toss with the fresh berries. Turn into pastry-lined 9-inch pan.
Cover with top crust.
Cut several slits in top near center.
Seal and flute edge.
Bake at 425° for 35 to 45 minutes or until browned.

title: chanukah brisket
directions: Brown brisket in skillet.
Mix all other ingredients together. Bake brisket 10 minutes, then pour ingredients over to cover. Seal with foil.
Bake 1 1/2 hours.
Slice and refrigerate.
Cook until done (1 hour prior to serving).

title: cheese loaf
directions: Dissolve gelatine in 2 cups cold water.
Add 1 cup boiling water.
Work in cheese.
Add other ingredients.
Chill.

title: baked apples filled with cheese
directions: Peel and halve the apples.
Using a spoon, remove the core from the apple.
Rinse apples with cold water and drain or blot off excess water.
Set aside.

title: simple corn bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into a greased 8 x 8-inch pan.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Check center for doneness.

title: can-can casserole
directions: Put all ingredients into a buttered casserole dish.
Bake, uncovered, at 325° for 1 hour.

title: chocolate cake brownies
directions: Grease a 15 x 10 x 1-inch baking pan.
Combine flour, baking powder and 1/2 teaspoon salt.
Beat butter for 30 seconds; add sugar and beat until fluffy.
Add eggs, cocoa, vegetable oil and vanilla; beat well.
Add dry ingredients and milk alternately to beaten mixture, beating after each addition.
Stir in walnuts. Turn batter into pan.
Bake in a 350° oven for 18 to 20 minutes. Cool on a wire rack.
Frost with Chocolate Frosting.
Cut into bars.
Makes 36.

title: banana split dessert
directions: Layer 1:
Mix Graham cracker crumbs and 2/3 c. melted margarine and pat in 9 x 13 pan.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Cook sliced zucchini and onion 7 minutes; drain.
Add grated carrot, soup and sour cream to zucchini mixture.
In separate pan, melt butter and add stuffing mix.
Place 1/2 stuffing mixture in bottom of casserole dish with low sides.
Add all the vegetable mixture.
Place remaining half of stuffing mixture on top.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: open fire roast chicken
directions: Will also need 1 fishing pole, 1 forked sticks and 1 screw stick.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix well; pour in buttered 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.

title: deep dish pumpkin pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350.
In medium bowl, combine flour and sugars; cut in margarine until crumbly.
Stir in nuts.
Reserving 1 Cup crumb mixture, press remainder firmly on bottom and halfway up sides of 12 X 7 in baking dish.
In large mixing bowl, combine remaining ingredients except reserve crumb mixture; mix well. Pour into prepared dish.
Top with crumb mixture.
Bake 55 minutes or until golden.
Cool.
Garnish as desired.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: loaf paraffin wax candy
directions: Put all ingredients in a heavy saucepan; let stand 1/2 hour. Put on low heat; let stand until paraffin wax is melted.
Cook gently until a soft ball is formed in cold water.
Divide into 3 parts.
In each of the 3 parts, use peanut butter, cocoa, nuts, coconut, almond flavoring or whatever you want.
Put in layers (cocoa in the middle, peanut butter with extra peanuts added on the bottom, the coconut or light part on the top) in a bread pan lined with wax paper.
Slice as used.
This is a real keeper.

title: chicken italian
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Dip chicken in egg, then in bread crumbs mixed with 4 tablespoons Parmesan cheese.
Refrigerate for 30 minutes or freeze 5 minutes.
Brown chicken in hot oil in a large skillet.
Place chicken in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Pour small amount spaghetti sauce over chicken; top with Mozzarella and Parmesan cheeses.
Bake for 15 minutes.
Serve with spaghetti and remaining spaghetti sauce.

title: zucchini-cabbage stir-fry
directions: Heat oil and brown garlic; discard.
Add veggies.
Stir-fry 2 to 3 minutes.
Add seasonings.
Reduce heat and cook 5 to 6 minutes.

title: easy peach cobbler
directions: Melt oleo in casserole dish.
Mix flour, sugar and milk together.
Pour over melted oleo. Add the peaches (with just a little juice).
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: scrambled egg whites(serves one)
directions: Combine all ingredients except margarine and mix well.
Beat gently with a fork until foamy and very well blended.
Melt margarine in a small frying pan to coat bottom.
Pour egg mixture into pan.
Scramble over low heat.

title: autumn apple sheet cake
directions: Cream sugar and shortening. Add eggs and beat. Combine flour, soda, 3/4 teaspoon cinnamon and salt. Sift into creamed mixture, adding alternately with coffee. Fold in apples and nuts., Pour butter into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan. Combine 1/2 teaspoon, cinnamon and brown sugar; sprinkle over the top of the cake before baking. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Cool and cut into squares and serve.

title: frosty
directions: Combine all ingredients in blender.
Blend until creamy. Makes 2 or 3 drinks.

title: barbecue beef
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour over beef. Bake 4 1/2 hours at 325°. Tear apart with 2 forks when done. Place on buns.

title: corn chowder
directions: Cook potatoes and onion with water and bouillon cube.
Boil 10 to 15 minutes or until potatoes are tender.
Add milk, flour, butter and corn.
Cook at medium heat 5 minutes until flour thickens.
Lower heat and simmer for 10 minutes.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Serve hot.

title: slaw or fresh vegetable dressing
directions: Mix well and refrigerate.
Keeps well in refrigerator.

title: peanut clusters
directions: Heat in crock-pot.
Add ingredients.
Spoon out on cookie pan and allow to cool.

title: good 'n easy beef 'n gravy
directions: Combine all ingredients in slow cooker.
Cover.
Cook on low 10 to 12 hours. Yield: 8 servings.

title: pecan squares
directions: Blend milk with flour. Add molasses and salt. Fold in pecans. Spread about 1/4-inch thick on well-greased pan.
Bake in a 350° oven for about 25 minutes. Cut into squares.
Can top with powdered sugar, if desired.

title: beef patties
directions: Place meat in pan.
Add 1/2 teaspoon of salt or to taste and ketchup.
Brown same.
Add onion and green onions.
Add dash of black pepper.
Add tomatoes and cook meat until done.
Add water to aid in cooking meat; let cool.

title: chocolate kahlua truffles
directions: Place knife blades in food processor bowl; add cookies and process until cookies turn to crumbs.
Combine skim milk, dry milk and Kahlua in a large bowl.
Stir in crumbs.
Add dates, stirring until mixture forms soft dough.
Shape into 1/2 to 3/4-inch balls. Roll in chopped pecans; cover and chill.
Serve in miniature paper baking cups.
Yields 4 1/2 dozen (74 calories per 2 truffles).

title: fruity summer punch
directions: In a large pitcher, pour orange juice, grapefruit juice, sugar and lemon juice over cracked ice. Add club soda. Float orange slices in each glass. Makes 8 (8-ounce) servings.

title: pork chop dinner
directions: Pan-fry chops in skillet just until golden brown.
Place chops in a 9 x 13-inch Pyrex casserole dish.
Slice onion and green pepper over chops.
Sprinkle lightly with salt and pepper.
Mix the soup with 1/2 can of water and pour over casserole.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: pecan oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix together all ingredients, then drop by teaspoonful on well-greased cookie sheet, about 2-inches apart.
Bake in 350° oven for about 12 minutes or until nicely browned.

title: marie's chili con carne
directions: Brown ground beef, onion and green pepper until fully cooked in small amount of cooking oil or butter.
In saucepan combine kidney beans, tomato soup and butter.
Cook until almost done (approximately 1 hour on low heat).
Add ground beef mixture and cook 1/2 hour more on low.
If you love cheese, top each bowl with one slice of cheese just before serving.

title: play dough(non-edible)
directions: Combine ingredients and cook over low heat.
Stir until firm. Take out of pan and knead until smooth.
Can add food coloring into shaped ball or before firm in the pot.

title: apricot whipped cream pie
directions: Wash apricots and cook in water about 20 minutes.
Add tapioca and cook until clear, then add sugar and cook until thick.
Remove from heat and chill.
Pour into baked pastry shell and cover with whipped cream and top with toasted coconut.

title: flour tortillas
directions: Mix flour, baking powder and salt in large mixing bowl.
Next, work in the shortening and add the hot water in order to mix the ingredients together until you form a large dough ball that is not sticky.
Do not over add the hot water.
Add just enough to form a soft dough ball.
Knead the dough until all the ingredients are mixed well and the dough becomes easy to work with.
Allow the dough to sit at room temperature for about 15 minutes.
Make about 24 small dough balls out of the large dough balls and allow them to sit for another 10 minutes.

title: apple wafers
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix sugar, cinnamon and nutmeg; toss with apple slices.
Place wafers on cookie sheet.
Top with 1 cheese slice and two apple slices.
Bake 4 to 5 minutes or until cheese begins to melt.
Serve immediately.

title: cracker dip
directions: Mix altogether and enjoy.

title: lemon pineapple cake
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients.
Beat at medium speed.
Add eggs one at a time beating after each.
Add lemon-lime beverage.
Mix well.
Pour into three (9-inch) cake pans that have been greased and floured.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Remove from pans and let cool completely.
Top with Pineapple Topping.

title: corn cruncher cookies
directions: Cream margarine with fructose, brown sugar, vanilla and egg. Mix soda and salt with flour and stir into creamed mixture.
Stir in cornflake crumbs, oats and coconut.
Roll in balls and flatten with glass dipped in flour.
Bake at 350° for 8 minutes.

title: million dollar pie
directions: Mix Eagle Brand milk and lemon juice.
Stir until thick.
Add pineapple and nuts.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Put into 2 graham cracker pie crusts.
Chill.
Makes 2 pies or one 13 x 9-inch pie.

title: flank steak teriyaki
directions: Mix all ingredients together well.
Take a 1 to 1 1/2 pound piece of flank steak (or round steak or Swiss steak) and make several lengthwise cuts partially through the steak.
Place steak in baking dish and pour marinade over the meat.
Turn several times to spread the marinade.
Cover pan and place in refrigerator, turning meat several times to soak up marinade. (Best if left to marinade overnight.)
Broil or grill to desired doneness.

title: cinnamon mallow apples
directions: Mix imperials, apples and 1 1/2 cups marshmallows in glass baking dish.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.
Stir once or twice.

title: cheesy meat bread
directions: Mix meal, milk, eggs, corn and oil. Pour half of this mixture into greased 9 x 13-inch dish. Brown meat and drain. Place on top of corn mixture. Chop onion and spread on top. Pour remaining mixture over onion. Bake at 350° for 50 minutes. Cover bread with grated cheese and cook until cheese is melted.

title: ambrosia fruit salad
directions: Mix pineapple and pudding together with mixer.
Add Cool Whip and sour cream and mix until well blended.
Stir in fruit and chill.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix bananas until well mashed.
Add sugar and shortening; mix well.
Add eggs and mix.
Add dry ingredients and milk.
Stir in walnuts.
Pour mixture into 2 greased bread pans.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.
Remove from oven and from bread pans.
Allow to cool. Good with a glaze frosting.
Spread on bread while cooling.

title: coconut cream layer pie
directions: In a large mixing bowl, beat cream cheese, sugar, Dream Whip, milk and 2 teaspoons of vanilla until light and fluffy.
Pour into pie shells.
Spread 1 cup of coconut on each pie and chill several hours.
In a large mixing bowl, combine pudding mix, half and half and 1 1/2 teaspoons of vanilla.
Beat until smooth and mixture begins to thicken.
Divide mixture in half and pour over each pie.
Chill until set.
Spread half of Cool Whip over each pie.
Sprinkle each pie with 1/2 cup toasted coconut.

title: bread sticks
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Butter one side of bread.
Place buttered side down on baking sheet.
Cut 1/2-inch wide.
Butter and season. Use any of the following (alone or mixed):
salt, garlic salt, herbs, onion salt, seasoning salt or seed.

title: baptist pie
directions: Combine all ingredients and pour into graham cracker pie crust; refrigerate overnight.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix the two dressings together, half and half.
Mix for the amount you want for your dressing.

title: chili and chips
directions: Heat chili in microwave until warm and bubbly.
Arrange on plate the Fritos or chips and spoon hot chili over them.
Top with shredded lettuce, chopped tomatoes, cheese, salsa and sour cream.

title: caramel brownies
directions: Melt caramels on low heat with 1/3 cup evaporated milk. Grease 9 x 13-inch baking pan. Mix cake mix (powder only) with 1/3 cup evaporated milk and 3/4 cup melted butter.
Spread half the dough on bottom of pan and bake 6 minutes at 350°.
Take out and sprinkle with 1 cup chocolate chips.
Spread the melted caramel over that.
Drop spoonfuls of the rest of the dough over it. Return to oven and bake for 15 to 18 minutes.
Refrigerate 30 minutes before serving.

title: eggplant parmesan
directions: Mix flour, egg, salt and water in bowl.
Dip eggplant in flour mixture coating well.
Fry in deep fat (oil) until brown.
Place a layer of eggplant in deep casserole dish.
Sprinkle with layer of Parmesan, then layer of Ragu sauce.
Repeat layering until all eggplant (almost all) Parmesan and Ragu are used up, ending with layer of Ragu on top.
Sprinkle with Parmesan on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: escalloped potatoes
directions: Combine potatoes with 1/2 cup melted butter, salt, pepper, soup, cheese, onion and sour cream.
Pour mixture into a 3-quart or large flat casserole. Mix together corn flakes and 1/4 cup melted butter. Pour over potato mixture.
Bake 45 minutes in a 350° oven.
Serves 10 to 12.
Can be frozen before baking.

title: soup-pot pie
directions: Wipe 1/2 teaspoon margarine onto a paper towel and spread over inside of a casserole dish (throw towel away).
Pour can of soup into the casserole.
In a small bowl, mix 1 cup Bisquick and 1/3 cup milk.
Pour over top of soup in the casserole dish.
Bake uncovered in oven at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes or until golden on top.

title: pumpkin soup
directions: Melt butter in saucepan.
Add onion, fennel, curry and salt to taste.
Cook until onion is translucent over medium heat.
Add stock and pumpkin and simmer, covered, 15 minutes.
Puree pumpkin mixture in food processor or blender until smooth.
Add cider and mix.
Pour mixture back into saucepan.
Add half and half and heat before serving.
Serves 6.

title: cloud biscuits
directions: Sift together the dry ingredients.
Cut in shortening until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Combine egg and milk; add to flour.
Mix all at once.
Stir until dough follows fork around bowl.
Place by tablespoonfuls on ungreased baking sheet (or roll out and cut with glass).
Bake at 450° for 10 to 14 minutes.
If desired, can chill dough 1 to 3 hours before use.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: apple walnut cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Add eggs, oil, vanilla and lemon juice.
Mix well.
Add apples and walnuts.
Pour into greased and floured pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
When cool, sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: apricot pound cake
directions: Mix
all
ingredients
until smooth.
Pour into greased and floured Bundt pan.
Bake at 325° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: chocolate sauce
directions: In a 1 quart saucepan, combine sugar and cocoa.
Gradually add water.
Bring to a boil.
Add evaporated milk and boil about 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add butter and vanilla and stir until butter melts.
Serve warm.
Cook longer if wish thicker.

title: busy day stew
directions: Mix all ingredients well and place in a baking dish. Bake at 350° for 3 hours. Stir occasionally.

title: salmon sweet
directions: Spray pan with Pam spray.
Place salmon on it and sprinkle with pepper and garlic.
Place 1 orange, lemon and onion slice on each steak.
Place in 350° oven for 30 minutes, covered.
Remove.
Top each steak with pineapple ring.
Pour juice over steaks; cover again and cook for 15 minutes.
Serve at once.
Be gentle to keep fruit in place.
No salt; salmon is a salt water fish.
Serve with rice and green beans.

title: white sauce
directions: Melt butter over low heat in a heavy saucepan.
Blend in flour and seasonings.
Cook over low heat, stirring until mixture is smooth and bubbly.
Remove from heat.
Stir in milk.
Return to heat and bring to boil, stirring constantly.
Boil for 1 minute.

title: cheeseburger logs
directions: Combine minced onion, bread crumbs, egg, milk, salt and prepared mustard; mix well.
Add ground beef and mix thoroughly with
fork.
Divide
into
portions;
shape each portion into a log
around
a
stick of cheese, enclosing cheese completely. Arrange
logs
on
shallow baking pan;
bake at 400° for about 20 minutes or until well browned.
Meanwhile, split, toast and butter
the buns.
Place a cheeseburger log in each bun.

title: french meat pie
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in a large saucepan. Stir until meat loses its pink color. Stir in next 5 ingredients and simmer for 20 minutes. Cook and coarsely mash potatoes, then stir into entire mixture. Put meat mixture into pie shell. Place leftover pie crust on the top of your pie. Brush with beaten egg mixed with a small amount of water. Bake at 425° for 15 minutes and at 350° for 30 minutes until brown.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix Eagle Brand milk and lemon juice.
Add sour cream.
Add fruit and nuts, then Cool Whip, marshmallows and cherries.
Mix all together, then refrigerate until good and cold.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Brown sausage and drain. Take the croissants and pat them out on a cookie sheet (no sides).

Make them solid. Spread sausage on top and put hash browns on top of sausage. Then take beaten eggs and pour over sausage and hash browns and top with Velveeta. (You can shred or cube cheese on top, too.) Put in preheated oven and bake at 350° until cheese is melted and brown. It is excellent reheated.

title: chinese chicken rice salad
directions: Blend soy sauce, mustard and oil.
Add chicken and toss to coat.
Let stand 30 minutes.
Stir in rice, vegetables, eggs and salad dressing.
Spoon onto beds of lettuce.
Top with noodles.

title: sour kraut salad
directions: Combine top five ingredients and mix well.
Combine sugar and vinegar and mix with other ingredients.
Marinate in refrigerator. Keeps well.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix all together until smooth.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix together by hand in order given.
Pour into pie crust. Bake at 350° for approximately 1 hour.

title: creole stuffed peppers
directions: Wash peppers.
Cut thin slices from stem end of each; remove seeds.
If necessary, cut very thin slices from bottom of peppers so they will rest evenly and not topple over.
Place peppers in boiling salted water; remove from heat.
Let stand 5 minutes; drain.
Preheat frypan to 300°.
Melt butter in frypan.
Add ground beef and onion; saute until brown, about 5 minutes.
Place meat mixture in bowl.
Add rice, salt, pepper and 1 can tomato sauce; combine thoroughly.
Stuff peppers with the mixture; place in frypan.
Pour remaining cans of tomato sauce into frypan, spooning some on top of each pepper.
Cover; reduce temperature to low.
Cook for 20 to 25 minutes, or until peppers are tender. Baste occasionally.
Yields 6 servings.

title: lasagne
directions: Brown meats until done and drain; set aside.
Simmer tomatoes, tomato paste, salt, pepper, garlic and then add meat.
Mix together the Ricotta, parsley, eggs, spices, dash of salt and pepper and Parmesan in a bowl.
In lasagne pan, place in alternating layers the noodles, cheese mixture, Mozzarella and meat sauce.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until hot.
Serves 12. Excellent.

title: shrimp casserole
directions: Cook rice according to directions.
Brown onion in melted butter.
Mix the other ingredients together.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: pear and apple muffins
directions: Spray muffin tins with vegetable spray.
Set aside.
Preheat oven to 400°.
Combine flour, baking powder, cinnamon and ginger in a mixing bowl.
Set aside.
Cut pears into chunks and set aside. Mix butter and sugar in bowl.
Beat until blended.
Add eggs and blend.
Alternately add flour mixture and milk, half at a time, until both are blended.
Add pear chunks and applesauce.
Spoon into muffin tin 2/3 full.
Bake 30 minutes.
Cool 5 minutes.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Preheat oven and cookie sheet to 375°.
Boil potatoes until easy to pierce (or open canned yams and pour into bowl).
Beat with mixer until smooth.
Stir in butter and sugar.
Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Mix in spices, salt and milk.
Pour into pie crusts.
Bake on preheated cookie sheet near center of oven for 70 minutes or until knife inserted comes out clean.
Cool on wire rack; garnish with marshmallows, if desired.
Makes two 9-inch pies.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Mix together flour, sugar, baking soda and salt.
Beat well the eggs.
Add the oil and strawberries.
Add liquid to dry ingredients and mix well.
Bake in greased loaf pans at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: bran muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Prepare muffin tins with Crisco. Combine bran and milk.
Sift together the flour, baking powder and sugar. Combine beaten eggs and oil.
Add to the bran and milk. Mix well.
Add dry ingredients all at once.
Stir just enough to mix.
Fill muffin tins 2/3 full with batter and bake 25 to 30 minutes.

title: broken pretzels
directions: Place broken hard pretzels on cookie sheet.
Mix soup mix with melted butter.
Make sure it is well mixed.
Pour over pretzels. Bake in oven at 250° for 30 minutes.
Pretzels will brown.
Cook and place in airtight container.

title: chow chow
directions: Grind all vegetables.
Add salt.
Grind and let stand overnight.
Next morning, drain all liquid off.
Add all other ingredients and bring to boil.
Reduce to simmer and cook for 1 hour, stirring occasionally.
Put in jars and store in dark place for 3 weeks before using.

title: no meat bean dip
directions: Mix taco seasoning with refried beans.
Spread into medium size baking dish.
Mix Tabasco and lemon juice with avocado. Spread over beans.
Next, spread sour cream.
Sprinkle Jack cheese, then Cheddar cheese on top of avocado.
Let set up in refrigerator.
Dip tortilla chips! Yum.

title: impossible bacon, lettuce and tomato pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease pie plate, 10 x 1 1/2-inches.
Layer bacon and cheese in plate.
Beat remaining ingredients except lettuce and tomatoes until smooth, 15 seconds in blender on high or 1 minute with hand beater.
Pour into plate.
Bake until knife inserted in center comes out clean, 30 to 35 minutes.
Cool 5 minutes.
Garnish with lettuce and tomatoes and, if desired, additional bacon and mayonnaise.
Yields 6 servings.

title: selma neil's graham refrigerator pudding
directions: Beat egg yolks. Add sugar and beat well. Add the light cream and cook in double boiler until the custard coats a silver spoon, then remove from heat immediately. Add gelatin (softened in cold water).
Mix well, then add butter and stir until melted. Cool slightly. Fold in pineapple, then fold in egg whites that you have beaten stiff and sweetened with 1/4 cup additional sugar.

title: tuna-noodle casserole
directions: Cook egg noodles according to cooking directions.
Combine remaining ingredients with cooked egg noodles; mix lightly but well. Pour into a 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: kosher dill pickles
directions: Fill fruit jars with cucumbers, either whole or sliced.
Put 1 clove of garlic and a sprig of dill in bottom of each jar and a sprig of dill on top, also 1 teaspoon alum.
In a kettle, bring vinegar, water and pickling salt to a boil.
Pour over pickles and seal.
Process five minutes in boiling water.
Let stand for 6 weeks before using.
Makes 7 quarts of pickles.

title: punch
directions: Mix frozen juices with seltzer and 50/50 instead of tap water. Top with lemon and watermelon sherbet.

title: microwave caramel corn
directions: Spray inside of a large brown grocery bag with vegetable cooking spray (Pam).
Pour popped corn into paper bag.
In a bowl, combine brown sugar, margarine, corn syrup and salt.
Microwave on High 2 1/2 minutes.
Stir; microwave on High for 2 minutes.
Stir in soda and add vanilla.
Pour over popcorn in bag.
Close bag and shake.
Microwave on High for 1 1/2 minutes.
Shake well and microwave for 1 minute more on High.
Shake well.
Add additional popcorn salt, if desired.
Store in airtight container.

title: wedding cake
directions: Put flower of love, good looks and sweet temper into a well-furnished house.
Beat butter of youth to a cream.
Mix together blendness of faults, self-forgetfulness, powdered wits and dry humor into sweet argument.
Then add them to the first mixture.
Pour into gently rippling laughter and common sense. Work it together until all is well mixed, then bake gently forever.

title: good sugarless cookies
directions: Cook the raisins, dates and water for 5 to 6 minutes.
Add oleo.
Cool.
Beat in eggs and vanilla.
Sift in flour and baking soda.
Add nuts, if desired.
Drop by teaspoon on ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake 12 minutes at 350°.
Makes 48 small cookies.

title: homemade egg noodles
directions: Mix ingredients together and knead well. Let set for about 15 minutes and re-knead well. Let set just a few minutes and roll out (thick or thin depending on your preference) in just enough flour so that it doesn't stick to the table. Place on a clean sheet in a cool place. Let rolled out dough dry just enough until you can still roll it into a roll. Slice to desired thickness. Place in plastic bags. Can be kept frozen for up to 6
months.

title: spinach pandango(8 servings)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Brown hamburger; drain grease.
Add mushrooms, salt and pepper.
Simmer for 5 minutes.
Add spinach. Simmer until spinach is thawed.
Drain the juice.
Add mushroom soup, sour cream, garlic and oregano.
Put mixture into a lightly buttered baking dish.
Top with Mozzarella cheese.
Bake for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: oven fried chicken
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Combine yogurt, paprika, thyme, salt, pepper and garlic powder.
Mix well.
Coat chicken with mixture. Chicken may be covered and refrigerated overnight or until baking or bake immediately. Spray shallow roasting pan or jelly roll pan with vegetable spray.
Combine bread crumbs and margarine in shallow dish, mixing well.
Coat chicken in crumbs.
Place in pan. Bake breasts for 25 minutes or until chicken is tender and juices run clear.
Contains 5.3 grams of fat.

title: egg pie or custard
directions: Mix well.
Use flavoring of your choice.
Pour in unbaked pie crust.
Cook at 350° until done.

title: lemon verbena tea loaf
directions: Cream margarine, sugar and eggs.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt.
Add to batter alternately with milk.
Add lemon juice and lemon verbena leaves.
Bake in greased and floured loaf pan for 1 hour at 350°.

title: easy pineapple party punch
directions: The day before, add one maraschino cherry to each well of an ice cube tray, or carefully arrange cherries in a Jell-O ring mold.
Fill with water and freeze overnight.
Mix the rest of ingredients in a large punch bowl.
Then add ice cubes or mold with cherries or 1 cup of ice cream sherbet (rainbow, orange or pineapple).

title: m&m's cookies
directions: Blend shortening and sugars in a large bowl.
Beat in vanilla and eggs.
Add dry ingredients.
Stir in 1/2 cup M&M's.
Place on cookie sheet.
Decorate tops with remaining candy.
Cracking should occur.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes until golden brown. Makes 6 dozen.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Mix in egg and flavorings. Measure flour; blend in dry ingredients.
Refrigerate dough 2 to 3 hours until chilled.
Roll dough to about 3/16-inch thick.
Cut into shapes with cookie cutter that has been dipped in flour. Sprinkle with sugar.
Place on greased baking sheet.
Bake at 375° for 7 to 8 minutes.

title: beef bourguignon
directions: Mix well. Pour into covered casserole. Bake 4 hours at 250° or 3 hours at 300°. Serve over rice or chow mein noodles.
Serves 4.

title: vegetable trio
directions: Drain beans and peas.
Place in casserole.
Mix remaining ingredients, except onion rings.
Add to bean mixture; stir until mixed.
Place onion rings over top.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 20 minutes.
Bread crumbs may be used instead of onion rings.

title: cherry cream pretzel pie
directions: In a 13 x 9-inch pan, press mixture of pretzels, 3 tablespoons sugar and margarine.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
When this crust is cool, cover with mixture of cream cheese, 1 cup sugar and 8 ounces of Cool Whip.
Mix together jello, 2 cups boiling water, 1 cup cold water and 1 can cherry pie filling.
Allow this mixture to cool until partially set.
Pour on top of cream cheese mixture.

title: basic ice cream mix
directions: Beat eggs slightly.
Add other ingredients.
Place in ice cream freezer cylinder and add enough whole milk to fill cylinder to freeze line.
Any flavors desired may be added to mix (i.e., 1 can Hershey's chocolate syrup, 2 to 3 cups peaches, etc.).

title: hot cheese dip
directions: Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until cheese melts.

title: pisto(cuban cookery)
directions: Cut potatoes and pork into small cubes and fry.
Cut ham in small pieces.
Fry onion, green pepper and garlic in oil.
Add tomato sauce, cut pimentos and dry wine.
Let tomato sauce and wine mixture set for a while.
Add potatoes, pork, shrimp, ham and beaten eggs with the salt and pepper.
Keep beating mixture on stove, stirring constantly.
When the egg mixture begins to thicken, add the green peas.
Continue stirring until the egg mixture is thick, but do not let it get too dry.
Serve immediately with white rice.
Serves 8.

title: corn pudding
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Lightly grease a 1 1/2-quart casserole. In a large bowl, combine corn and eggs.
Mix well.
Combine flour, salt, pepper, sugar and nutmeg.
Stir into corn mixture.
Add butter and cream; mix well.
Pour into prepared casserole.
Set casserole in pan; pour hot water to 1-inch depth around casserole. Bake, uncovered, for 1 hour and 10 minutes or until pudding is firm and knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Serve hot.
Makes 8 servings.

title: ice cream
directions: Take ice and cream, put it in the freezer for 1 hour.
Take it out till it's not icy anymore, then eat it which is the best part.

title: mom's butter cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Mix all ingredients together in a large bowl. Using a cookie press, press cookies onto a cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 9 minutes. Watch closely as the cookies burn easily.

title: bridal salad(serves 12, must do ahead)
directions: Combine pretzels, margarine and 3 tablespoons sugar.
Press mixture in bottom of well oiled 12 x 9-inch dish.
Bake 12 minutes at 400°.
Cool.

title: apple pie
directions: Combine sugar, flour, spices and salt.
Mix with apples.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Sprinkle with sugar and place butter all around on top.
Put second pie pastry on top.
Cut slits to let steam escape.
Bake at 400° for 50 minutes or until done.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Cube Velveeta cheese and melt in microwave.
Mix together the cheese, picante sauce, milk and soup.
Drain string beans and add to cheese mixture.
Pour into casserole dish and bake for 25 minutes at 350°.
Sprinkle onion rings on top and bake for 5 minutes more.
Serves 6 to 8 people.

title: rhubarb crisp
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Place rhubarb in ungreased baking dish, 13 x 9 x 1 1/2-inch.
Sprinkle with salt, if desired.
Mix sugar, flour and cinnamon in large bowl.
Cut butter into mixture until it resembles coarse crumbs.
Sprinkle over rhubarb.
Bake 40 to 50 minutes or until topping is golden brown.
Serve warm with light or whipped cream.
Serves 6.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Cook broccoli; drain. Saute onion in butter until soft but not brown. Stir in rice, soup and broccoli. Stir in a little cheese, if desired. Butter shallow 1 1/2-quart casserole dish. Place ingredients in prepared dish. Top with 1/2 cup of grated cheese. Cook in 350° oven for 30 minutes or until slightly browned or bubbly.

title: homemade vegetable soup
directions: Mix ground chuck and other meat of your choice together.
Cut large onion into small pieces.
Boil these ingredients in big boiler; add salt and pepper to season.
Pour off first water to remove some grease.
Add water back to boiler.
Add all other vegetables and tomato sauce.
Season again with salt, pepper and garlic salt.
Cook all this together for 1 hour on medium heat. Serves 6; if any leftover, freeze and serve at a later date.

title: jackie cougan
directions: Brown hamburger with onion soup mix.
In 9 x 13-inch pan, layer hamburger, corn and potatoes.
Top with shredded cheese. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: In a 6-quart boiler, boil chicken breasts until done.
Remove and let cool.
Remove chicken from bone.
In another 6-quart boiler, melt butter, then add onion and cook until tender.
Add salt and pepper.
Add flour; let cook about 1 minute.
Pour in 1 quart chicken broth and 1/2 gallon milk.
Cook until it begins to thicken.
Add mixed vegetables and chicken.
Cook, uncovered, for 5 minutes.
Pour in 4 of the unbaked pie crusts.
Use the remaining pie crust to put on top.
Bake in a 350° oven until golden brown. Makes 4 deep dish pies.

title: popcorn cake
directions: Pop the corn.
Melt oil and butter.
Add marshmallows over low heat.
Mix nuts, M&M's and popcorn.
Pour melted ingredients over mixture and stir thoroughly.
Press into greased Bundt pan.
Cool thoroughly 12 hours in refrigerator.
Remove and slice.
Can use angel food cake pan or 2 loaf pans.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Spray 4 x 9-inch baking dish with cooking spray.
Spread raw rice evenly in bottom of dish. Sprinkle onion soup mix over rice.
Place chicken over soup and rice mixture.
Mix cream of chicken soup and water, then pour over all.
Cover tightly.
Bake at 400° for 1 1/4 hours.

title: mrs. field's cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Cream the butter and sugars. Beat in eggs and vanilla. Stir in dry ingredients.
By hand, stir in chocolates and nuts.
Make golf ball size cookies.
Place 2-inches apart on cookie sheets.
Bake at 375° for 6 minutes.
Makes 9 to 10 dozen.

title: rice salad with alfalfa sprouts
directions: In large bowl, combine rice, peas, scallions and spinach. In a small bowl, mix together oil, lemon juice and pulp, basil, oregano and mustard.
Toss half of the dressing with the rice mixture, then arrange sprouts on top of rice and drizzle the remaining dressing over them.
(Sprouts are hot, tossed with rice, because they tend to mat and tangle when mixed.)
Serve at room temperature in individual salad bowls. Makes 4 servings.

title: chinese chews
directions: Mix first three ingredients and press in bottom of a 10 x 10-inch pan.
Bake at 375° about 10 minutes.

title: bonbons
directions: Mix powdered sugar, milk, coconut, margarine, pecans and cherries.
Mixture will be stiff.
(I mix with my hands.) Roll into balls between the size of Whoppers and walnuts.
Let one ball set for 1 to 2 minutes and if ball squats, mix in more powdered sugar.
Finish rolling balls onto waxed paper.
Let dry 30 minutes and turn balls over to dry on other side.
Melt chocolate chips and paraffin wax in double boiler.
Use toothpicks to dip balls into chocolate.
Let dry on waxed paper.
Store in airtight containers.
Great for Christmas!

title: green bean salad
directions: Mix first 9 ingredients in large bowl.
Mix remaining ingredients and bring to boil for 3 minutes.
Cool completely. Pour over vegetables.
Store in airtight bowl.
Good for many days.

title: best ever chocolate cream pie
directions: Mix and boil in double boiler until thick.
Keep stirring until smooth.
Pour in baked crust.
Serve with Cool Whip or whipped cream.

title: chocolate chip bars
directions: Cream oleo or butter with sugars.
Add vanilla and eggs; mix well.
Add flour and soda; mix well.
Add chocolate chips and mix well.
Bake at 350° in a 9 x 13-inch greased pan for 30 minutes. Cool and cut into squares.

title: world's best bean dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except cheese.
Place in casserole.
Top with layer of Jack cheese and layer of Cheddar cheese.
Heat until bubbly in a 350° oven.

title: scalloped ham and cabbage casserole
directions: Cook cabbage in boiling water for 6 to 8 minutes.
Drain. Saute ham and onion in butter in skillet.
Stir in flour.
Add milk, stirring constantly until mixture thickens.
Add 3/4 cup cheese, celery seed and salt.
Place layers of cabbage alternately with layers of ham mixture in a 2-quart casserole.
Combine bread crumbs, butter and remaining cheese.
Sprinkle over top and bake at 350° until top is golden brown.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake at 350° until done for about 35 minutes.
Cool before icing.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Brown hamburger meat with onions and green peppers.
Add other ingredients; let simmer for 1/2 hour.
Serve on buns.

title: avocado salad
directions: Cut avocado in half and take out seeds.
Fill inside of each half with 1/3 cup cottage cheese.
Drizzle 1 tablespoon French dressing over cottage cheese.
Top with maraschino cherry.

title: dutch slaw
directions: Shred cabbage fine.
Add water to cover and cook until tender.
Beat egg; add sugar, salt, pepper and vinegar.
Pour over drained, cooked cabbage.
Heat for 5 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: beanburgers
directions: Brown ground beef in olive oil; add onion, catsup and Worcestershire sauce. Add sufficient water to prevent burning and simmer 20 minutes. Add kidney beans; salt and pepper to taste. Garlic powder and chili powder or oregano may be added. Continue simmering about 30 minutes more. Serve on buns, using only one-half of bun. Top with slice of cheese and melt in hot oven. Serve hot.

title: ground chuck and bean casserole
directions: In large skillet, brown chuck and onion.
Drain off grease. In a large casserole dish, combine chuck mixture with the pork and beans, mustard, catsup and vinegar.
Mix well.
Place bacon strips across the top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: coconut pound cake
directions: Have butter and eggs at room temperature.
Grease, line bottom with wax paper, grease paper and flour a 10-inch tube pan. Preheat oven to 325°.
Cream butter, shortening and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Sift flour and salt together; add alternately to creamed mixture with milk, starting and ending with flour.
Beat until smooth.
Add flavorings.
Remove bowl from mixer; fold in coconut.
Pour into prepared pan and smooth top.
Bake for 1 hour and 30 to 35 minutes, until golden brown, top springs back when touched lightly, cake shrinks from sides of pan and a cake tester inserted in center comes out clean.
Place on wire rack; poke holes all over with a toothpick.
Pour topping over while cake is still warm.
Cool cake completely before removing from pan.

title: chocolate eclair
directions: Mix pudding with milk, then fold in Cool Whip.
Line 9 x 13-inch pan with graham crackers; cover with half the pudding mixture.
Layer of graham crackers, then the other half of pudding mixture, layer of graham crackers, then cover with chocolate icing. Make the day before so crackers will soften.

title: garlic spread
directions: Wrap garlic clove in foil and bake in oven for 30 minutes at 190°.
Squeeze clove to remove cooked garlic.
Mix with a pinch of thyme and the margarine.
Spread on roll, toast, bagel, etc.

title: red chicken stew
directions: Boil chicken and debone.
Remove skin of chicken before boiling.
Place chicken pieces in saucepan and cover with broth from boiling.
Add tomato sauce, most of the bottle of ketchup, salt, pepper, hot sauce, Worcestershire sauce and chopped onion. Cook low on simmer for 30 to 45 minutes.
Water may be added if stew is too thick.
Serve over rice or as stew.

title: pumpkin cake roll
directions: Beat eggs on high speed of mixer for 5 minutes.
Gradually beat in sugar.
Stir in pumpkin and lemon juice.
Combine dry ingredients and fold into first mixture.
Spread on greased and floured pan, 15 x 10 x 1-inch.
Top with walnuts.
Bake at 375° in preheated oven for 15 minutes.
Turn out on tea towel that has been sprinkled with powdered sugar (spread with hand).
Starting at the narrow end, roll towel and cake together.
Cool in refrigerator.

title: cream cheese frosting
directions: In a mixing bowl, beat together cream cheese, margarine or butter and vanilla.
Beat until light and fluffy.
Gradually add 2 cups of powdered sugar, beating well.
Slowly beat in enough of the remaining sugar to make the frosting spreadable.
Frost the cake, topping with walnut halves.
Cover and store in the refrigerator.

title: killer breakfast or brunch
directions: Make this dish the night before.
Place bread in bottom of a greased pan.
Mix eggs, cheese, milk, meats and mushrooms.
Pour over bread.
In the morning, bake in a 350° oven for 35 to 40 minutes. You may use any combination of meats and vegetables you like.

title: fruit dip
directions: Drain pineapple (reserve 2 or 3 tablespoons liquid).
Mix all ingredients.
Serve with fresh fruit.

title: beef and shrimp stir-fry
directions: Combine first 8 ingredients in a medium saucepan and bring to a boil; reduce heat, and simmer 30 minutes.
Remove from heat and pour liquid through a wire mesh strainer into a 2-cup liquid measuring cup, discarding solids.
Return broth mixture to saucepan.
Combine cornstarch and water, stirring until smooth; stir into broth mixture and bring to a boil.
Cook 1 minute; remove from heat.
Set broth mixture aside.
Peel and devein shrimp; set aside.
Heat olive oil in a cast-iron wok 10 to 15 minutes or until hot.
Add shrimp, beef and broccoli; cook 1 to 2 minutes, stirring constantly.
Add zucchini and remaining vegetables; cook 2 minutes, stirring constantly.
Add broth mixture and cook until thoroughly heated.
Serve over rice.
Yields 4 servings.

title: instant hot chocolate
directions: Mix well; store. Add to hot water to taste.

title: oatmeal-coconut cookies
directions: Sift together the flour, sugar, baking powder, soda and salt. Add brown sugar, shortening, eggs and vanilla; beat well.
Stir in oats, pecans and coconut.
Roll dough in small balls and dip in sugar.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 14 minutes.
Makes 8 to 9 dozen.

title: banana split dessert
directions: Mix 2 cups crushed wafers and 1 stick melted margarine.
Press into a 9
x 13-inch pan and chill.
Mix powdered sugar with 1 stick margarine and softened cream cheese.
(Best to mix with mixer.)
Spread mixture over cooled crumbs.
Slice bananas over mixture.
Drain pineapple and spread over bananas.
Top with Cool Whip.
Garnish with cherries or chocolate syrup drizzled over all. Sprinkle with nuts.
Enjoy!

title: hot cider
directions: Simmer in crock-pot for 2 hours.

title: blueberry nectarine smoothie
directions: Combine all ingredients in blender. Blend at high speed until ice is dissolved. May substitute other fruits and flavored yogurts as desired.

title: punch for a bunch
directions: Combine juice concentrates and water in a gallon container. Stir well to mix.
Just before serving, add soft drink.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown beef, onions and celery in heavy skillet.
Arrange beef mixture and noodles in layers in 2-quart casserole.
Combine soups, milk and seasonings.
Pour over beef and noodles (stir a little).
Cover and bake in slow (325°) oven for 1 hour.
Uncover and sprinkle with bread crumbs.
Bake 10 minutes or until brown. Serves 6.

title: mock apple pie(no apples needed)
directions: Roll out bottom crust and fit into 9-inch pie pan.
Break Ritz crackers coarsely into pastry-lined plate.

title: pecan pie
directions: In small bowl of mixer, beat eggs slightly. Mix in syrup, sugar, butter, vanilla and salt; mix well. Stir in pecans. Pour into pie crust. Bake for approximately 45 minutes or until filling is set. Makes 6 servings.

title: beef broccoli pie
directions: In skillet, brown beef and onion; drain off fat.
Stir in flour, salt and garlic salt.
Add milk and cream cheese; cook and stir until mixture is thickened and smooth.
Add a moderate amount of hot mixture to beaten egg; return to mixture in skillet.
Cook and stir over medium heat for 1-2 min. or until thick.
Stir in well-drained broccoli.
Unroll one pkg. of crescent rolls.
On floured surface, place the 4 sections of dough together, forming a 12x7 rectangle.
Seal edges and perforations together.
Roll to a 12-inch square.
Fit into a 9-inch pie plate; trim.
Spoon meat mixture into shell.
Cut Monterey Jack cheese in slices; arrange slices atop meat mixture.
Roll second pkg. of rolls to 12-inch square as before.
Place on top of filling.
Trim and seal edges with fork; cut slits for escape of steam.
Brush top of pie with a little milk.
Bake at 350 degrees for 40 min.
If pastry browns too quickly, cover with foil the last 20 min.
Let stand 10 min. before serving.

title: tuna fish casserole
directions: While potatoes cook, rinse and chop celery, green pepper and onion.
Preheat oven to 350°.
In large bowl, mash hot potatoes with 1/2 cup evaporated milk.
(Leave it lumpy.)
Mix in fish, onion, celery, green pepper, hot sauce and the other 1/2 cup milk. Spoon into sprayed baking dish.
Sprinkle top with Parmesan cheese and black pepper.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Serves 6. Keeps well in refrigerator but does not freeze.
Reheat in 350° oven for 15 minutes.

title: double blueberry pancakes
directions: Combine milk, corn syrup, corn oil and egg in mixing bowl. Add pancake mix; stir until dry ingredients are moistened. Batter will be lumpy.
Stir in blueberries and cottage cheese carefully.
Pour 1/4 cup of batter for each pancake on hot griddle; cook until brown, turning once.
Serve with blueberry syrup.
Makes 8 pancakes.

title: banana split cake
directions: First Layer:
Mix graham cracker crumbs and melted oleo. Press in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: pumpkin bread(yields 9 x 5 x 3 loaf)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream sugar and oil* well.
Add eggs and beat vigorously.
Add pumpkin and stir.
Mix dry ingredients together and add to first mixture, stirring well after each addition.
May add nuts or raisins, if desired.
Fresh pumpkin may be substituted for canned.
Put in greased and floured 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan or two smaller pans.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Let cool in pan.

title: sister ruth's calico beans
directions: Brown and drain bacon, hamburger and onion.
Combine all ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: hamburger tin foil dinner
directions: Take piece of foil for each dinner (two).
In each foil, place small amount of each of the listed ingredients.
Top each dinner with 1/2 can condensed cream of mushroom soup.
Bake at 400° for 1/2 hour.

title: fast fiesta soup
directions: In a saucepan, combine tomatoes, corn and beans; heat through. Garnish servings with cheese and sour cream, if desired. Yield: 4 servings.

title: cake dessert
directions: Into a one-piece, greased tube pan, put the following ingredients, one on top of the other:
pineapple, pie filling and cake mix (dry).
Sprinkle pecans over all.
On top, dot with margarine in small pieces.
Bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour.
Serve warm or cold.

title: sweet pickles
directions: Soak cucumbers in salt water overnight (1/3 cup salt).
Drain and dry.
Boil vinegar, water and sugar 10 minutes or until clear. Add cucumbers and let stand over low fire until they lose their grass green color.
Place 1 teaspoon mixed spices and a few dill on bottom of jar.
Fill with pickles and hot syrup and place a few dill on top.
Seal.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Cook cabbage until tender; drain off liquid. Add sugar, salt, peppers and margarine to cooked cabbage. Cook ground beef; season with salt, white pepper and onions until brown. Drain off fat. Mix soup and water in small bowl with a dash of white pepper. Pour cabbage in casserole dish. Top with ground beef mixture. Pour soup mixture over ground beef, all the way to the edge. Bake until bubbly, about 30 to 35 minutes.

title: cold broccoli salad
directions: Fry, dice and pat dry the bacon.
Mix with cut flowerets, green onions and raisins.
Refrigerate until needed.

title: lo-cal - lo-fat brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spray Pam on 8-inch square pan.
In mixing bowl, beat egg and egg white.
Add sugar, Sweet 'N Low, vanilla and chocolate extract and beat well.
Beat in cocoa and applesauce.
With wooden spoon, gently fold in mixture of flour, baking powder and salt.
Do not beat.
Pour into pan and bake for 15 minutes.
When cool, cut into 9 pieces.
Each piece = 42 cal. and 1 gram fat.

title: mama's pumpkin pie
directions: Cook fresh pumpkin and put through food press.
Do not peel pumpkin.

title: apple crows nest
directions: Arrange apples in greased pie tin and dot with butter. Sprinkle with 1 tablespoon sugar and 1 1/2 teaspoons cinnamon. Sift flour, baking powder, salt and 1/4 cup sugar together twice. Cut in shortening.
Add enough milk gradually to make a soft dough.
Spread over apples.
Bake in hot oven at 400° until apples are tender.
Turn out upside down.
Serve hot with whipped cream. Sprinkle cinnamon and chopped nuts.
Serves 6.

title: italian spaghetti
directions: Saute vegetables in dressing.
Add cream cheese, milk and Mozzarella cheese; stir over low heat until cheese is melted. Stir in Parmesan cheese.
Pour over hot spaghetti and bacon. Sprinkle with additional Parmesan cheese, if desired.
Makes 6 servings.

title: lillian's chocolate pie
directions: Mix cocoa, sugar, flour and salt together.
Stir in 1/4 cup milk until ingredients are moistened.
Add remaining milk, butter and egg yolks.
Cook until thickened, stirring constantly.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Beat 2 egg whites until frothy.
Add 2 tablespoons sugar; continue beating and beat until egg whites form peaks.
Spread on pie; brown lightly in 325° oven.

title: icebox pies
directions: Line bottom of 3 pie pans with crushed vanilla wafers.
Stand remaining wafers around sides of pan.
Mix together in saucepan the sugar, pineapple juice and egg whites; bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Remove from stove; add the jello.
Whip the evaporated milk; sweeten to taste.
Add to the jello mixture and mix thoroughly.
Let stand in the refrigerator until firm.

title: dirt cake
directions: Will also need medium plastic flowerpot, fake flowers, leaves and gummy worms.

title: italian zeppoli
directions: Mix all ingredients together in bowl until smooth.

title: pie crust
directions: Beat egg.

Add vinegar and enough water to equal one cup. Mix flour, salt and shortening until it looks like meal (fine crumbs). Add liquids to flour and mix well. Separate into 6 balls and place into ziploc bags and freeze.
Ready to roll out and bake.

title: micro meat loaf
directions: Mix beef, milk, soup mix, egg, crumbs, salt, pepper and 3 tablespoons ketchup.
Form in shallow microwave-safe loaf pan. Mix the brown sugar, 3 tablespoons ketchup and mustard.
Spread over meat.
Microwave 12 to 14 minutes, rotating once.
Remove from oven.
Cover with wax paper; let stand 10 minutes.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix all together while potatoes are frozen.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch greased baking pan.
Melt 1 stick margarine and mix with 1 1/2 cups crushed corn flakes.
Sprinkle on top of potatoes.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour or until bubbly.

title: fruit salad
directions: Use "lite" fruit and sugar-free pudding for low calories. Drain juice from fruit in a large bowl.
Pour pudding, juice and Tang mixture over fruit and mix well.
Chill.
Serves 20.

title: mac's peach blossoms
directions: Mix and pour over ice.
Yields 1 gallon.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Mix together the pretzels, melted margarine and 4 tablespoons of sugar; pat into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 400° for 8 minutes; cool.
Mix together the cream cheese, 1 cup sugar and Cool Whip, spread over the cooled pretzel crust and refrigerate.
Mix the jello and water, stir until dissolved.
Cool and add the strawberries.
Place strawberry mixture in the refrigerator until almost set.
Pour over the cream cheese mixture and refrigerate until serving time.

title: microwave turkham veggie rolls
directions: Break off tough ends of asparagus.
Place tender asparagus in 2 quart microwavable casserole.
Add water.
Cover and microwave on High (100%) until tender, 7 to 8 minutes; drain.

title: delicious green peas
directions: Saute onion and pepper in butter.
Add remaining ingredients and place in buttered casserole (13 x 9 x 2-inches).
Top with bread crumbs or dressing.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Makes 8 servings.

title: bean casserole
directions: Drain all beans, except pork and beans.
Put in a large casserole.
Simmer brown sugar, mustard, vinegar, bacon and onions for 20 minutes.
Add to the beans and stir to mix.
Bake for 2 hours at 325°.

title: cheese bobs
directions: Wrap each cheese cube with a strip of bacon and broil on the end of a stick or fork over coals until bacon is crisp and cheese melted.

title: poppy seed-lemon loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 1 (9 x 5-inch) loaf pan or 3 (5 1/2 x 3-inch) loaf pans.
Into bowl, sift together flour, sugar, baking powder, mace, ginger and salt.
Add poppy seed; blend well.
In another bowl, beat egg, buttermilk, oil and lemon peel. Add flour mixture and stir until blended.
Pour batter into prepared loaf pan; bake 45 to 50 minutes or until wooden toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool in pan 5 minutes on wire rack.
In small bowl, combine powdered sugar and lemon juice for glaze; blend well.
Turn bread out of pan onto rack and brush top and sides with glaze; cool completely before serving.

title: go cola cake
directions: Combine all ingredients, except cola and marshmallows, in a large mixing bowl.
Blend at low speed, then beat one minute at medium speed.
Add cola and blend well.
Fold in marshmallows. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: bordeaux relish
directions: Chop tomatoes, onions and peppers.
Drain.
Add spices and vinegar.
Boil 20 minutes, then add chopped cabbage.
Stir well. Put in hot sterile canning jars and seal.
Do not process.

title: old fashioned sugar cookies
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder, salt, soda and sugar.
Cut in shortening until mixture resembles coarse meal.
Blend in eggs, milk and vanilla.
Roll out on floured board.
Cut with cookie cutters and place on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake at 375° for about 8 minutes.

title: vanilla peach pie
directions: Position rack in lowest third of oven and preheat to 400 degrees.
Combine peaches, 1/2 cup sugar, brown sugar, flour and cardamom in large bowl.
Scrape in seeds from vanilla bean; discard bean.
Toss to blend well.
Let stand until dry ingredients are moistened, about 15 minutes.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix together all ingredients except the pudding. When you have everything mixed well, add the pudding dry to the mixture and mix well again.

title: watergate salad
directions: Combine Cool Whip and pudding.
Mix, then add remaining ingredients and stir.
Pour into bowl; refrigerate.

title: a.b.c. vegetable soup
directions: Heat oil in a saucepan over medium heat.
Add onion and garlic and cook until the onion is soft, about 2 minutes.
Stir occasionally.
Add chicken broth, tomato, pasta and parsley to the saucepan.
Bring liquid to a boil; reduce heat and simmer for 10 minutes.
Add broccoli, carrots and celery to soup; cook 10 minutes.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese if desired.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Mix together ingredients.
Pour into 10-inch pie shell.
Bake in oven at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: yum yum bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a mixing bowl, cream together margarine, sugar, egg yolks and water.
Beat well with electric mixer; add vanilla.
Sift flour, baking soda and salt together; fold into batter; mix well.
Press dough into bottom of a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour entire package of chocolate chips over dough, the press into dough.
In another bowl, beat 2 egg whites until stiff; add 1 cup brown sugar and beat well.
Spread mixture over chocolate chips making peaks and swirls.
Sprinkle with finely chopped nuts.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Cool completely before cutting.
Store in an airtight container.

title: biscuit pudding
directions: One 10 count can biscuits baked according to package directions and crumbled may be used for crumbled biscuits.

title: mom's sweet pickles
directions: Buy one large jar of good kosher dill pickles.
Drain well and cut into chunks.
Boil sugar, vinegar and a piece or two of cinnamon bark.
Make a thick syrup.
Cool and pour over pickles. Let stand a week or several days.
They are delicious.

title: myrtle's banana bread(mrs. peter russell)
directions: Do not use an electric mixer.

title: potato casserole
directions: Peel and dice potatoes which have been boiled in jackets until tender.
Combine with cottage cheese, sour cream, onion and seasonings.
Pour into a lightly greased 1 1/2-quart baking dish. Top with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix with hands in casserole dish. Put pats of butter on top. Bake at 350 degrees 1-1 1/2 hours.

title: sourdough biscuits
directions: Combine buttermilk, yeast and cooking oil; add flour.
Mix until dough is in a ball.
Pinch off dough to make biscuits. Place in lightly greased pan.
Bake at 350° until brown.
Store remaining dough in an airtight container in refrigerator.

title: cactus beef
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Cook in oven in covered casserole for 3 1/2 hours at 325°.
Serve over cooked noodles or rice.
Serves 8.

title: bean dip
directions: Cut cheese into chunks and mix with tomatoes and peppers and beans. Cook in microwave 1 minute at a time, stirring after each minute, until cheese is melted. A pound of cooked and drained ground beef may also be added for a change.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix together and bake in 9 x 13-inch glass dish at 350° for 45 minutes or microwave 25 minutes.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Brown sausage, pepper, onion and celery.
Drain off grease. Boil rice for seven minutes.
(Boil rice in soup mix and water.) Mix together all ingredients and bake one hour at 350° in covered casserole dish.

title: yummy s'mores dessert
directions: On 6 heatproof dessert serving plates, place 2 graham crackers side by side.
Cover crackers with chocolate, breaking up to fit and dividing evenly.
Top each cracker with 2 marshmallow halves, cut sides down.
Place plates on baking sheets.
Bake about 2 minutes or until tops of marshmallows are golden.
Watch carefully!!
Serves 6.

title: hot, hot, chili con queso
directions: Combine all ingredients, except cheese, in a 2 1/2-quart, covered casserole.
Cook in microwave oven for 45 minutes until sauce is thick enough for dipping.
Stir every 10 minutes.
Stir in cheese.
Serve as hot dip with tortilla chips.
Yields 3 cups.

title: apricot jello salad
directions: Drain juice from fruit and set aside.
Dissolve Jell-O in 2 cups boiling water, add fruit. Pour mixture into oblong dish and chill.
Spread on topping and sprinkle cheese on top.

title: strawberry delights
directions: Mix all ingredients together, including 1/2 of juice from pineapple.
Use a large bowl and chill until firm.

title: toffee
directions: Melt butter over low heat.
Stir in sugar; stir until butter and sugar are not separated any more.
Blend in nuts, water and syrup.
Place candy thermometer in mixture and cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until it reaches 300°.
Remove from heat and stir in vanilla.
Pour onto well buttered pan and let cool.
You can melt chocolate and spread over top.
Break into pieces and enjoy!

title: buffalo chicken wings
directions: Blend all ingredients and add wings for 24 hours.
Line 2 shallow pans with foil.
Drain chicken and roast for 40 to 60 minutes at 450°.
Turn every 15 minutes and baste with reserved liquid.

title: easter eggs
directions: Cook potatoes and measure 1/2 cup of potatoes; add butter and cool.
Add vanilla and gradually the sugar.
Knead and shape into eggs, then chill.
Melt chocolate in double boiler.
Add melted paraffin.
Dip eggs in chocolate and cool on wax paper and decorate.

title: dirt cake
directions: Line a clay pot with clear wrap.
Layer cookies, whipped cream and chocolate pudding.
End with cookies.
put some gummy worms in and on top.

title: impossible quiche
directions: Mix milk, Bisquick and eggs with mixer or by hand.
Pour over the remaining ingredients that have been placed in the bottom of a 9 to 10-inch or 11-inch quiche pie dish that has been sprayed with Pam.
Deep dish pie dish is best.
Cook at 400° for 35 to 50 minutes or until golden brown.
Insert knife to see if done.
If it comes out clean, it's done.

title: microwave meat loaf ring
directions: Mix first three ingredients together and set aside.
Then combine the rest of ingredients.
Put the sugar and beef mixture together, stirring until well mixed.
Place mixture in a 6-cup microwave-proof ring mold.
(A ring mold can be made with a microwave-proof bowl and a glass placed in center.)
Pour the reserved 2 ounces tomato sauce over the meat mixture.
Cook on High for 12 to 14 minutes or until done (time may vary according to your microwave.)
Yields 6 servings.

title: raw vegetable dip
directions: Mix well and serve with assorted raw vegetables.
Yields 2 cups.

title: crock-pot roast
directions: Pour 1 can of soup into the bottom of crock-pot.
Add 1/2 package of dry soup mix and place roast on top.
Pour remaining soup mix on roast and then other can of soup.
Turn crock-pot on high for first 3 hours of cooking time.
