Add potatoes and carrots and turn on low.
Cook until potatoes and carrots are tender.
I cook mine all day.
The meat will be very tender, no need to slice.

title: orange marmalade gingerbread
directions: Sift the flour, baking powder, baking soda, cinnamon, ginger and salt together.
Cream the shortening.
Add egg and mix well. Add molasses and marmalade and beat thoroughly.
Add sifted dry ingredients and hot water alternately in small amounts, beating well after each addition.
Pour into greased 8 x 8-inch pan and bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Wash strawberries before capping.
Set aside a few of the best ones for garnish.
Remove caps from remaining berries and place half of them in a saucepan.
Add 1 cup of sugar.
Using a pastry blender or potato masher, crush berries in saucepan.
Combine cornstarch and lemon juice; add to berry mixture.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens and becomes transparent.
While mixture is hot, add gelatin.
Place 2 or 3 tablespoons of cooled mixture in bottom of pastry shell.
Fill shell with halved or whole strawberries.
Pour remaining cooled glaze over berries.
Refrigerate for several hours (at least 2 or 3).
Before serving, whip the cream with 3 tablespoons of sugar and 1 teaspoon of vanilla.
Spread on pie.
Add fresh strawberries reserved for garnish.

title: baked potato casserole
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients.
Place in casserole.
Top with bacon.
Bake 1 hour at 325°.

title: honey mustard salad dressing
directions: Mix well and refrigerate.

title: zesty potatoes
directions: Cook the potatoes in 1 inch boiling salt water (1/2 teaspoon salt to 1 cup water) just until tender.
While hot, cut unpared potatoes diagonally into 1/2-inch slices.
Place in shallow glass dish.
Pour the salad dressing over hot slices.
Let stand 1 hour, turning slices once.
Place on grill, 3 inches from hot coals. Cook 8 to 10 minutes on each side, or until golden brown.
Season with 1 teaspoon salt and 1/4 teaspoon pepper after turning.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: graveyard shift dip
directions: Spread top of "brick" with horseradish.
Pour apricot or pineapple jam over the whole mess.
Now slice off a slab and smear on a Ritz type cracker.
Dare you to bite into it. Double dare you to eat just one!!!

title: german potato salad
directions: Fill 3 1/2-quart pan with potatoes.
Cook potatoes with jackets on until firm, but not mushy.
Cook bacon until crisp.
Drain. Saute sliced onions in bacon grease until golden brown.
Add vinegar, water, sugar and flour.
Stir until thickened.
If too much grease, spoon off excess.
Crumble bacon into mixture.
Peel and slice potatoes, a few at a time, into mixture.
Add salt and pepper to taste and mix.
Repeat until all potatoes are sliced into mixture.
Make the night before to enable flavor to go through potatoes.
Reheat before serving, stirring to avoid sticking to bottom of pan.

title: good old pudding(this pudding has a great sauce to add just before serving.)
directions: Mix in a bowl the bread crumbs, milk, raisins and butter.
In a separate dish, mix remaining ingredients, then combine and mix well.
Pour into a greased baking dish and bake in a 350° oven until firm, 25 to 30 minutes.
Just before serving, add the following sauce.

title: taco dip
directions: Beat ingredients.
Garnish with diced tomatoes, black olives, scallions and shredded Cheddar cheese.
Serve with nacho chips.

title: best ever chicken
directions: Boil chicken until tender.
When cool, remove meat and cut finely.
Make dressing of stale bread soaked with chicken broth. Dice or grate in onion, salt and pepper to taste.

title: shoestring tuna salad
directions: Toss all ingredients (except shoestring potatoes) and allow to marinate.
Immediately before serving, toss in shoestring potatoes, trying not to break them.
Serve very cold.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Slice zucchini and simmer in water until tender.
Drain. Saute onion and green pepper in butter.
Add mushrooms.
In a buttered casserole dish, mix half of zucchini, onion, pepper and mushrooms.
Sprinkle with half of the seasonings, Parmesan cheese and croutons.
Continue with the other half.
Pour spaghetti sauce over casserole and top with Mozzarella cheese.
Bake at 350° until cheese melts and casserole is bubbly.

title: chicken chow mein casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients except noodles.
Place in greased 11 x 7-inch baking dish.
Cover with chow mein noodles.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: christmas cooler
directions: In a bowl, dissolve jello in boiling water; cool.
In blender container, combine jello mixture, frozen limeade concentrate, almond extract and vanilla.
Cover; blend at high speed, adding 1 ice cube at a time, until smooth and frothy.
Transfer to serving bowl.
Gently stir in ginger ale and water.
Garnish with cherries.
Yields 16 (4-ounce) servings.

title: teriyaki pork chops
directions: Marination:
Blend 1/2 cup soy sauce, 1/2 cup brown sugar, juice from pineapple and 1 teaspoon garlic salt.

title: hot chicken casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except chips.
Place in oblong 3-quart casserole or 2 small casseroles (grease dish).
Top with chips.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
Yields 12 servings.

title: frozen lemon pie
directions: Beat egg yolks, salt and sugar in top of double boiler.
Stir in lemon juice and cook over boiling water until mixture coats spoon.
Remove from heat and chill.
Beat egg whites until stiff and fold into cooked mixture, then fold in whipped cream. Sprinkle vanilla wafer crumbs in freezing tray or small pie pan and top with lemon mixture.
Freeze firm.
Double recipe for larger pie.

title: cheeseburger casserole
directions: Put noodles on to cook.
In a large skillet, mix onion, bell pepper and hamburger meat; cook until done.
Pour off excess fat. Add all other ingredients, except cheese and noodles.
Let simmer 10 minutes, then add cheese (save enough to put on top).
Mix with drained noodles and simmer a few more minutes.

title: ugly duckling cake
directions: Combine cake mix fruit cocktail with syrup, 1 cup coconut and eggs in a large mixing bowl.
Blend, then beat at medium speed for 2 minutes.
Pour into greased 9x13 inch pan.
Sprinkle with brown sugar.

title: deviled nuts
directions: Place pecans in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Combine remaining ingredients; pour over pecans, stirring to coat. Spread evenly in pan; bake at 300° for 20 minutes, stirring twice.
Drain on paper towels; cool.
Store nuts in an airtight container.
Yields 4 cups.

title: pecan pie
directions: Add ingredients as listed stirring after each addition.
Do not use mixer.
Pour in pie crust.
Bake at 350° until middle is firm.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Combine milk, soup and pepper; pour over beans in a glass casserole baking dish.
Add 1/2 can of onions.
Mix together. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Garnish with 1/2 can onions.
Bake an additional 5 minutes.

title: date loaf candy
directions: Mix all ingredients together in large kettle.
Stir and bring to a rolling boil for 8 minutes.
Remove from heat; beat until stiff.
Shape mixture into loaf and chill for 24 hours.
Slice to serve.
(I add nuts and vanilla after it is cooked.)

title: sweet and sour cabbage
directions: Cook cabbage in boiling salted water for 7 minutes.
Fry bacon.
Add sugar and flour to bacon fat.
Blend well.
Add water, vinegar and seasonings.
Cook until thickened.
Add onion, diced bacon and cabbage.
Heat through.
Yields 6 servings.

title: red potato salad
directions: In a large pot of salted boiling water, cook potatoes 25 minutes or until just tender. Drain and cool 15 minutes. Cut potatoes in half and place in a large bowl. Stir in 4 tablespoons olive oil and 2 tablespoons vinegar. Add bell pepper, pimento, onion and pickles and toss gently to combine. Whisk together remaining 2 tablespoons olive oil and 1 tablespoon vinegar with sour cream and next 5 ingredients. Season to taste with salt and pepper. Pour dressing over vegetables, tossing gently to coat. Cover tightly and chill 4 hours to blend flavors. Serve at room temperature. Serves 6.

title: sour cream coconut cake
directions: Cook cake mix as directed on box.
Let cool and split into two layers.

title: pineapple 'n ice cream punch
directions: Combine all ingredients except ale.
Beat at low speed with mixer.
Pour mixture into punch bowl.
Add ale just before serving.

title: dill dip
directions: Mix all together and let stand for a few hours.

title: raspberry teas
directions: Cream butter, shortening, sugar and salt until light and fluffy.
Add egg yolk and vanilla; mix well.
Add flour and blend. Divide dough into 2 parts.
Place half in refrigerator and chill for several hours.
Divide other half into 48 pieces.
Roll into balls in palms of hands.
Roll in nuts.
Roll chilled dough 1/8-inch thick on a well floured pastry cloth.
Cut out with 2-inch serrated cookie cutter.
Place on ungreased cookie sheets. Add 1/2 teaspoon jam to center of each flat cookie.
Place balls on jam and press gently.
Make an indentation in center of each ball with a thimble.
Place 1/4 teaspoon jam on center of each ball.
Bake in moderate oven at 350° for about 15 minutes, or until delicately browned (48 cookies).

title: turkey-shrimp oriental
directions: Cut turkey into 1-inch cubes.

Heat oil in large skillet over medium-high heat until hot. Cook turkey in oil until no longer pink. Add pineapple, water chestnuts, mushrooms, shrimp, onions, green pepper and 1/2 cup pineapple juice.
Heat to boiling. Reduce heat and simmer until vegetables are tender-crisp, about 10 minutes.
Stir remaining ingredients into remaining pineapple juice. Stir into turkey mixture.
Heat to boiling, stirring constantly.
Boil and stir until sauce is thickened and clear. Salt and pepper to taste. Serve with rice, if desired.
Yields 6 servings.

title: chinese chicken noodle soup
directions: For stock, combine the chicken, chicken broth, water, onions, garlic, salt and red pepper flakes in Dutch oven.
Bring just to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer gently, 45 minutes.
Drain, reserving broth and chicken separately.
Cook chicken slightly. Remove meat from bones and dice; cover and refrigerate.
Freeze broth for 1 hour or refrigerate overnight; skim fat.
Return broth to Dutch oven and bring to a boil.
Add the chicken, mushrooms, snow peas, carrots, soy sauce, ginger and sesame oil.
Return to a boil.
Add the pasta and green onions.
Cook, stirring with cilantro.
Yield:
10 cups.

title: indian corn pone
directions: Combine ingredients; stir into a thick batter. Grease a heavy skillet. Drop batter in a hot skillet, divided into 4 pones. Brown to golden brown on both sides. Serve hot with butter.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli for 10 minutes in a little salted water, drain well.
Mix all ingredients together, put in buttered casserole. Cover with Ritz cracker crumbs and dot with butter on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves 10.

title: popcorn balls
directions: Measure corn into a large bowl.
Measure marshmallows, syrup, oleo, sugar and water into a saucepan.
Stir constantly over low heat until marshmallows are melted and syrup begins to boil. Remove from heat.
Add vanilla and stir well.
Pour syrup over popcorn, tossing with 2 large spoons to coat well.
Let cool slightly.
Coat hands with oleo and form into balls.
Makes about 14 balls.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Beat eggs.
Stir in the rest of the ingredients.
Mix well. Turn into greased round 1-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes or until a knife comes out clean.

title: spoon bread
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Stir boiling water into cornmeal. Continue stirring until mixture is lukewarm.
Stir in 1 tablespoon butter and egg yolks until blended.
Stir in buttermilk, salt, sugar, baking powder and soda.
Beat egg whites until soft peaks form.
Fold into batter.
Pour into greased casserole.
Bake until knife inserted in center comes out clean, 45 to 50 minutes.
Serve hot with butter or oleo.

title: snowball cake
directions: Rub crust off cake; break into small pieces and set aside. Soften gelatin in cold water.
Add boiling water and sugar; mix well.
Add juices and cool until like jelly.
Whip Dream Whip as directed.
Fold into gelatin mixture.
Oil bottom and sides of round mixing bowl (like crock).
Alternate gelatin and cake.
Begin and end with gelatin mixture.
Refrigerate overnight.
Turn out into cake plate.
Whip the cream and ice cake.
Cover with coconut.

title: barbecue shrimp
directions: Clean shrimp.
Cut bacon into thirds.
Individually wrap shrimp with bacon and put on skewer, leaving enough room between each for heat to cook all sides.
Cook on grill, basting them with the barbecue sauce until bacon is slightly crisp and shrimp are done. Serve as an appetizer with steak dinner.

title: polish easter soup(from poland)
directions: Cook ham, kielbasa, and beef heart until tender.
Add in potatoes and onions.
When the potatoes are tender, add in sliced hard boiled eggs.
Liquify cornstarch and sour cream with a little bit of water and pour into soup, be careful not to let it curdle. Serve with sprinkle of parsley, add salt and pepper to taste.

title: broccoli supreme
directions: Cook broccoli as directed on package.
In small pan, combine cream of mushroom soup and garlic cheese.
Heat until cheese is melted.
Drain water from broccoli.
Combine broccoli, 1/2 cheese mixture and 1/2 can onions in large casserole dish (spray with Pam).
Top with remaining onions and cheese mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes in covered dish.

title: mom's pumpkin pie
directions: Mix in order given and bake in a pastry-lined pie pan in hot oven (450°) for 15 minutes.
Then reduce oven to 350° and continue baking until filling is firm.
Remove from oven and cool before serving.

title: tomato-rice casserole
directions: Fry hamburger and drain.
Slice potatoes.
Take potatoes and "layer" them on a buttered roaster or casserole dish; cover the bottom of the pan with potatoes.
Next, put some of the hamburger on top of the potatoes.
Take some of the diced onion and sprinkle over the hamburger.
Next, take some "uncooked" Minute rice and sprinkle over the onions.
Repeat this process again.
Should have 2 layers of each now.
Pour the tomato soup over all and bake at 350° for 1 hour or so.
If potatoes are done when poked, then remove and enjoy.
Great with lettuce salad and bread.
Very filling.
To insure against any burning, add also 1 to 1 1/2 cans of cold water on top of tomato soup.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: pistachio salad dessert
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Put in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cover with foil and freeze.
Take out of freezer and cut, one piece at a time.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugars.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Then add flour, soda and salt.
Mix well.
Add oats, nuts and coconut. Beat well.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: raisin coconut pie
directions: Put raisins in hot water to cover for 15 minutes.
Combine eggs, sugar, corn syrup, vanilla, well drained raisins and coconut. Mix all ingredients until well blended. Pour into pie shells and dot lightly with margarine.
Bake at
300° for 45 minutes or until lightly browned and firm.
Stick with fork occasionally while baking.

title: the westerner(pound cake)
directions: Have eggs and vanilla at room temperature.
Cream margarine; add powdered sugar.
Beat until fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Sift flour 3 times.
Add gradually to batter.
Add flavorings and mix well.
Bake in 10-inch greased and floured tube pan at 325° for 1 1/2 hours. Cool 4 minutes, then invert pan and cool completely.

title: oatmeal scotchies
directions: Combine flour, soda, salt and cinnamon.
Set aside.
Combine in large bowl butter, sugar, brown sugar and eggs.
Beat until fluffy.
Slowly add dry ingredients.
Then stir in oatmeal and butterscotch morsels.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on ungreased cookie sheet.
Allow space.
Bake for 8 minutes for chewier cookies. Bake 10 minutes for crispier cookies.
Bake at 375°.
Yields 4 dozen cookies.

title: fudge pie
directions: Melt margarine in pan on low heat.
In another bowl, mix sugar, cocoa and flour.
Add sugar mixture to margarine and stir. Add eggs and vanilla and stir well.
Pour into unbaked pie shell and bake 40 minutes at 350°.
Allow to cool before cutting.

title: grandma miller's m&m cookies
directions: Beat together sugars, shortening and eggs.
Add flour, soda, salt and vanilla.
Stir 1 cup of M&M's into batter.
Drop by teaspoon on a greased cookie sheet.
Decorate with the rest of M&M's.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Bake 10 minutes.

title: sweet and sour kielbasa
directions: Cut kielbasa into bite size pieces.
Put into crock-pot.
Mix all other ingredients in a separate bowl. Pour over kielbasa. Cook on high for 2 hours or low for 4 hours.

title: yum yum cake
directions: Heat oven to 350 degrees.
Measure dry ingredients into 8 inch square pan.
Make 3 holes in the dry cake putting oil in one, vinegar in second and oil in the third.
Pour water over mixture and mix by hand.

title: apple-spice oatmeal
directions: Add enough water to apple juice to make 5 cups.
Combine with brown sugar, cinnamon and salt in a large pan.
Bring to a boil over medium-high heat.
Gradually stir in oats.
Cook, stirring occasionally, for 5 minutes.
Reduce heat to simmer; cook, uncovered, stirring occasionally, 30 minutes or until tender and a good consistency.
Serve with a dollop of yogurt and apple, if you wish.
Makes 4 servings.

title: spinach dip
directions: Thaw spinach.
Mix vegetable soup mix with sour cream.
Blend in mayonnaise.
Stir in thawed spinach.
Serve with dark rye bread, squared.

title: alabama biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast and sugar in water, then add other ingredients. Mix and roll out and cut biscuits.
Dip each in melted butter. Place one on top of the other to form top and bottom in greased pan.
Let rise 1 hour.
Bake at 400° until brown.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: *If doubling the recipe, use 1 can cream-style corn and 1 1/2 teaspoons salt.

title: slaw
directions: Mix all together in food processor.
Refrigerate.

title: corn pudding(hot casserole)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Butter a 2-quart casserole.
Slice onion into 1/4-inch slices.
Stir eggs until beaten.
Add rest of ingredients.
Mix until corn is just mixed into batter.
Pour into casserole.
Bake one hour and 10 minutes, or until firm.
Serves 6.

title: fruit kabobs
directions: Cut fruits in large chunks.
Thread on party picks.
Chill and serve.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients in an 8 quart Dutch oven or stockpot; bring to a boil.
Reduce heat to medium and cook, uncovered, 1 hour.
Remove from heat.
Remove chicken from broth; place chicken in a bowl and chill for 15 minutes.
Strain broth through a cheesecloth-lined colander into a bowl; discard solids. Set aside 4 1/2 cups broth.

title: chewy oatmeal scotchies
directions: Sift together flour, cinnamon, soda, salt and nutmeg.
Add shortening, sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Beat until smooth.
Stir in oats and chips. Drop rounded teaspoonfuls of dough onto greased cookie sheet.
Flatten.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 12 to 15 minutes.
Makes about 3 1/2 dozen cookies.

title: corned beef casserole with noodles
directions: Mix all together.
Use buttered crumbs or crushed croutons for topping.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until thickened.

title: turkey meatballs in lemon sauce
directions: In bowl,
combine egg, cereal, Worcestershire sauce and lemon peel.
Add	turkey,
mix
well.
Shape into 8 balls, 1/4 cup mix each.
Brown meatballs in hot oil, drain off fat.
Add broth, cover and simmer 20 minutes.
Transfer to dish, reserving juices in	pan.
In
small bowl, combine sour cream, cornstarch and lemon juice.
Add
to juices in skillet.
Cook and stir 2 minutes after
mixture
is	thickened and bubbly.
Add carrot and onions. Serve sauce over meatballs.
Serves 4.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Blend together ingredients except cheese and chips.
Put into greased 1 1/2 qt. baking dish.
Sprinkle with cheese, then chips over top.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients.
Add the zucchini, nuts and raisins.
Beat together in another bowl the eggs and salad oil. Pour this into the flour mixture and blend well.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes in greased loaf pans.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: hawaiian cake i
directions: Bake yellow cake in 9 x 13-inch pan; cool completely.
Beat together pudding mix, cream cheese and milk.
Spread over cake, then spread the crushed pineapple.
Spread the Cool Whip.
Sprinkle with coconut.
Chill if desired.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: scalloped pineapple
directions: Cream eggs and sugar together, then add melted oleo and stir. Add 1/2 cup milk and pineapple and stir well.
Last, add bread crumbs and mix thoroughly.
Bake in regular size casserole at 350° for 40 to 60 minutes or until a knife blade comes out clean from center.
Can be served hot or cold.

title: meatball cocktails
directions: Combine chili sauce, grape jelly and water in saucepan heat, stirring, until well blended.
Combine remaining other ingredients in a bowl mixing well, shape into 1-inch balls and place in jelly sauce.
Simmer over low heat for 30 minutes or until done.
Serve with toothpicks.

title: mincemeat
directions: Cut meat into 1-inch cubes and place in Dutch oven with just enough water to cover.
Cook and simmer over moderate heat 2 hours.
Remove meat and reserve 1 cup of the liquid.
Force meat and suet through the coarse blade of food chopper.
In a large kettle combine chopped meat and all remaining ingredients except lemon juice, orange juice and brandy.
Stir to blend and bring mixture to boil over moderate heat.
Cover and simmer over moderately low heat 1 1/2 hours.
Add juices and brandy.
Freeze or can in 1-quart containers.
To blend flavors, let stand at least 1 week before using.
Makes about 6 quarts.
Use 1 quart for pies.
Also good for cookies.

title: wilted lettuce
directions: Tear lettuce into pieces.
Bring remaining ingredients to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 2 to 3 minutes.
Pour hot mixture over lettuce in a bowl and toss to coat evenly.

title: old fashion fruitcake
directions: Heat oven to 275°.
Line pan with foil paper and grease it well.
Mix all dry ingredients.
Add oil, eggs, juice and syrup. Mix well.
Add raisins, chopped fruit and nuts.
Spread in pan and bake 2 1/2 to 3 hours or until a knife inserted in the center comes out clean.
If necessary, cover top with foil to prevent burning the last hour.

title: eggplant parmesan
directions: Heat 1/4 cup oil in skillet.
Saute garlic and onion.
Add tomatoes, basil, salt and pepper.
Cook, covered, stirring for 30 minutes.
Make batter with flour, eggs and milk.
Dip eggplant in batter and fry in hot shallow oil until browned on each side.
Add more oil after each frying.
Arrange in layers in casserole; eggplant, sauce and cheese.
Sprinkle each layer with salt and pepper and dot with butter.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: pecan pie 5
directions: Mix ingredients and pour in unbaked pie shells.
Cook 45 minutes at 325°.

title: jello pound cake
directions: Bake at 350°
until golden brown.
Serve with ice cream or peaches.

title: corned beef salad
directions: Dissolve bouillon cubes and lemon jello in 1 cup boiling water.
Let cool.
You can use mixer or blender to blend the dressing and cream cheese with the mixture.
Shred the corned beef and fold it in; add the celery, onion and eggs.
Put in mold or large dish and refrigerate.
Can be made day before.

title: little spice cookies
directions: Sift flour, baking powder, salt, sugar, spices and soda together.
Combine egg, butter and molasses in bowl.
Add flour mixture and blend.
Chill until firm enough to shape.
Shape in small balls about 3/4-inch in diameter.
Roll in sugar.
Bake on greased baking sheet at 375° for 10 minutes.
Makes 5 dozen.

title: sweet potato bread
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients together well. Pour into a buttered pan and bake at 400° for 30 minutes. When done, remove from oven and put several marshmallows on top. Put under broiler for a few seconds; marshmallows will begin to brown lightly. Before baking, you may also add 1 teaspoon lemon juice, if desired. Great holiday dish.

title: salisbury steak
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients together except soup.
Make into patties.
Roll in flour; put in to skillet and brown on both sides.
Place in baking dish.
Dilute soup with 1/2 can water.
Pour over patties.
Bake for 45 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6 people.

title: sour cream tarts(finnish prune tarts)
directions: Mix the dry ingredients together.
Add oleo; mix well. Combine sour cream, eggs and vanilla; add to flour mixture.
Mix until dough is smooth.
Set dough in refrigerator overnight.
Next morning, roll out dough to 1/8-inch thick.
Cut out and fill. Bake at 400° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Boil broccoli.
Boil rice.
Combine all ingredients except shredded Cheddar in baking dish.
Top with shredded Cheddar.
Bake at 350° until cheese bubbles.

title: salmon croquettes
directions: Mix together.
Shape into patties.
Coat with flour and fry.

title: crab dip
directions: Mix ingredients and chill.
Serve with crackers.

title: red snapper with orange sauce
directions: Place fillets in single layer in well-greased pan.
Combine remaining ingredients and pour over fish.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Pour any remaining sauce over fish before serving.

title: easiest pot roast(uses crock-pot)
directions: Wash and if you prefer, peel carrots and potatoes.
Quarter potatoes and carrots and place in bottom of crock-pot in the morning before work.
Place the roast on top of the vegetables. Mix together one envelope of the onion soup mix and 2 cups of warm water.
Pour over the roast.
Cover crock-pot and turn on at 300°. Cook all day and by evening you will have the most tender roast you have ever eaten.
This makes enough to use leftovers for vegetable soup later in the week.

title: buttercream icing
directions: Beat together until light and fluffy.
Spread on cool cake.

title: pulgogi
directions: Cut the beef into thin slices about 3 inches square by 1/8-inch thick.
This can be done at the butcher's shop.
Marinate the beef in remaining ingredients for up to 1 1/2 hours. Traditionally, this meat is broiled at the table on a Korean pulgogi grill over charcoal, gas ring or hot plate.
Otherwise, use a frying pan or oven-broiler.
Pork or chicken may also be cooked this way.

title: syd's vegetarian (low gas) bean chili
directions: Pour beans into boiling water and boil for 3 minutes.
Then soak for 2 hours in the same water.
Drain and rinse beans.
(This process allows the sugars that cause gas to leach out through the softened shell.)

title: swedish pepakaker cookies
directions: Cream margarine, sugar, egg and Karo.
Add dry ingredients and mix.
Put in refrigerator overnight or 5 to 6 hours.

title: apple betty
directions: Mound apples on buttered 9-inch pie plate.
Sprinkle with orange juice. Combine other dry ingredients (sugar, flour, spice and salt). Cut in butter until crumb mixture. Cover apples. Bake at 375° for 40 minutes.

title: panama cheese things
directions: Mix. Roll dough out like cookie dough. Make into rounds about 1 1/2-inches across. Top with slices of hot Polish sausage. Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.

title: peanutty brownies
directions: Cream peanut butter, butter, brown sugar and vanilla.
Beat in eggs.
Combine dry ingredients.
Add to creamed mixture.
Stir in baking chips and peanuts.
Bake in greased 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: gloria's meat loaf
directions: Mix and bake at 375°.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: blackberry pie
directions: Mix blackberries, sugar and flour.
Pour ingredients into deep dish pie shell. Cover with top crust.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes until crust is brown.
Delicious served warm with vanilla ice cream.

title: three bean salad
directions: Drain beans and put into a large bowl.
Add onion, pepper and pimiento.
Dissolve sugar in vinegar.
Add with salt, pepper and oil.
Stir to blend.
Marinate overnight.

title: broccoli corn casserole
directions: Cook broccoli.
Combine broccoli, corn, 1 cup stuffing mix, soup, egg, butter and onion.
Mix well.
Spoon mixture into greased casserole.
Sprinkle top with cheese and 1/4 cup stuffing mix.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: white grape juice spritzer
directions: In large non-metal pitcher or punch bowl, combine grape juice and club soda.
Garnish with lemon and lime slices.
Serve immediately.
Serves 24.

title: "oh so good" chocolate layered pie
directions: Prepare the pudding as directed, minus 1/2 cup milk.
Spread over cream cheese layer.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: strawberry punch
directions: Mix and add enough water to make 1 gallon.

title: chicken breasts and rice
directions: Arrange chicken breasts (I use the skinned and deboned) in covered baking dish; add 1/3 cup water.
Cover and bake slowly until tender; add rice, soup and 1/2 can of water.
Cook 15 to 20 minutes or until rice is soft.

title: betty's macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni for 10 minutes.
Drain and reserve juices from fruit.
Take juice from fruit and add flour, eggs and sugar.
Add cold macaroni and refrigerate overnight.

title: baked chuck roast
directions: Place roast in baking dish (unseasoned).
Sprinkle with onion soup mix.
Pour in Coca-Cola.
Cover and seal tightly with aluminum foil.
Bake until tender, at 300° for 3 1/2 hours.

title: meatballs
directions: Mix together ground beef, venison or mixture of two, eggs, onion soup mix and bread crumbs; make into balls and put in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bring to boil cranberry sauce, chili sauce, water an brown sugar.
Bring to boil; pour over meatballs.
Cover with foil and bake 2 hours at 350°.
Last 1/2 hour uncover.

title: louise little's kentucky nut cake
directions: Mix sugar, oil, egg yolks, hot water and pineapple thoroughly. Sift together dry ingredients and add to sugar mixture.
Fold in egg whites, well beaten.
Fold in nuts.
Pour into tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/4 hours.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Slice onion thin, chop garlic very fine.
Cook in olive oil until clear and very slowly add green pepper.
Cook a few minutes, cut thawed spinach in pieces.
Chop salami or pepperoni and add to onion mixture.
Add basil, 2 shakes nutmeg and spinach.
Put into casserole.
Pour eggs, milk and cheese over spinach mixture. Cover and cook until eggs are set at 350° for 1 hour.

title: apricot pie
directions: Combine milk, lemon juice, apricots and 3 to 4 tablespoons whipped cream.
Line 9-inch pan with wafers.
Add apricot filling. Top with remaining whipped cream.
Chill.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Combine all together, then put out into 3 loaves.
Bake 1 hour or more at 350°.

title: crab soup
directions: Stir soups together.
Add milk.
Heat slowly, stirring until smooth.
Add chicken broth.
Add crab.
Before serving, add wine or sherry and cream.

title: basic french dressing
directions: Place all ingredients in jar.
Cover and shake vigorously until sugar and salt are dissolved.
Makes 1 cup.

title: cranberry relish
directions: Dissolve the sugar and jello in the boiling water.
Set aside to cool.
Grind together in food processor the apples with peels and oranges with peels along with the raw cranberries.
Combine the fruit with the cooled jello mixture and add the nuts. Refrigerate.

title: mexican casserole
directions: In a casserole dish -9 x 13- layer Fritos onion and cheese. Heat chili, Pour over Fritos mixture in dish.
Top with more cheese. Bake in 375 oven for 20 minutes or till cheese is melted. Serves 6 to 8 people.
Serve with green salad.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Partially thaw hash browns. Mix all ingredients together. Put in a large bowl so it is easy to mix. Spread
in lightly greased 9 x 13 inch pan. Top with crushed
potato chips or saltine crackers or corn flakes.
Bake
350° for 1 1/4 to 1 1/2 hours, uncovered.
tags: cream of celery soup or cream of chicken

title: potato bake
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients and put in a 9 x 13-inch greased baking dish.
Top with melted margarine and crushed cornflakes.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves 8 to 12.

title: pumpkin custard cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 9 x 13-inch pan.
In large bowl combine dry cake mix, water and 3 eggs.
Blend as directed.
Pour into can.
In small bowl beat pumpkin and 2 eggs. Use spoon and pour evenly over batter.
Pour boiling water over all.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes until toothpick comes out clean.

title: chicken and peppers skillet
directions: Cut each chicken breasts in half.
Remove skin and bones. Slice in 1/8-inch thick slices.
Mix chicken, soy sauce, garlic powder, cornstarch and sugar substitute; set aside.
Cut green peppers into 1/4-inch wide strips; thinly slice mushrooms.
Over medium heat in 2 tablespoons margarine, cook green peppers and mushrooms, stirring frequently until tender-crisp.
Remove vegetables to bowl.
Over high heat in 2 tablespoons margarine, cook chicken mixture, stirring quickly until chicken is tender, about 5 minutes.
Return vegetables to skillet.
Add water; heat to boiling, stirring to loosen brown bits from bottom of skillet. Serves 4.

title: chinese fried rice
directions: Beat eggs. Heat wok

for 1 minute on high; add 1 teaspoon oil, then eggs. Scramble until cooked through; transfer to plate. Wipe wok clean. Return to high heat. Add 1 tablespoon oil, carrots, broccoli and dash of salt. Stir 2 minutes. Add zucchini and garlic. Stir-fry 2 minutes. Add peas, scallions and water chestnuts. Stir-fry 2 minutes. Reduce heat to medium. Add rice and stir to mix thoroughly with vegetables. Stir in scrambled egg. Sprinkle in soy sauce.

title: taco casserole
directions: Layer Doritos in bottom
of pan; add all other ingredients as listed.
Bake at 350°, uncovered, for 15 to 20 minutes or until cheese melts.
Then cook, covered, about 10 minutes.

title: cream cheese cookies
directions: You also need cookie cutters.

title: pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Bring butter or margarine and eggs to room temperature.
Grease and flour a 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan. Stir together flour, baking powder, salt and nutmeg.
In a large mixer bowl, beat the butter or margarine on medium speed of electric mixer about 30 seconds.
Gradually add sugar, beating 6 minutes or until fluffy.
Add vanilla.
Add the eggs, one at a time, beating 1 minute after each; scrape bowl frequently. Gradually add dry ingredients to egg mixture, beating on low speed just until thoroughly combined.
Turn batter into pan.
Bake in a 325° oven for 55 to 65 minutes or until done.
Cool 15 minutes on a wire rack.
Remove from pan.
Cool.
Makes 12 servings.

title: apple pie
directions: Prepare pastry for 2 (9-inch) pies; fill bottom shell with sliced apples.
Combine remaining ingredients and pour over apples.
Cover with top crust and bake at 350° for 45 minutes until crust is browned and apples tender.

title: pink cloud
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill at least 4 hours.

title: mexicali burgers and rice
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Pour into a 1 1/2-quart shallow casserole dish.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes, or until rice is done.
Makes 6 servings.

title: balkan hen
directions: Marinate hen several hours, or overnight, in the yogurt which has the lemon juice and spices mixed in it.
Bake hen until done, brushing with marinade periodically.
Makes 2 servings.

title: barbecue burgers
directions: Mix all ingredients and brown.
Use favorite barbecue sauce and simmer for 1 hour.

title: cold fudge
directions: Mix together with hands.
Put in buttered oblong pan.
Put in refrigerator until firm.

title: pecan pie
directions: Stir together first five ingredients until well blended. Place pecans in bottom of unbaked pie crust and pour the mixed ingredients over pecans.
Bake in 350° oven about 50 minutes.

title: raw apple cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Grease 13 x 9-inch baking pan. In small bowl, combine flour, cinnamon, baking soda and cloves. Pare, core and chop 2 apples.

title: german potato pancakes
directions: Combine potatoes and onion; let stand for 10 minutes.
Scoop off as much of the liquid as possible that has gathered on top. Add egg, salt, flour, milk and baking powder.
Mix well.
Drop in hot shortening by large tablespoonfuls.
Brown on both sides. Drain on paper towel; place in warm oven until all are baked.

title: corn fritters
directions: Note:
If desired, you may sprinkle with confectioners sugar while warm.

title: cornbread muffins
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Bake in greased muffin pan at 425° until brown.

title: quick rolls
directions: Mix in order given.
Make out rolls.
Let rise 1 1/2 hours. Bake in hot oven until golden brown.

title: green tomato pickles
directions: Put tomatoes before sliced in lime and water mixture and soak for 24 hours, stirring occasionally. Take out of lime and wash thoroughly in 3 or 4 waters. Soak in cold water for 3 hours. Then heat 3 quarts of vinegar, sugar, cloves, ginger, celery seed, cinnamon and pickling spice and pour over tomatoes after draining tomatoes well. Let stand overnight. Let all come to a boil. Cook slowly 1 hour. Can.

title: milky way cake
directions: Make sour milk: 1 cup milk, 1 tbsp vinegar, 1/2 tsp baking soda, 2 tsp vanilla.

title: far east eggplant
directions: Cook all ingredients, except cheese and bacon in skillet until tender.
Top with cheese and bacon.
Brown under broiler.
Makes 4 servings.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Put bread in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Then add cheese. Cook and
drain
meat.
Beat
eggs
with
cup milk and mustard. Pour
over
bread.
Refrigerate
overnight.
Dilute soup with additional
1/2 cup milk.
Pour over other ingredients.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours or until cheese has melted and bubbly.
Great recipe to do with company.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Mix water with Jell-O.
Add cranberry sauce until sugar dissolves, then add rest of ingredients.

title: cheese wafers
directions: Mix cheese and margarine until smooth.
Add flour, salt and pepper to taste.
Add Rice Krispies.
Mix together; roll in small balls.
Place on cookie sheet.
Press slightly.
Bake at 275° until brown around edges.

title: candied sweet potatoes
directions: Bake sweet potatoes until done.
Mix sugar, flour and salt together.
Pour over potatoes that have been cut and placed in pan.
Sprinkle water over sugar and flour mixture until it is covered.
Sprinkle nutmeg, then cover with sliced butter.
Put lemon or orange around potatoes.
Bake in moderate oven until syrup is thick enough.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Mix together butter, flour and milk.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix together.
Pour into large casserole and refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: quick nut panocha
directions: Melt butter. Add sugar.
Cook over low heat 2 minutes, stirring constantly. Add milk and continue cooking and stirring until mixture boils.
Remove from heat. Cool.
Gradually add powdered sugar until mixture is of fudge consistency. Add nuts. Spread in buttered 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan. Chill.

title: potato casserole
directions: Wash and peel potatoes; cut up in small blocks.
Put potatoes in a casserole dish (2-quart size).
Pour 1 can of cream of mushroom soup over potatoes.
Add salt and pepper.
Put lid on. Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: eggplant lasagna(serves 12 to 18)
directions: Saute eggplant, onion and garlic in oil.
When vegetables lose their color, add the rest of the sauce ingredients.
Cover and simmer for 1 hour.

title: low-fat pork chops and potato casserole
directions: Peel and slice potatoes thinly.
Put in baking dish.
Put water, flour and butter in saucepan and boil for 1 minute or until thick, stirring constantly.
Pour over potatoes.
Brown pork chops in frying pan with a little Pam.
Place on potatoes.
Cover with foil and bake 1 hour, then uncover for 10 minutes.

title: easy cheesy lemon bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease bottom only, 13 x 9-inch pan. Combine cake mix, butter and 1 egg.
Stir until moist.
Pat into pan.
Blend frosting mix into cheese.
Save 1/2.

title: creamy broccoli bake
directions: Cook broccoli until tender by bringing to boil in salted water.
Place cooked broccoli in ungreased dish.
Heat oven to 400°.
Beat soup and milk until smooth.
Pour over broccoli. Sprinkle with cheese.
Mix Bisquick and margarine until crumbly. Sprinkle over cheese.
Bake until crumbs are light brown, about 20 minutes.

title: grandma's sweet dill pickles
directions: Drain pickles, saving liquid. Bring 2 cups pickle juice to a boil with cinnamon and allspice. Let cool. Pour over pickles in jar. Cover loosely and allow to set for 4 days. Shake jar occasionally to mix. Pour off liquid and dry out inside of jar (do not wash). Dry off each pickle with paper towels. Slice into 1/4-inch slices. Layer in jar with sugar, alternating pickles and sugar. Cover loosely and allow to sit for 2 days to let sugar melt.

title: chicken rice casserole
directions: Sprinkle chicken pieces with salt, pepper and paprika.
Heat oil in skillet and brown chicken pieces. Set aside.

Rehydrate onion flakes in water for 10 minutes. Add to oil in skillet and saute for 5 minutes. Stir in soup, 1 3/4 cups water and 1/4 teaspoon salt. Bring to boiling, stirring to loosen browned particles in skillet.
Heat oven to 350°.
Pour rice into large baking dish. Stir in seasoning mixture from skillet. Arrange chicken pieces on rice. Cover and bake for 2 hours.

title: freda's 1000 island dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Store in refrigerator.
For thinner dressing, add 1 teaspoon of relish juice.

title: hidden valley ranch cheese puffs
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients.
Spread mixture on bread slices. Broil until puffed and golden (about 3 to 4 minutes).
Great served with salad or soup.

title: taco soup
directions: Brown beef and onion, then drain.
Pour corn, means, water, tomatoes, dressing mix, and taco mix into large cooker with beef and onion.
Cook on medium heat for 1 to 2 hours, until beans are tender.
May serve with Fritos or tortilla chips, shredded cheese, or sour cream.

title: pankuchen
directions: Mix ingredients thoroughly.
Pour like pancake batter onto hot griddle.
Makes 2 to 3 pankuchen.
Serve warm with cranberry sauce or applesauce with cinnamon.
Works best if recipe is not doubled.

title: microwave bread pudding
directions: Combine
milk
and
butter
in a 1 quart glass measure. Microwave
on
Medium for 4 1/2 to 5 1/2 minutes until milk is scalded.
Quickly stir in eggs, sugar and vanilla.
Meanwhile, arrange
bread
cubes
in
a
quart ring mold or Bundt pan. Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Pour milk and egg mixture over bread. Cook,
covered,
with
plastic
wrap
at
Medium
for 16 to 18 minutes or until pudding is set.
Serve warm or chilled.

title: green tomato relish
directions: Put tomatoes, pepper and onions through food chopper.
Mix flour, sugar, salt, vinegar, celery seed, turmeric and mustard. Blend well.
Add to tomato mixture and bring to boil.
Simmer 10 minutes and pour into jars and seal.

title: pear raspberry jam
directions: Mix all ingredients together except pectin.
Chop or mash fruit to get 4 cups puree.
Bring to rolling boil.
Add pectin and boil hard for 1 minute more.
Skim foam.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients.
Pour into a lightly greased baking dish (13 x 9 x 2-inch).
Sprinkle cracker crumbs evenly over top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until bubbly.

title: easy backyard barbecue chicken
directions: You will need a gas grill for easy cooking.
Check temperature of gas grill.
Keep at 300° during cooking or medium-low on your dial.
Brush racks with oil to keep from sticking.

Place chicken on grill. Baste every 5 minutes or so with a mixture of vinegar, salt and pepper. Sprinkle paprika on one side. Baste often with vinegar or you can spray or sprinkle the vinegar, turning the chicken often.
Chicken will be done in 45 minutes. Tastes just like the kind you can buy at roadside stands.

title: broccoli chicken casserole
directions: Poach chicken breast in wine (about 4 minutes until chicken is white).
In a baking dish, place layer of all the broccoli and arrange chicken over broccoli.
Mix soup with mayo.
Pour over broccoli and chicken.
Sprinkle with grated cheese and buttered bread crumbs (optional).
Bake in 350° oven for 35 minutes (approximately).

title: spanish chicken
directions: Boil hen until done; pull from bone.
Cut in bite size pieces. Fry onions, pepper and garlic in small amount of fat; do not brown.
Make a sauce of soup, tomato paste and stock.
Add onion mixture and chicken.
Cook noodles in boiling water until done; drain.
Just before serving, add to chicken mixture with 1/2 of peas.
Sprinkle remaining peas on top.

title: oatmeal candy
directions: Combine the first 4 ingredients; boil for 4 minutes.
Add peanut butter, Quaker oats and vanilla flavoring; mix well.
Spoon out onto foil.
Let cool.

title: 7-layer cookies
directions: Melt margarine in square cake pan. Sprinkle graham cracker crumbs over margarine and add in layers the coconut, chocolate bits, peanut butter bits and nuts. Finally, spread sweetened condensed milk over top and bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Cool and cut into squares.

title: caramel oatmeal chewies
directions: Heat oven to 350° and grease 9 x 13-inch pan.
Combine oatmeal, flour, sugar, soda and salt.
Add margarine until well blended.
Reserve one cup; press remaining onto bottom of pan. Bake for 10 minutes; cool for 10 minutes.
Sprinkle with nuts and chocolate chips.
Mix caramel topping with 1/4 cup flour until smooth.
Drizzle over nuts and chocolate chips to within 1/4 inch of pan edges.
Sprinkle with the reserved oat mixture.
Bake an additional 18 to 22 minutes.
Cool; chill to set and cut into bars.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix well.
Mold into ball and roll in additional chopped pecans; chill.
(May be frozen.)

title: harried housewife delight
directions: Sprinkle spices on both sides of meat.
Put meat in a covered container and place in refrigerator overnight.
Only good when cooked over charcoal grill by male!!

title: holiday brew
directions: Combine all ingredients in a pan on stove.
Bring just to a boil.
Remove from heat and discard cinnamon stick.
Serve hot.

title: apple crisp
directions: Place sliced apples in a greased 8 inch square pan. Blend remaining ingredients until crumbly. Spread over apples. Bake at 375° (350° for glass pan) for 30 to 35 minutes. Serve warm or room temperature. Top with vanilla ice cream or cool whip, if desired.

title: chinese chicken wings
directions: Mix ingredients.
Coat chicken.
Bake at 350° on foiled cookie sheet.
Turn every 15 minutes and baste with mixture.
Bake 1 hour.

title: the best pineapple pie
directions: Beat all together until smooth.
Bake in 2 unbaked pie shells at 350° for 45 minutes or until done.

title: peach cake
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Cool and ice.

title: *finikia 2(date filled pastries)
directions: Cream the butter and sugar well. Add egg, oil, orange juice, brandy, baking powder, soda and flour.
Mix thoroughly.
Adjust flour for soft dough. Wrap each date with 1/4-inch blanket of dough. Will be oval shaped.
Bake for 45 minutes at 375°.

title: chocolate pie
directions: In a boiler, combine sugar, flour and cocoa.
Add 3 egg yolks and mix well by hand.
Slowly add milk. Cook on medium heat until thickened. Remove from heat.
Add 1 teaspoon vanilla and 1 tablespoon oleo. Beat well with electric mixer.
Pour into baked pie shell. Top with meringue if desired.

title: potato soup
directions: In large kettle, cook diced potatoes, carrots and celery until tender (about 20 minutes).
Drain and reserve liquid.

title: vegetable cheese soup
directions: Combine all vegetables in 4 quart water.
Cook until tender; add chicken bouillon cubes, margarine, Cheez Whiz, black pepper and garlic salt.
Thicken with flour and 1 cup water.
Makes 1 gallon.

title: marinara spaghetti
directions: Remove casings from sausages and crumble or chop meat.
Finely chop Prosciutto or ham.
In a wide frying pan over medium-low heat, melt 2 tablespoons of the butter.
Add sausage and Prosciutto to pan and cook, stirring, for about 10 minutes or until sausage is lightly browned.

title: omelet in a mug
directions: In a microwave-safe mug coated with nonstick cooking spray, combine all ingredients. Microwave, uncovered, on High for 1 minute; stir. Cook 1 to 1 1/2 minutes longer or until eggs are completely set. Yields 1 serving.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Scald milk and add to other ingredients.
Mix well.
Pour into 2 unbaked pie shells.
Bake in hot oven for 15 minutes, then 40 minutes in a slow oven.
(Hot oven, 400° to 450°, slow oven, 300° to 325°.)

title: reunion dip for fruit
directions: Mix half jar fudge with cream cheese.
Shape into mound.
Pour remaining caramel over top.
Wonderful with apples.

title: lemon lime punch
directions: Mix the first four ingredients together until sugar is fully dissolved.
When ready to serve, add sherbet, then pour ginger ale over top.
This will make one large punch bowl.

title: enchiladas
directions: In a skillet, warm corn tortillas.
Remove from skillet.
Fill with chili, cheese and onion.
Roll up and pin together with a toothpick.
Place on cookie sheet.
Top with chili and cheese. Bake at 350° until cheese is melted.

title: pickled mirlitons
directions: Peel and remove seed from mirlitons.
Cut into bite size pieces. Chop bell peppers and onions. Dissolve salt in enough water to cover vegetables.
Pour water over vegetables and top with ice. Refrigerate 3 hours or overnight.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix together eggs, sugar and oil.
Beat well, then add flour, salt, soda, cinnamon, apples and nuts.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.
While cake is cooling, mix together brown sugar, sugar, 6 tablespoons flour, water and oleo.
Bring mixture to a boil and pour over cooled cake.

title: maple pecan muffins
directions: Mix flour, sugar, baking powder and salt. Beat egg and stir together the syrup, milk, baking soda, melted butter and vanilla. Add to flour mixture. Stir until moistened. Stir in pecans. Fill greased muffin pans 2/3 full. Mix cinnamon and sugar together and sprinkle over muffins. Bake at 400° for 15-20 minutes.

title: brunch muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease or paper line 2 1/2-inch muffin cups. In medium bowl, combine egg, milk and oil.
Stir in cereal and let stand for 10 minutes.
In large bowl combine flour, sugar, baking powder, salt and cinnamon.
Add cereal mixture all at once to dry ingredients, stirring just until moistened.
Fill muffin cup 2/3 full.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes.
Remove from pan.
Mix 1 tablespoon sugar and 1/8 teaspoon cinnamon.
Brush top of warm muffins with butter and sprinkle with cinnamon-sugar mixture.

title: honey bran muffins
directions: Can add 1 teaspoon vanilla, apple pieces or raisins (optional).

title: pecan pie
directions: Combine sugar, syrup and butter in a 2-quart saucepan.
Bring to a boil on high, stirring constantly until butter is melted. Remove from heat.
Gradually add hot syrup to beaten eggs, stirring constantly.
Add pecans and cool to lukewarm.
Add vanilla.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake in 350° oven for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Wash and cut broccoli into bite-size pieces.
Combine broccoli, onion and bacon.
Thin mayo with vinegar until salad dressing consistency.
Add sugar.
Pour mayo mixture over broccoli mixture.
Toss to mix.
Refrigerate a few hours or overnight.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Put onion and rice in casserole dish.
Pour chicken and celery soup and enough water to mix rice; place chicken on top.
Cover and bake 1 hour at 300°.

title: greg's garlic bread
directions: Slice bread into 1 to 1 1/2-inch slices. Brush bread with a thin layer of olive oil. Sprinkle with garlic powder, parsley and about 1/2 teaspoon cheese.
Place slices on baking sheet and put under broiler until lightly browned.

title: southern pecan pie
directions: Mix eggs, syrup, butter, sugar and salt.
Add nuts and stir. Pour into prepared pie shell and bake in a preheated 450° oven for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° and bake for 30 minutes.

title: wassail(hot)
directions: Put spices in top of 30 cup percolator, normal perk cycle. Can also put spices in cheesecloth and boil.

title: barbecue
directions: Brown ground beef in skillet.
Drain beef in colander to remove all grease.
Place beef back in skillet with onion, celery, ketchup and oregano.
Mix well.
Add salt to taste.
Simmer about 30 minutes or until flavors blend.
(You may need to add a little more ketchup if too dry.)
Stir often to keep from scorching.

title: cream cheese cookies
directions: Combine margarine, cream cheese, sugar, egg yolks and vanilla. Beat until light and fluffy.
Then add flour.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Press center of each with thumb to flatten.
Bake at 325° for 25 minutes.
Makes 72 cookies.

title: bean casserole
directions: Brown hamburger, bacon, onion and sausage. Drain off fat. Mix ketchup, brown sugar, mustard and vinegar. Add remaining ingredients. Mix all ingredients together and put in large casserole dish. Bake 30 minutes at 350°. Add grated Mozzarella cheese and bake another 5 to 10 minutes, until cheese is melted. Do ahead 1 to 2 days if you like.

title: pineapple berry relish
directions: Mix ingredients in a bowl and chill.
Makes about 6 1/2 cups.

title: texas sheet cake
directions: Combine first three ingredients in a saucepan and bring to a boil.
Cook until thick. Set aside.
In large bowl, mix flour, sugar, salt, and soda.
Beat together eggs and sour cream and add to cocoa mixture.
Mix dry and wet ingredients together.
Grease and flour cookie sheet.
Bake at 325° for 20 - 22 minutes. Frost.

title: sweet potato balls
directions: Cook sweet potatoes with margarine and sugar until done. Mash up, let cool.

title: pizza burgers
directions: Brown hamburger, salt and onion.
Drain.
Add tomato soup, water, garlic salt and oregano and simmer 15 minutes.
Place hamburger buns, cut side up, on cookie sheet.
Spoon hamburger mixture on each bun and top with shredded cheese.
Bake at 300° until cheese is melted.

title: crunchy walnut brittle
directions: Place walnuts in a 9-inch glass pie plate, and microwave on High for 5 minutes, stirring half way through, until toasted.
Set aside.
In a 2 quart glass measuring bowl, combine sugar, corn syrup, water, butter and salt.
Microwave on High for 5 to 6 minutes, stirring well at least twice until sugar dissolves.
Then microwave on High for 4 1/2 to 9 minutes, stirring every 2 minutes, until mixture reaches 300 degrees (on candy thermometer).
Stir in baking soda; add toasted walnuts.
Pour into greased 15X10 inch jelly roll pan and spread thin.
Let stand until cooled.
Break into pieces.
Makes 1 1/2 pounds.

title: corn chowder
directions: Cut bacon up and fry in skillet.
Add onion, chopped.
Then add corn, pepper, celery (chopped) and cover with water.
Let stew for 30 minutes or until water is gone.
Add milk and if you are going to use noodles add at this time.
Cook until noodles are done. Then mix flour with a little cold milk and add.
Cook until thick, then add butter, salt and pepper.
Eat like soup with crackers.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve Jello and sugar in water.
Add cranberries, crushed pineapple and pecans.
Refrigerate until solid.

title: ground beef tamale pie
directions: In skillet, brown ground beef with onions.
Stir in soup mix, water, corn, olives and chili powder until well blended.
Heat through.
Place in 1-quart dish.
Top with cheese.
Spread muffin cubes over cheese.
Bake at 350° for 5 to 10 minutes.

title: apple bread
directions: Cream sugar, shortening, eggs, flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt.
Mix all together.
Add nuts, cinnamon, apples and vanilla.
Pour into greased bread loaf pans.
Mix 1/2 teaspoon cinnamon and 1/2 teaspoon sugar to sprinkle on top of loaves. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: german apple bars
directions: Mix eggs and oil and heat over low heat until foamy.
Add dry ingredients to warm mixture.
Add vanilla.
Mix well.
Add nuts and apples, stir.
Pour into greased jelly roll pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.
When cool, drizzle powdered sugar icing over top (1 cup powdered sugar, 2 Tbsp. milk).
Freezes well.

title: pistachio dessert
directions: Drain pineapple and mix all ingredients in bowl.
Refrigerate for 1 hour.
May garnish with maraschino cherries or fruit.

title: white fruit cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Stir in flavorings.
Coat nuts
and
fruit	in the 2 cups of flour. Add to batter and	mix
well.
Bake
at
350° for 1 1/4 hours. This cake is much
better
if
wrapped
and frozen for a while before serving.

title: pesto catfish
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Rinse fillets and pat dry. Combine all dry ingredients. Coat fillets evenly and shake off excess coating. Heat 1 tablespoon each of butter and oil over medium-high heat in large skillet until butter foams, but doesn't burn. Cook 2 fillets, rounded side down, for 2 minutes. Turn fillets and cook 2 minutes. Transfer to a baking sheet, rounded side up. Wipe skillet; add remaining butter and oil. Repeat cooking process with remaining fillets. Spread fillets with pesto. Bake for 6 to 7 minutes or until fish flakes easily when tested with a fork. Makes 4 servings.

title: broccoli cheese casserole
directions: Mix eggs, rice, margarine, onions, milk and cheese.
Fold in broccoli.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: caramel corn
directions: Mix all ingredients except soda and boil 4 minutes.
Remove from stove and stir in soda.
Stir and quickly pour over 6 quarts of popped corn.
Mix well and pour out on cookie sheet.
Put in preheated 250° oven and cook 1 hour.
Stir 3 or 4 times while baking.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix pudding and milk until thick.
Fold in sour cream and half of Cool Whip.
Layer with vanilla wafers and bananas.
Top with remaining Cool Whip.
(Best if let set for 12 to 24 hours.)

title: hot spiced tea
directions: Mix all ingredients; store in airtight container. Mix 3 to 4 teaspoons mixture to cup of hot water (depends on size of cup).

title: spaghetti pizza
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Combine butter and Parmesan in the bottom of 9 x 13-inch ovenproof dish. Toss spaghetti into mixture. Combine the cheese. Put 1/2 of the cheese mixture on top of the spaghetti. Place pepperoni in a single layer on cheese. Spread spaghetti sauce on pepperoni. Top with remaining cheese mixture Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until cheese is melted.

title: frozen fruit salad(good hot weather salad, popular with children.)
directions: Dissolve gelatin and salt in boiling water.
Drain pineapple, saving syrup and adding water to make 1/2 cup.
Stir into gelatin with lemon juice. Blend in mayonnaise.
Chill until very thick. Fold fruits, nuts and whipped topping into gelatin.
Pour into a 9 x 5 x 3-inch foil lined loaf pan. Freeze until firm, at least 3 or 4 hours.
To serve, cut into 8 slices.
Keeps well if tightly covered.

title: pecan pie
directions: Turn on oven and set at 375°.
Have pastry crust ready.
Mix sugar, flour and salt in a 1 1/2-quart bowl.
Stir in corn syrup. Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Mix in remaining ingredients.
Pour into crust.
Bake 50 minutes or until firm.
Cool before serving.

title: sausage and potato stuffing(for turkey)
directions: Crumble toasted bread between fingers.
Saute sausage and set aside.
Saute onions and celery in the sausage fat.
In a large bowl, combine bread, mashed potatoes, sausage, onions and celery and slightly beaten eggs.
Add poultry seasoning and salt to taste.
Mix well; stuff turkey.
Stuffing will expand slightly while turkey is roasting.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Mix together and put in large casserole dish.
Sprinkle with croutons, enough to cover mixture.
Top with grated cheese.
Bake for 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.
Let set for 15 minutes before serving.

title: beef jerky - for those who don't have smokers
directions: Marinate meat for at least 3 hours in deep container.
Turn every hour or so and push meat down into sauce.
Remove rack from oven and place over sink.
Put a toothpick through the ends of the meat and hang between the bars of the oven rack.
Line the bottom of the oven with aluminum foil.
Place rack in oven and bake at 150° for 4 to 6 hours.
Turn off oven and allow to hang there overnight.

title: fish cakes
directions: Mix tuna fine.
Add potatoes, spices and egg.
Mix well.
Add bread crumbs and wheat germ.
Mix again.
Then make fish cake and coat them with bread crumbs.
Fry cakes in a little oil.
Drain on paper towels.
Serve them with your favorite toppings.

title: leftover turkey pot pie
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Mix mayonnaise, flour, bouillon and pepper in saucepan; gradually add milk.
Cook over medium heat until thickened.
Add turkey and veggies; cook 5 minutes.
Spoon mixture into 8-inch square baking dish.

title: pie crust
directions: Mix the oil, milk and salt.
Add the flour.
This mixes together very easily.
Divide in half and roll out between two pieces of waxed paper.
This makes 2 crusts.

title: mom's potato pancakes
directions: Grate potatoes into bowl.
Drain off excess water from mixture. Grate onion into mixture.
Add eggs, flour and salt and pepper to taste.
(Mixture should be consistency of sour cream.)
Drop with tablespoon into hot frying pan with oil.
Fry until golden brown.

title: risotto - buon appetito!(italian)
directions: In a medium-large size pot, saute onion and 2 ounces olive oil until onion is soft and translucent.
Add 1 cup of Arborio rice and cook over medium heat for 1/2 minute, stirring gently.
Add 1 cup broth, stirring constantly.
Continue to add broth as rice absorbs liquid.
Stir constantly to avoid rice sticking to bottom of pan. After adding 3 or so cups broth, add scallops, peas and mushrooms. Add saffron and herbs.
Continue to add broth until rice is a sticky, soft consistency.
When rice is completely cooked and all broth has been added, squeeze fresh lemon juice and add fresh black pepper to taste.
Serve with diced tomatoes on top.
Fresh yellow corn is a wonderful vegetable to serve with Risotto.
Serves 2 to 3.

title: holly's granny- bob ranch potatoes
directions: Boil potatoes until almost tender.
Mix milk, ranch dressing, and 1 c. cheese.
Pour over potatoes, and top with bacon and remaining cheese.
Bake at 350 degrees for 25 to 30 minutes- until tender.

title: punch
directions: Mix together and chill.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Add sugar gradually to shortening; beat until creamy.
Add egg, peanut butter, salt and soda.
Add flour and vanilla.
Roll dough in small balls, place on greased cookie sheet and press flat with a fork.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.

title: pistachio ice cream cake
directions: Melt margarine; mix with crackers and press into bottom of a 13 x 9 x 2-inch casserole dish.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 350°. Cool and then mix ice cream, pudding mix and milk.
Spread over crust.
Cover with Cool Whip.
Cover and freeze for 1 hour.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix drained pineapple and fruit cocktail.
Combine pudding mix and Cool Whip; add to fruit mixture.
Place nuts and cherries on top.

title: aggression cookies
directions: Put all this in a huge bowl and mash, knead, squeeze (the more the better), then form into walnut-size balls on ungreased cookie sheet.
Butter bottom of a small glass; dip it in granulated sugar and mash the balls flat.
Keep doing it (you need only butter the glass bottom once or twice, but re-dip it in sugar for each ball). Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes or until brown.
Makes 15 dozen.

title: upside-down german chocolate cake
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients and set aside.
On bottom of pan, spread nuts and coconut.
Bake cake mix by following directions. Pour over bottom layer; put cream cheese mixture on top of batter.

title: mountain dew cake
directions: Grease (solid shortening) and flour a Bundt cake pan.
Put pecan chips in bottom of pan.
Preheat oven to 325°.
Mix ingredients together.
Bake 50 to 60 minutes.

title: mama's family secret pecan pie
directions: Melt and slowly brown the butter in a skillet.
Cool.
Beat eggs; add sugar, salt, flavoring and cooled butter.
Stir in pecans and put into 2 pie crusts.
Bake at 425° for 10 minutes. Reduce heat to 300° and bake for 40 minutes more or until set.

title: sprite biscuits
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Roll out dough to 1/2-inch thick. Cut out. Place on lightly greased baking pan.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: baked tacos
directions: Brown meat and onion in a 10-inch skillet; drain.
Add salt, taco sauce and tomato sauce.
Alternate layers of tortillas, cheese and meat mixture in a 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake for 30 minutes in a 375° oven.
Sprinkle with cheese.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream sugar, margarine and eggs 1 minute.
Stir in bananas and add flour mixed with salt and soda.
Add vanilla.
In loaf pan (greased and floured), bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes.

title: easy peach cobbler
directions: Melt butter in small saucepan; set aside.
Pour peaches into a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Add sugar and cinnamon; stir.
Sprinkle cake mix on top.
Pour butter over cake mix.
Do not stir.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 40 minutes or until top of cake is golden brown.

title: cheeseburger casserole
directions: Brown beef and onion; add water, ketchup, mustard, salt and pepper.
Mix well and bring to a boil; stir in rice.
Cover and remove from heat.
Let stand for 5 minutes.
Top with cheese; cover and let stand for 3 to 5 minutes or until cheese is melted. Will serve four.

title: dump cake
directions: Put cherries, pineapple and walnuts on bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour dry cake mix over fruit.
Put margarine pats on top of cake mix.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Cook until it forms a soft ball in cold water.
Add 1 teaspoon vanilla and 4 tablespoons peanut butter.
Pour into pie tin to cool.
Cut into pieces.

title: potato casserole
directions: Combine potatoes, sour cream, cheese, soup, onion and salt in bowl; mix well.
Spoon into casserole dish sprayed with Pam.
Top with optional crumbs; drizzle with butter.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: mustard chicken
directions: Mix all of the above.
Place boneless chicken breasts in mixture and marinate for several hours.
Grill over hot coals or broil in oven.
Heat remaining sauce and use for chicken.

title: yellow squash souffle
directions: Steam squash until tender; smash with fork and drain off excess water.
Combine grated cheese, onion and egg.
Mix. Add whipping cream; stir to mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 375° in uncovered greased casserole dish for 45 minutes.

title: creole
directions: Cook in crock-pot on high at least 4 hours.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Cook potatoes in enough water to cover, until tender.
(Add salt to water.)
Drain, mash potatoes.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Pour into greased casserole dish and top with topping.

title: strawberry nut bread
directions: Grease and flour two loaf pans.
Mix all ingredients together. Mix well.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: scalloped pineapple
directions: Cream together butter and sugar.
Add eggs and beat thoroughly.
Add milk and remaining ingredients.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: pear-pecan salad
directions: Drain juice from pears and reserve 1 cup of liquid.
Bring the juice to a boil on high heat.
Remove from heat and add lemon jello.
Chill until partially set.

title: microwave shrimp scampi
directions: Mix all ingredients; microwave on High, stirring and turning shrimp until they are pink done.
Do not overcook.
Serve in small bowls with sauce cooked in and crackers.

title: mom's spaghetti
directions: Sprinkle garlic salt into oil.
Add chopped onion and saute until clear.
Pour in tomato juice.
Simmer 20 to 25 minutes, then add tomato paste, water, Parmesan cheese, sugar and crushed red pepper.
Stir and simmer.
Add browned hamburger meat to sauce. Stir and simmer mixture for 2 hours.
If sauce is too thick, add 1/2 can water.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Prepare cake per directions on box.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Place 1/2 of cake in bottom of gallon punch bowl.
Cover with 1/2 of all ingredients; repeat with remaining ingredients.
Store in refrigerator.
Serves 25.

title: white casper hamburgers
directions: Mix meat, baby food and broth and form patties.
Mix water with minced onion.
Spoon on meat as it cooks.
(Punch holes in meat as it fries.)
Cut the ends off the hot dog buns and use the center cut as hamburger buns.

title: cherry blossom dessert
directions: Sift flour, salt and soda.
Add brown sugar and oatmeal.
Cut in margarine until mixture is a coarse meal.
Press half of mixture into a 12 x 8 x 2-inch pan, ungreased.
Spread with cherry filling.
Cover with remaining mixture.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.
Serve with Cool Whip or vanilla ice cream topping.

title: praline strip
directions: Arrange crackers on ungreased 10 x 15-inch pan.
Place butter and sugar in saucepan; heat to boiling.
Boil for 2 minutes.
Stir in pecans; spread over crackers.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes. Cut crackers in half while warm.
Makes 48 strips.

title: quickie ham and cheese ball
directions: Add ham to cream cheese and relish.
Mix well.
Roll completely in chopped pecans.
Serve with crackers!

title: cornmeal waffles
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Combine liquid.
Add, mixing just until moistened.
Makes 8 to 10 waffles.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Heat soup, lemon juice, mayonnaise and cheese to simmer.
Add chopped chicken.
Cut broccoli into flowerets.
Steam until tender.
Immediately run cold water over broccoli.

title: candy balls
directions: Mix all ingredients. Roll into 1-inch balls and dip in mixture of 6 Hershey bars with 3 tablespoons paraffin. Cool on waxed paper. Makes lots.

title: rhubarb crunch
directions: Mix flour and powdered sugar.
Cut in shortening.
Pat into 9 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Remove from oven.
In large bowl, beat eggs until fluffy.
Gradually add dry ingredients and mix well.
Add rhubarb and pour over crust.
Bake at 375° for 35 minutes.

title: caramel corn
directions: Boil brown sugar, margarine, corn syrup and salt for 5 minutes.
Add soda.
Pour over popcorn.
Bake on greased cookie sheets 1 hour at 250°, stirring every 15 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Continue stirring every 15 minutes until cool.

title: carrot bread
directions: Sift together first 4 ingredients.
Add coconut and nuts. Stir in remaining ingredients and mix well.
Pour into 3 greased loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chicken-fried steak
directions: In a shallow dish, combine 1/3 cup flour, 1/2 teaspoon salt and 1/4 teaspoon pepper. In another shallow dish, combine the eggs and water. Place the bread crumbs in a third shallow dish. Coat the steaks with the flour mixture, then dip in the egg mixture and coat with the bread crumbs.

title: upside-down fettucini bake
directions: Brown meat and drain.
Add onion.
Cook until tender.
Add tomatoes and oregano.
Bring to boil and simmer 20 minutes.
Stir in Mozzarella cheese.
Transfer into glass baking dish.
Sprinkle with 1/4 cup Parmesan cheese.

title: cool whip cream cheese cake
directions: Beat cream cheese until smooth.
Gradually add with sugar. Beat in sour cream and vanilla.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Pour into crust.
Put in refrigerator for at least 2 hours.

title: berry banana smoothie
directions: In blender, combine banana, berries, juice and yogurt.
Cover and blend until smooth.

title: braised beef esterhazy
directions: Sprinkle one side of beef with half the flour, pound in. Turn beef, pound in remaining flour.
Cut into 6 serving pieces. Heat oil in 12 inch skillet.
Cook 3 pieces of beef at a time in oil over medium heat until brown on both sides or about 15 minutes.
Drain.
Add beef broth and water.
Heat to boiling. Reduce heat.
Cover and simmer 15 minutes.
Add carrots, parsnips and onions.
Sprinkle with salt, pepper and thyme.
Cover and simmer until beef and vegetables are tender or 40 to 60 minutes. Add cucumbers during last 5 minutes.
Remove beef and vegetables to heated platter.
Skim fat from broth in necessary.
Stir in sour cream.
Heat just until hot.
Serve gravy with beef and vegetables.

title: barbecued ham
directions: Mix and stir constantly over heat until mixture boils.
Lower heat.
Cook 30 minutes.
Add ham and heat through.
May be reheated.

title: boston baked beans
directions: Soak beans overnight in cold water.
In morning, drain and cover with fresh water and baking soda.
Cook slowly, simmering 10 to 15 minutes.
Drain beans and rinse in cold water.
Scald bacon. Pour beans into pot alternating layers of bacon and beans.
Mix together molasses, mustard, cloves, sugar, salt, pepper and cup of boiling water.
Pour over beans, adding enough additional water to cover beans.
Cover pot and bake steadily for 6 hours at 250°. Uncover last 1/2 hour of baking to brown.
Add water as needed.

title: hungry boy cookies
directions: Cream first three ingredients. Add eggs.
Sift together flour, baking powder, soda and salt. Add to creamed mixture.
Stir in remaining ingredients. Drop by teaspoon on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake 7 to 8 minutes at 325°.
Remove from cookie sheet and cool on wire rack.

title: tina's popcorn balls
directions: Put popcorn in large bowl.
Mix sugar, water, syrup, salt and butter in saucepan.
Cook on stove until mixture reaches 250°, or until a few drops form a hard ball when dropped into cold water. Remove from heat.
Stir in vanilla.
Pour in thin stream over corn, stirring constantly to mix well.
Shape into balls with buttered hands.

title: never fail divinity
directions: Place all but egg whites,
vanilla
and nuts in a large saucepan.
Stir until dissolved
and boiling point is reached. Cover pan and boil 2
minutes
then
uncover
and cook to firm soft boil stage (238°
on
candy thermometer).
Meantime, beat until stiff but not dry
egg
whites
in a large bowl.
Slowly pour 3/4 hot syrup over
beaten egg whites (return 1/4 to boil until a hard crackle ball
forms
when dripped in cold water). Beat constantly, then add
balance of syrup.
Beat until candy is nearly cold and holds its shape.
Add vanilla flavoring and chopped nuts.

title: copper carrots
directions: Layer in a dish and marinate overnight.

title: 9-day cole slaw
directions: Chop or grind ingredients.
Make a mixture out of sugar, celery seed, oil and vinegar.
Pour this over the other ingredients.
Mix and chill before serving.

title: oatmeal pancakes
directions: Mix in blender. Let set for 5 minutes, then fry.

title: fried zucchini
directions: Perfect side dish or finger snacks.
Kids love them.

title: ginger cookies
directions: Mix in small balls (walnut size) and dip in sugar.
Do not flatten!
Bake at 350° for about 10 minutes.

title: cheezy party dip
directions: Fry sausage and drain oil.
Mix together tomatoes and cream of mushroom soup in crock-pot.
Add sausage and cheese.
Heat until all cheese is melted, stirring often.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: spicy chicken casserole
directions: Mix the soups together.
Mix with chicken and onion.
Layer the chicken mixture in a 2-quart casserole dish.
Add layer of Doritos and another layer of chicken mixture, then top with grated cheese.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: a jem of a carrot cake(a triple 9-inch layer or 9 x 13 sheet cake.)
directions: Heat oven to 350°. Sift together flour, baking powder, soda, salt and cinnamon; set aside. In a large mixing bowl, beat eggs, sugar, oil, carrots and pineapple. Stir in flour and nuts. Spread evenly in desired style pan. Bake 35 to 40 minutes for layers. For sheet cake, bake for about 45 to 50 minutes. Cool in pans 10 to 15 minutes, then gently turn out onto wire rack and allow to cool completely before frosting.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs until light and fluffy.
Add Crisco oil and sugar; mix well.
Add grated zucchini and vanilla.
Mix together.
Add flour, salt, soda, baking powder, cinnamon and nuts.
Pour into greased pan (3 medium loaf pans).
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix together.
Cook for 1 hour at 350°.

title: pineapple bread pudding
directions: Cream together margarine, pudding, vanilla and cinnamon until fluffy. Add eggs, one at a time.
Beat well.
In another bowl, combine milk, undrained pineapple, coconut, raisins and vanilla. By hand, blend milk mixture into creamed mixture (mixture will look curdled).
Fold in bread cubes.
Pour into an ungreased 2-quart casserole.
Place casserole in a large shallow pan on the oven rack.
Pour hot water into the larger pan to a depth of 1-inch.
Bake in a 350° oven for 1 1/4 hours or until toothpick inserted comes out clean.

title: baked beans
directions: Brown ground beef with half of the onion, salt and pepper to taste.
Mix the beans, sugar, mustard, catsup and the remainder of the onion.
Add the ground beef to this mixture.
Bake at 350° for approximately 45 minutes.

title: poppy seed cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix all the ingredients together, beat 7 minutes.
Grease Bundt or tube pan well and flour pan.
Pour mixture in pan.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 45 minutes. Sprinkle top with cinnamon sugar, if desired.
Remove from pan while warm.

title: salt free bread and butter pickles
directions: Thinly slice cucumbers and onions.
Make a spiced vinegar, using vinegar, celery seed, ginger, honey, turmeric and mustard seed.
Mix all ingredients.
Let mixture come to boil in an enamel or stainless steel pan.
Add cucumbers and onions and bring to boiling point.
Pack cucumbers and onions in scalded pint jars. Then pour hot vinegar over them, leaving 1/4 inch headspace.
Seal and process 10 minutes in boiling water bath.
Yields 11 pints.

title: wheel soup(triple this recipe will serve 8 as a main dish)
directions: Steam sausage in 1/2 cup water in a soup kettle 2 minutes. Drain off water.
Brown sausage slightly.
Add onion, green pepper and garlic.
Saute until onion is clear.
Add tomatoes, sauce, water, bouillon and garlic salt.
Cover and simmer 15 minutes. Stir in wheels.
Cover and simmer 10 to 12 minutes until macaroni is tender.
Top each serving with cheese.
Serve with crusty bread and a green salad.

title: four-cheese macaroni
directions: Cook macaroni according to package directions.
Meanwhile, in a saucepan over medium heat, melt butter.
Stir in flour, salt and pepper until smooth.
Bring to a boil; boil and stir for 2 minutes.
Gradually add milk, stirring constantly.
Reduce heat and cook until thick.
Add macaroni and stir until blended.

title: double fudge chocolate cake
directions: Optional:
Can use chocolate frosting or dust with powdered sugar and cocoa mixed.

title: easy meat loaf
directions: Combine ground beef, milk, soup mix and oats. Mix well and pack in loaf pan sprayed with nonstick cooking spray. Spread with catsup. (*May mix 1/4 cup brown sugar with catsup, if desired, then spread.) Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: tomato and feta salad
directions: In serving bowl, gently toss together all ingredients. Warm pita bread, cut into wedges. Serve immediately or chill, covered, until ready to serve. Makes 8 servings.

title: crabby lemon pasta salad
directions: Combine all ingredients in a bowl and toss well.
Serve on a bed of romaine lettuce and garnish with a lemon wedge.

title: shrimp and ham in patty shells
