directions: In saucepan, brown ham and cook mushrooms and garlic in butter. Stir in soup and cream. Add shrimp and parsley. Heat; stir now and then. Serve in patty shells.

title: orange salad
directions: Mix pineapple and sugar; bring to a boil.
Remove from heat; mix in gelatin.
Add water; mix well.
Refrigerate until thick, then add remaining ingredients.
Refrigerate until set.

title: island chicken
directions: Combine
garlic,
oil,	lemon juice, soy sauce, oregano, salt and
pepper
in
bowl, mixing well.
Pour over chicken in glass bowl.
Marinate
tightly
covered,	in
refrigerator for several hours,
turning once.
Place skin side down on rack in broiler pan.
Broil
to	7 inches from heat for 25 minutes; turn. Broil 15 minutes longer.
Yields 4 servings.

title: luncheon salad
directions: Heat soup and gelatin, not too hot.
Cool.
Mix all other ingredients up well.
Add to soup mixture and mix well.
Pour into large Pyrex dish and chill several hours.

title: date bread
directions: Pour boiling water and soda over the dates and set aside. Cream together the oleo and sugar.
Add the vanilla and egg; beat well.
Add the flour and mix.
Pour dates and water mixture over and mix together.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Makes 3 small size loaves.

title: creamy chocolate fudge
directions: Melt butter in a saucepan.
Add sugar and milk; bring to a boil, then cover and cook with the lid on for 3 minutes.
Remove lid and add chocolate squares or cocoa and corn syrup.
Cook to the softball stage (236°).
Remove from heat and add vinegar and vanilla.
Cool to room temperature, then beat until the fudge is thick and creamy.
Add nuts, if desired, and spread in a well buttered pan.

title: mexican spoon bread
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients.
In a deep casserole, layer approximately 1 1/2 cups of mixture, then 1/4 cup cheese, followed by a thin layer of hot pepper.
Continue to layer until all ingredients are used.
Bake at 350° until browned and bubbly.

title: rice pudding(sugar-free, low-fat)
directions: In small saucepan, put raisins and water to cover. Bring to a boil. Remove from heat.

Cover and let stand 10 minutes. Drain. Combine skim milk and pudding mix in a large bowl. Stir with a wire whisk 2 minutes or until thickened. Add rice, pineapple, raisins and cinnamon. Stir well. Cover and chill.
Yields 7 servings (3/4 cup).
Contains 196 calories (1% from fat).

title: tomatoes a l'antiboise(from france)
directions: Mash tuna, oil, butter, salt, pepper and a little lemon juice until creamy.
Empty tomatoes.
Sprinkle salt and a little vinegar on the inside and let stand 15 minutes.
Put tomatoes upside down in a colander to drain.
Fill tomatoes with tuna mixture and arrange gracefully on a bed of parsley.
Garnish platter with cut up hard-boiled egg.
Serve as hors d'oeuvres.

title: veggie dip
directions: Blend together cream cheese, mayonnaise and olive juice.
Add olives, nuts and dash of pepper.
Use for squash, cukes, cauliflower, carrots, broccoli, etc.
Also makes a good sandwich.

title: poppy seed cake
directions: Mix first 8 ingredients until smooth.
Add remaining ingredients and beat well on medium speed for 2 minutes.
Bake at 350 degrees for 1 hour and 10 minutes in a 10-inch angel food tube pan. Do not grease pan.
Cool cake before removing from pan.

title: grandma's sour cream oatmeal cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Mix baking soda into sour cream.
Sift flour, cinnamon, nutmeg, cloves and salt. Set aside.
Pour hot water over raisins and soak for 15 minutes.
Drain well. Cream the shortening, sugar and eggs.
Add oatmeal and vanilla.
Mix well. Alternately add sour cream/soda mixture and sifted flour, mixing well. Add drained raisins and nuts.
Mix well.
Drop on oiled cookie sheets by tablespoon. Bake at 375° until light brown on top.
It is a "soft" cookie.
Makes 3 dozen cookies.

title: pie crust
directions: Beat with electric mixer lard or shortening, 1 cup flour and salt until fluffy.
Then add the rest of flour.
Let set 20 minutes.
Roll and line pie plates.

title: hot potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes with peels on until done.
Cook bacon until crisp and crumble.
Peel and dice potatoes.
Add mayonnaise and bacon. Dice cheese and add to potatoes with onions and stir until well blended.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Bake at 350° until cheese bubbles.

title: pecan rolls
directions: Soften yeast in warm water.
Combine hot milk, shortening, sugar and salt.
Cool to lukewarm.
Add 1 cup flour; beat well. Beat in softened yeast and egg.
Gradually add remaining flour to form a soft dough.
Knead until smooth and elastic, about 8 to 10 minutes.
Place in greased bowl, turning to grease top.
Cover; let rise in warm place, free from draft, until doubled in bulk (about 1 1/2 to 2 hours).
Punch down dough.
Turn out onto lightly floured board.
Divide in half.
Roll each into 12 x 8-inch rectangle. Brush each with 2 tablespoons melted butter.
Combine 1/2 cup sugar and 2 teaspoons cinnamon.
Sprinkle half on each rectangle.
Roll jelly-roll style and seal.
Cut into 8 (1 1/2-inch) slices. Combine in saucepan brown sugar, corn syrup and butter.
Heat slowly, stirring frequently until blended.
Remove from heat. Sprinkle 13 x 9-inch pan with pecans.
Pour syrup mixture and top with 16 rolls.
Cover; let rise 35 to 45 minutes.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.
Immediately invert on plate or cookie sheet.

title: onion roasted potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 450°. In large plastic bag, add all ingredients.
Seal bag and shake.
Empty into shallow baking pan. Bake, stirring occasionally, 40 minutes or until potatoes are tender. Garnish with chopped parsley.

title: hawaiian pie
directions: Mix pineapple, sugar and flour together.
Cook for 2 minutes. Stir while cooking.
Mix unflavored gelatin, orange jello and 1/4 cup water into hot pineapple mixture.
Add nuts, coconut, cherries and bananas; mix well.
Put into baked 9-inch pie shells; let congeal.
Put Cool Whip over top before serving.
Makes 2 pies.

title: potato dish
directions: Mix all together in 9 x 13-inch pan; sprinkle bacon on top. Bake 1 hour in 325° oven.
Mix in cubes of leftover ham and makes a main dish.
Very tasty.

title: apricot jello salad
directions: Prepare jello as directed; add pineapple after draining.
Save pineapple juice.
After jello and pineapple are set, add marshmallows on top.
Mix the eggs, sugar, butter, flour and pineapple juice in saucepan.
Cook until thick.
Add cheese; mix until smooth.
Chill.
Fold mixture in Dream Whip and spread on top of marshmallows.
Chill.

title: favorite chocolate cookies
directions: Mix margarine, sugar and egg thoroughly.
Add buttermilk and vanilla.
Sift together flour, soda, salt and cocoa; stir in.
Mix in nuts, if desired.
Chill at least one hour.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls about 2 inches apart on lightly greased cookie sheet. Bake until almost no imprint remains when touched lightly with finger, 8 to 10 minutes in a 400° oven.
May be iced with chocolate icing.
I use canned frosting if in a hurry.

title: gourmet potatoes
directions: Boil potatoes with their skins on.
Peel potatoes and grate. Melt butter and cheese over low heat; add sour cream, salt and either grated onion or grated chives.
Fold into potatoes.
Cook in 2-quart buttered casserole dish at 350° until heated.

title: wild turkey salad
directions: Mix all ingredients except salt, pepper and mayonnaise.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Work in mayonnaise until the salad is a good consistency for spreading.
Serve on sandwiches or on a cracker.

title: two minute fudge
directions: Mix sugar, cornstarch, cocoa and milk over medium-high heat until it doubles in size (about 2 minutes).
Remove from heat and add remaining ingredients.
Pour into buttered pan.
Chill.

title: chocolate drop cookies
directions: Measure flour, soda and salt; sift together.
Cream butter. Gradually add sugar; mix until light and fluffy.
Beat in vanilla and egg, then blend in melted chocolate.
Alternately add flour mixture and buttermilk, mixing well.
Fold in walnuts.
Drop by teaspoon onto ungreased baking sheets.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes about 3 1/2 dozen cookies.

title: cherry pie
directions: Crust:
Crumble enough vanilla wafers to cover bottom of pie dish.

title: graham cracker goodies
directions: Melt butter.
Stir in sugar.
Cook slowly over low heat until sugar dissolves.
Don't overcook.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Place 1 teaspoon of mixture in center of each graham square.
Bake at 350° for 7 to 10 minutes.
The mixture will spread and coat top of cracker.
Less mess if crackers touch in pan.

title: 90 minute yeast rolls
directions: Mix 3/4 cup flour, sugar, salt and undissolved yeast.
Heat milk, water and margarine to 120° to 130°.
Gradually add to dry ingredients and beat 2 minutes at medium speed of mixer.
Add 1/4 cup flour.
Beat at high speed for 2 minutes.
Stir in enough additional flour to make soft dough.

title: spicy hot eggplant casserole
directions: Cook eggplant in a small amount of boiling water 5 minutes; drain well.
Layer half of eggplant, tomatoes, breadcrumbs, oregano, tomato sauce, Parmesan cheese and Cheddar cheese in a 1 1/2-quart casserole coated with cooking spray.
Repeat layers omitting top layer of Cheddar cheese.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Sprinkle with remaining Cheddar cheese and bake 5 minutes.
Yields 3 servings.
Contains 153 calories, 5 g fat.

title: cheesy herb topping
directions: Crush stuffing mix; toss with melted butter. Sprinkle over hot cooked vegetables or casserole. Top with cheese; allow cheese to melt before serving.

title: california zucchini bake
directions: Saute beef, zucchini, onions, garlic powder and chili powder in a lightly greased skillet until vegetables are tender, but still crisp, stirring frequently.
Add green chiles, rice, sour cream and 1 cup Jack cheese.
Turn into a greased shallow 2-quart casserole dish.
Arrange tomato slices on top and top with remaining 1 cup cheese.
Bake in a preheated 350° oven for 20 to 25 minutes.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: janet ross' mexican chicken(february 26, 1989)
directions: Line bottom of pan with crushed tortilla chips.
Top with diced, cooked chicken.
Mix picante sauce with cream of mushroom soup.
Pour over chicken.
Grate Monterey Jack over soup mixture. Add layer of crushed tortilla chips.
Top with Colby cheese.
Bake at 350° until heated through.

title: honey-glazed chicken
directions: Rinse chicken pieces; pat dry.
Remove skin if you wish.
Melt butter in a shallow baking pan; stir in remaining ingredients. Roll chicken in butter mixture to coat both sides, then arrange, meat side up, in a single layer in same pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, or until chicken is tender and richly glazed.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: strawberry pretzel salad
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients and press into 9 x 13-inch pan or dish.
Bake at 400° for 7 minutes.
Cool.

title: stuffed shells
directions: Cook shells. Drain and let cool. Brown the ground beef. Add spaghetti sauce to beef. Mix Mozzarella, Swiss and cottage cheese together. Stuff shells with the cheese mixture. Place in a glass 9 x 13-inch dish. Cover with spaghetti sauce and bake in a preheated 350° oven for 40 minutes. Sprinkle Parmesan cheese on top.

title: chicken enchiladas for a crowd
directions: Mix salsa and tomato soup in a large bowl.
Fill each tortilla with 1/2 cup chicken and 2 teaspoons salsa mix.
Roll each tortilla, sealing so there are no leaks.
After all tortillas are rolled, place them one at a time in a 13 x 9-inch pan, stacking them if necessary.
Pour rest of salsa mixture over top of tortilla rolls, spreading to cover well.
Sprinkle with 1 cup shredded cheese.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: easy salad
directions: Make jello.
When slightly cool, add additional ingredients. Chill.

title: a & w swiss burgers
directions: Brown ground beef with onion and water (make very fine).
Add catsup, chili powder, mustard and salt.
Simmer for 1 hour.

title: chicken wings
directions: Disjoint the wings, discarding the tips.
Place the wings with the remaining ingredients in a foil pan.
Cook by indirect heat method for 30 minutes.
Brown the wings at either side of the grill directly over hot coals for 10 to 15 minutes.
(Cover off.) Keep the sauce hot.
Serve the wings on a warmed platter with the cooking liquid (scallions removed) as a dipping sauce.

title: cornbread dressing
directions: Cook onion and celery in water until tender. Combine meal, baking powder, salt, pepper and eggs. Add enough canned milk to make batter the consistency of pan cake batter. Fry on griddle or frying pan in small pancake patties until brown on both sides. Toast bread until browned and crumble with corn bread cakes while still hot. Mash with potato masher until thoroughly mixed, adding hot turkey broth while mixing. Add cooked celery and onions plus water they were cooked in. Add sage or poultry seasoning if you like. Pour into 10 x 14 x 2 1/2 inch pan. Dot all over generously with
margarine. Bake one hour at 325°. Stir good once or twice during baking.

title: watermelon drink
directions: Cut watermelon open by making a 2 x 9-inch slit down the middle of the watermelon.
This will be top to replace later.
Scoop out all the insides of the melon.
Put in a colander with a bowl underneath to catch all the juices.
You will have to mash the meat of the melon a lot.

Make sure you get all the juices out of it. Strain the juices a couple times to be sure there are no seeds. Pour some of the juice in ice cube trays and freeze to use for ice. Pour the rest of the juice in containers and put in the refrigerator to chill.
Before serving, mix 1 quart of vodka to every 3 quarts of watermelon.
Pour back in watermelon rind and put in watermelon ice to keep chilled while serving.
Place top cut back on.
Great for summer outside parties.
Poke holes in the rind with a pencil to insert straws.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Cook spinach and drain well. Saute onion in butter.
Mix remaining ingredients and fold in spinach and onion, including butter.
Bake in covered casserole at 350° about 30 minutes.

title: pig cake
directions: Mix cake mix, oil, margarine, eggs and mandarin oranges.
Bake in 3 layers at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Mix and let set the large instant vanilla pudding and crushed pineapple.
When cake is cool, mix pineapple and pudding.
Add Cool Whip, powdered sugar and coconut.
Mix all together.
Spread between cake layers and on top and sides.
Keep refrigerated.
It should be made a day or two before you serve it.

title: malcolm's steak marinade
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Fork-pierce meat and pour mixture over it.
Best if marinated overnight.
Do not use leftover marinade.
This can also be used for London broils.

title: hot cakes
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour small amounts on a hot griddle.
Serves about 5.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Melt butter in 9 x 13-inch rectangular baking dish.
In medium mixing bowl, combine other ingredients.
Mix well and pour butter over this, leaving enough butter in pan to grease well.
Bake in 375° preheated oven for 35 minutes.

title: double-quick rolls
directions: In mixing bowl, dissolve yeast in water.
Stir in sugar, half of the flour and salt.
Beat until smooth.
Add egg and shortening.
Beat in rest of flour until smooth.
Scrape down sides; cover.
Let rise in warm place about 30 minutes.
Stir down batter; spoon into 12 greased, large muffin cups, filling half full.
Let rise in warm place until dough reaches top.
Heat oven to 400°.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes.
Makes 12.

title: tortoni (frozen cream cups)
directions: In a large bowl combine all ingredients except whipped cream. Mix well.
Fold in whipped cream.
Fill 2-1/2 inches in foil cups. Cover and freeze 6 hours until firm.
Garnish with almonds, cherries and coconut.
Keeps well in freezer several days.
Serve frozen.

title: vegetable supper salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in 2 cups boiling water in saucepan; stir in vinegar and salt.
Cool; pour into medium bowl.
Fold in vegetables.
Chill until firm.

title: cheese ball
directions: Combine cream cheese and Cheddar cheese, mixing until well blended.
Add remaining ingredients, mixing well.
Chill.
Shape into ball and roll in nuts.

title: ham and broccoli casserole
directions: Mix eggs and milk.
Add Bisquick, salt and pepper in mixing bowl.
Layer broccoli, ham, onions and cheese in a 9-inch quiche or pie pan.
Pour mixed ingredients over top.
Bake in microwave on Medium-high for 15 to 20 minutes until center is done.
If no turntable, turn halfway or bake at 350° for approximately 30 minutes until center is done.
Serve immediately.

title: cucumber dressing
directions: Mix in jar and pour over sliced cucumbers.
Season with salt and pepper.

title: strawberry icing in the cake
directions: Put everything into bowl and blend on low 1 minute, then beat on medium 2 minutes.
Pour into 14-cup angel food cake pan, greased and floured.
Fill pan 2/3 full.
Any remaining batter can be put in smaller pan.
Line oven with foil and/or put a cookie sheet on lower rack in the event the cake crawls out of pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
If it looks like it's breathing, don't test it with a toothpick; it's not done and will collapse.
Remove and cool about 5 minutes.
Turn out on rack to cool.

title: dough sculpture salt ornaments
directions: I dry my ornaments on a screen, at room temperature, turning twice a day.
Leave them 3 to 4 days.
Put a hole in ornament before it hardens.
Obviously, the finished creations are not for consumption.

title: pork chops for april
directions: Put layer of pork chops in bottom of medium size casserole dish.
Cover with layer of uncooked noodles.
Place mixture of all other ingredients in layer over noodles.
Repeat layer of pork chops, noodles and mixture.
Bake, covered, at 400° for 50 minutes.

title: chicken potato casserole
directions: Melt margarine in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Put layer of chicken and layer of onion rings.
Salt and pepper.
Bake for 1 1/2 hours at 325°, covered.
Cover with layer of potatoes, sliced thin.
Bake for 30 minutes, covered.
Add 2 cans soup; cover and bake 30 minutes.
Take out and cover top with 2 cans biscuits.
Bake until brown, uncovered.

title: twinkie surprise
directions: Cut Twinkies in half.
Place in dessert dish.
Sprinkle strawberries over Twinkies.
Mix pudding using directions on box. Then spread over strawberries.
Spread Cool Whip over top of all. Chill and serve.

title: apple crumble
directions: Place apple in greased 1-quart dish.
Mix white sugar and cinnamon.
Sprinkle on apples. Cut butter into mixture of flour and brown sugar.
Cover apples with mixture and pat down.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: baked bean casserole
directions: Brown together hamburger and onion.
Drain.
Mix hamburger with pork and beans and put in casserole dish.
Cover the mixture with cheese.
Cut each biscuit in half and place around edges. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: mandarin orange cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Blend the cake mix, oil-margarine, eggs and oranges; mix well.
Bake in 2 layer, round pans or one 9 x 13-inch pan (well-greased and floured) for 20 to 25 minutes. Cool, then spread with icing.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix together and chill.

title: pecan moons
directions: Combine first 2 ingredients in bowl and beat until smooth. Add vanilla.
Stir in flour and mix until dough begins to form. Add pecans and continue working the mixture until all is incorporated.
Shape dough into a log, about 1 1/2-inches thick. Roll up in waxed paper or foil.
Chill for 30 minutes.
Unwrap dough and slice into 1/4-inch thick rounds.
Bake 10 minutes; cool slightly.
Remove from tin.
Sprinkle with confectioners sugar.

title: sour cream dressing
directions: Mix all together.
Very good on sliced onion or sliced cucumbers.

title: cheerwine punch
directions: No need to premix.
Chill thoroughly and mix in punch bowl. Serves 30 to 35.

title: shrimp cheese ball
directions: Combine and mix all ingredients except pecans.
Place in waxed paper and mold in bowl.
Sprinkle pecans in bottom of dish; flip ball over, rounded side up.
Sprinkle all over with pecans. Chill.

title: stuffed green peppers
directions: Remove seeds and wash peppers. Parboil 3 minutes. Combine rice, salt, pepper, ground beef, egg, milk and onion. Stuff peppers lightly and place in Mirro-Matic pan on rack. Add tomato soup and water. Cover pan. Set control at 10 and cook for 15 minutes after control jiggles. Reduce pressure normally for 5 minutes, then place pan under faucet. Serves 4.

title: marble bars
directions: Mix oleo, sugars and vanilla thoroughly.
Beat in eggs.
Blend in flour and soda.
Spread in a greased oblong cake pan (9 x 13-inch).
Sprinkle chocolate chips over top of dough.
Place in oven one minute.
Remove from oven and run a table knife through the dough to marbleize.
Return to oven, bake at 375° for 12 to 14 minutes.
Cool.
Cut into squares.

title: easy fudge
directions: Melt margarine; add chocolate morsels until melted.
Add powdered sugar and mix well.
Add evaporated milk as needed.
Add walnuts.
Butter pan and pour mixture into pan.
Let set.

title: quick chocolate pie!
directions: Melt Symphony bar over hot water. Mix with whip cream with an electric beater. Pour in crust and enjoy!

title: coconut cream pie
directions: Combine milk, sugar, egg yolks and salt in saucepan.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Thicken with cornstarch mixed with 3 tablespoons water.
Cook and stir until smooth.
Remove from heat. Stir in coconut and pour into pie shell.
Top with meringue.

title: broccoli cheese casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients together; place in glass 9 x 12-inch pan.
Bake for 30 minutes in oven, or microwave on High for 20 minutes.
When done, sprinkle French fried onions on top and serve.
Serves 6.

title: orange juice cake
directions: Pam Bundt pan.
Spread 1 cup chopped almonds on bottom of pan. Mix remaining ingredients and pour over nuts.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes.

title: special devil's food cake
directions: Place ingredients in mixing bowl and beat vigorously by hand or mixer (medium speed) for 2 minutes.
Add 1/3 cup water and 3 large eggs.
Beat 2 more minutes.
Bake in moderate oven until cake tests done.
Makes 3 layers.

title: daddy's dump cake
directions: Dump cherry pie filling and pineapple with juice into well-greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Next, sprinkle on yellow cake mix, 1/3 cup melted oleo or margarine and chopped nuts over the top. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: sprinkle cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease all type of pans.
Mix cake mix, oil, eggs and water in large mixing bowl on low speed for 30 seconds.
Drop dough by rounded tablespoonfuls 3-inches apart and bake 8 to 11 minutes.

title: brownies
directions: Mix butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time and beat.
Sift in cocoa and flour; mix well, then add nuts.
Bake in one 9-inch round, greased and floured pan for 20 minutes at 350°.
Beware! Don't overcook.
Best when still chewy in the middle.
Makes 15 squares.
Serves a few; they are so good.

title: brown cow
directions: Using 4 tall glasses, place 1 scoop ice cream in each glass. Fill each with root beer.
Serve immediately with straws. Serves 4.

title: chocolate delight
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients and pat into a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.
Let cool.
Mix next 3 ingredients in bowl with blender.
Spread on cool crust.
Mix into another bowl with mixer.
Combine next 2 ingredients and spread on top of cheese mixture.
Top with remaining Cool Whip.
Refrigerate.

title: banana-blueberry cream cheese pies
directions: Line bottom of pie crusts with bananas.
Prepare Dream Whip according to package directions.
Combine cream cheese and sugar. Fold in Dream Whip.
Spread over bananas.
Top each pie with blueberry pie filling.
Makes two 9-inch pies.

title: funnel cake
directions: Combine eggs and milk.
Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Add to egg mixture.
Beat until smooth.
In deep skillet, heat oil to 360°.
Fill a funnel with mixture.
Pour into
hot oil, making a circle.
Cook until light brown.
Drain and sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: spaghetti meat sauce casserole
directions: Brown beef.
Add sauce from box and rinse can with water; add to beef.
Add salt, oregano, sugar and onion.
Cook spaghetti and add sauce.

title: lemon mousse
directions: Put milk in a bowl in freezer until ice particles form around edge of bowl.
Using an electric
mixer whip milk until it begins to thicken.
Add sugar and juice gradually and continue to whip until sugar is dissolved.
Line a buttered container with crumbs. Add lemon mousse and top with a few crumbs or nuts.
Cut in squares to serve.

title: 7 layer dinner
directions: Layer in casserole dish in order given.
Salt and pepper after carrot layer and beef layer.
Bake in oven at 375° for 1 1/2 hours.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake for 1 hour at 325°.

title: good sure fudge
directions: Bring to a rolling boil and boil 3 minutes exactly. Take off heat and stir until cool. Add nuts and pour into buttered pan.

title: speedy strawberry smoothies
directions: In a 5 cup blender container, sprinkle gelatin over cold water. Let stand 3 to 4 minutes.
Add boiling water and blend at low speed until gelatin is completely dissolved, about 2 minutes.
Add 1 cup strawberries and blend at high speed until pureed.
Add eggs, yogurt, sugar, salt and food coloring, if desired.
Blend at high speed, adding ice cubes one at a time until ice is crushed.
Pour about 1/2 cup into each of 8 dessert dishes or 8 custard cups. Chill until set, about 15 minutes.
Garnish with fresh strawberries and mint leaves, if desired.

title: guacamole dip
directions: Mash avocados with lemon juice.
Stir in remaining ingredients; cover with plastic wrap and chill.

title: deep-fried batter
directions: Use this batter to retain shape of food like fish, chicken, cauliflower, onion rings and zucchini.
Coat food with flour, then dip into batter and drop into hot oil.

title: champagne salad
directions: Blend cream cheese and sugar until smooth.
Add remaining ingredients. Mix well.
Freeze in 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: tortilla soup
directions: Combine first 13 ingredients.
Cover and cook (slow cooker - 6 hrs.).
Discard bay leaf.
Cut tortillas 1/4 in. wide and bake at 375 degrees for 5 mins.
Stir and bake for 5 more minutes.
Serve with soup.

title: fudgsicles
directions: Combine and bring to a boil and freeze in molds or Dixie cups with popsicle sticks.

title: pineapple pie
directions: Combine all ingredients, reserving 1/2 cup pineapple, in a heavy saucepan.
Cook over medium heat until mixture boils and thickens.
Cool. Add reserved pineapple.
Pour into pie crust. Cover with top crust.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° and bake an additional 30 minutes.
Cool completely before slicing.

title: danish pastry apple bars
directions: Cut together the flour, salt and shortening.
Add together the egg yolk and enough milk to make 2/3 cup liquid; add to flour mixture and roll as a pie crust.
Put half the crust on a cookie sheet and cover with crushed cornflakes.
Add sliced apples, sugar and cinnamon.
Top with remaining crust.
Beat an egg white and spread on top of crust.
Bake at 375° about 50 minutes.
Dribble frosting on top.

title: corn salad
directions: Combine corn, cucumber, green pepper and green onion in large bowl.
Cover and chill several hours.
Just before serving, add tomatoes, mayonnaise, salt and pepper to taste.

title: potatoes romanoff
directions: Cook potatoes.
Mix remaining ingredients (except Cheddar cheese).
Put into a 3-quart casserole and sprinkle with cheese. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: baked lamb chops
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Rub both sides of chops with curry powder.
Place in large baking dish.
Top each chop with onion, then cheese and then 1 tablespoon sour cream.
Bake, uncovered, about 30 minutes.
Then cover and bake about 2 hours or until tender.

title: hush puppy dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Mix well.
Spoon into skillet or greased casserole and bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes or until golden brown.

title: pork chops
directions: Dampen pork chops and then coat with cracker crumbs.
Brown in small amount of fat in a skillet.
Transfer browned chops to a roasting pan with a cover.
Pour tomatoes over the chops and top with sliced onion.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours, covered.

title: soda cracker cookies
directions: Blend sugar, milk, margarine and vanilla in saucepan.
Bring to a boil for 3 minutes, stirring constantly. Remove from heat; add peanut butter and stir until melted. Stir in crackers. Drop by spoonfuls onto waxed paper. Let cool.

title: kraut
directions: Chop cabbage and pack into jars.
Add to the top of each jar the vinegar, salt and sugar.
Fill jars with hot water.
Seal.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Mix chicken, soup and Veg-All.
Pour into pie shells and cover with pie shells.
Bake at 400° until brown.
Makes two chicken pot pies.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix thoroughly and chill.

title: pizza salad
directions: Roll crescent rolls out flat on a cookie sheet.
Bake according to directions on can, or until lightly browned.
Mix together the salad dressing mix, cream cheese and mayonnaise; spread on cooled crescent roll.
Add chopped vegetables.
Top with grated cheese.
Cut into small squares and serve.

title: fresh cranberry salad
directions: Peel bananas and wrap in plastic wrap.
Freeze.

title: polish slaw
directions: Heat and pour over cabbage and other ingredients.

title: fresh spinach salad
directions: Layer the ingredients into a bowl and top with dressing.

title: sweet and sour green beans
directions: Bring to a boil.
Turn down heat and simmer about two hours or so - until beans are tender.
Do not let beans dry out.
Add another beer if necessary.

title: hamburg casserole
directions: Brown hamburg and onion together; drain off juice or grease. Combine all other ingredients with hamburg after dissolving bouillon cubes with water.
Bake 1 1/2 to 2 hours at 300°.
Makes 5 to 6 servings.

title: cream cheese cups
directions: Slice cookies (1/4 slice) and place in bottom of cupcake liner.
Mix rest of ingredients together (except cherry pie filling).
Fill liners 2/3 full.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 45 minutes.
Cool.
Top with cherry pie filling.

title: summer catfish chowder
directions: Scrub potatoes, then cut in 1/2-inch pieces to make about 2 1/2 cups.
Coarsely chop bell pepper and onion.
Heat oil in heavy 4-quart pot over medium-high heat.
Add potatoes, bell pepper and onion.
Cook about 5 minutes until onion is translucent.
Add broth, tomato sauce, thyme and garlic.
Bring to a boil, cover; then reduce heat and simmer about 8 minutes until potatoes are firm tender.
Meanwhile cut fish into 1-inch chunks.
Halve tomatoes, squeeze out seeds and chop coarse.
Add fish, tomatoes and okra to pot.
Bring to a boil, cover and simmer 8 minutes or until fish is barely opaque in center.
Serve hot, warm, or at room temperature with hot pepper sauce.
Yields 4 servings.
Ready in 26 minutes.

title: chicken and broccoli casserole
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix water and margarine in large bowl until margarine is melted.
Stir in stuffing mix just to moisten; set aside.
Mix chicken and broccoli in 12 x 8-inch baking dish.
Mix soup and milk in another bowl until smooth.
Pour over chicken mixture.
Spoon stuffing evenly over top.
Bake 30 minutes or until heated through.

title: barbecue meatballs
directions: Mix thoroughly beef, sausage, crumbs and egg.
Shape into balls.
Brown meatballs in skillet.
Pour off fat.
Add sauce mixture.
Cover and cook over low 20 minutes or until done.
Stir often.
Serve over rice.

title: peanut patties
directions: Mix sugar, milk, red food coloring, syrup and peanuts together.
Cook slowly at low temperature to soft ball stage.
Add butter and vanilla.
Remove from heat and beat until creamy. Either pour on buttered cookie sheet or spoon on wax paper to form patties.

title: cheese ball
directions: Combine cheeses after grating Cheddar cheese.
Mix well all other ingredients and form into a ball.
Roll ball in mixture of pecans and parsley on wax paper.
Chill.
Serve at room temperature.

title: peanut butter mashed potato fudge
directions: Mash potatoes well.
Knead in rest of ingredients.
Press lightly into buttered pan.
Allow to stand for 1 hour before cutting.
Coconut may be added.

title: jew bread
directions: Mix brown sugar and eggs in double boiler.
Cook for 20 minutes on
low
heat.
Remove
and
cool.
Add
flour, 2 cups nuts, baking powder and flavoring.
Pour in pan and bake 30 to 40 minutes at 325° or 350°.
Cut in squares to serve.

title: cherries in the snow
directions: Mix cheese and sugar together.
Mix Dream Whip by directions on box. Blend in cheese.
In bottom of baking dish, put half of the cake crumbs, then half of the Dream Whip mixture, then half of the cherries and pineapple.
Repeat layering. Refrigerate 4 hours before serving.

title: italian bread
directions: Dissolve 1 cup of water with 1 tablespoon yeast and 1 tablespoon sugar. Water should be quite warm.
Put flour in large bowl.
Add salt and oil or Crisco, 2 cups of warm water and last, add yeast mixture.
Work and knead dough until smooth.
Put dough in greased pan and cover.
Put in warm area and let it raise about 2 hours. Punch down dough and form into loafs.
Brush with egg wash and sprinkle sesame seeds (if you like).
Should raise in pans about 45 minutes to an hour.

title: kentucky pie
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Bake in unbaked pie shell at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: cream cheese brownies
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients and press into bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour on mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli as directed; drain completely and set aside. Blend together all other ingredients, except dried onions.
Put in well-greased casserole.
Add well drained broccoli; mix lightly.
Sprinkle dried onions on top; bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: cinnamon squares
directions: Mix together.
Bake in buttered 9 x 9-inch pan at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Quick, easy, delicious.
Wonderful with coffee.

title: lime pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together; pour into crust.
Chill 2 hours before serving.

title: fried cheese bites
directions: Dip cheese cubes into egg; dredge in flour and dip again in egg.
Roll cubes in breadcrumbs, pressing firmly so crumbs adhere. Place on waxed paper and chill 30 minutes.

title: martha washington chocolates
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients. Roll mixture into balls and chill. Melt chocolate chips and paraffin in double boiler.
(May use chocolate disks instead.) Hand dip balls in melted chocolate.

title: cheese chili appetizer
directions: Melt butter in a 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Beat eggs lightly in a large bowl.
Add flour, baking powder, salt and blend.
Add melted butter, chilies, cottage and Jack cheeses.
Mix until just blended. Turn batter into pan and bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° and bake 35 to 40 minutes longer.
Cut into squares and serve hot.
It can be made early and put in oven just before company arrives.

title: strawberry angel food dessert
directions: Dissolve jello in 2 1/2 cups boiling water.
Stir in thawed strawberries, salt and sugar.
Cool until it thickens.
Fold in Cool Whip.

title: cabbage and beef casserole
directions: Brown beef and onions until it loses its redness.
When beef is brown, stir in raw rice.
While beef is cooking, cut cabbage. Place cabbage in greased casserole dish.
Layer beef over cabbage. Mix soup, water, sugar, and vinegar and pour over layers.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: pineapple drop cookies
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients with mixer until creamy.
Then add crushed pineapple.
Mix good.
Add last 3 ingredients.
Mix well. May add nuts if desired.
Drop on greased cookie sheet with teaspoon.
Bake 7 to 10 minutes at 375°.

title: king ranch chicken
directions: Saute onion and mushrooms in butter; add soup, tomatoes, garlic and chili powder. Place tortillas in broth for about 10 minutes (corn only not flour); if you use flour tortillas, line 13 x 9 pan with them. Alternate layers of chicken, sauce and cheese. Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: rock-roll candy
directions: Melt chocolate over hot water.
Beat until smooth, then stir in the marshmallows and walnuts.
Spread in buttered 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan and chill thoroughly.
Cut into squares.

title: shrimp creole(the best!)
directions: Peel and season shrimp; sit in fridge.
Put oil in heavy pot and put all vegetables except green onions and shrimp.
Put on medium heat in covered pan; let simmer for 40 minutes from first bubble.
Add water and season to taste.
Bring to boil again and let simmer 20 more minutes.
Drop in shrimp and green onions and bring to boil and cook 10 minutes.
Serve over rice.

title: james' fruit salad
directions: Mix dry pudding with juice from pineapple. Chop rest of fruit and slice bananas.
Pour mixture over and refrigerate.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli until tender.
Drain off excess water.
Mix together soup, Miracle Whip, onion, egg, and 1-1/2 cups cheese together.
Sprinkle remaining 1/2 cup cheese on top of casserole. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: pizza sauce
directions: Mix together.
Makes enough for 2 pizzas.

title: cocktail meat balls
directions: Mix egg, onion, cinnamon, salt and pepper with ground beef. Make small meat balls and brown in a frying pan.
Drain grease. Mix chile sauce and jelly; then add to other meat balls.
Simmer for 5 minutes.

title: dr. pepper cake ii
directions: Mix above ingredients until smooth.
Pour into a greased and floured tube pan and bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: hot mulled or spiced wine
directions: Boil for 5 minutes a syrup of sugar, water, cinnamon, lemon and cloves.
Strain syrup and add fruit juice.
Heat red wine but do not boil.
Combine syrup and wine and keep hot in top of double boiler.

title: taco pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease a 10 x 1 1/2-inch pie plate.
Cook and stir beef and onions until brown; drain.
Stir in seasoning mix.
Spread in plate.
Top with chilies.
Beat milk, baking mix and eggs until smooth, 15 seconds in blender on high or 1 minute with a hand beater.
Pour into plate.
Bake 25 minutes.
Top with tomatoes and cheese.
Bake until a knife inserted between center and edge comes out clean, 8 to 18 minutes.
Cool 5 minutes.

title: cheesy potatoes
directions: Layer potatoes and onion; sprinkle with salt and pepper. Sprinkle cheese over the potatoes.
Put a few pats of margarine over cheese.
Mix soup with 1/2 can water.
Pour over cheese. Bake at 400° for 1 hour or until done.

title: hamburger baked beans
directions: Cook and crumble hamburger meat.
Mix all ingredients together.
Cook in crock-pot for 2 to 3 hours, slowly.

title: frozen mocha pie(for spring-form pan or 9 x 13-inch)
directions: Combine and press on the bottom of pan.

title: horseradish mustard yogurt sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients thoroughly, taste and adjust seasoning and chill.
Store in refrigerator for up to 10 days.

title: mama's buttermilk pie
directions: Beat egg yolks. Beat egg whites until fluffy.
Mix other ingredients.
Fold in egg whites.
Pour into unbaked pie shells. Bake in slow (300°) oven 45 minutes until set in middle.

title: stone soup
directions: Mix together; put in crock-pot.
Turn on 5.
Cook a whole day and a whole night.
Let it sit for awhile (because it will be hot).
Pour in bowls and eat.
Makes 100 bowls of soup.

title: low-fat buffalo chicken tenders
directions: Blend thoroughly Tabasco sauce, paprika and cayenne pepper; brush on all surfaces of chicken. Place chicken in greased 11 x 7-inch baking dish. Cover and refrigerate 1 to 24 hours. Bake in preheated 375° oven for 15 minutes or until chicken is no longer pink in center. Blend the Blue cheese dressing, sour cream and Blue cheese; pour into small serving bowl. Serve with the chicken and bell pepper slices for dipping. Makes 10 servings.

title: savory tomato soup
directions: Using vegetable peeler, remove peel (orange part only) from orange.
Reserve fruit for another use.
Heat oil in heavy 3-quart saucepan over medium heat.
Add orange peel, onions and garlic. Cover and cook until onions are tender and golden, stirring occasionally, about 30 minutes.
Stir in herbs, cumin and crushed red pepper.
Cook until cumin is fragrant about 15 minutes.
Add tomatoes with their juices and stock; bring to a boil.
Reduce heat.
Cover and simmer 20 minutes.
Cool slightly.
Puree soup in batches.
Return to saucepan.
Season to taste.

title: pineapple and rice
directions: Mix together and let chill overnight.

title: broccoli soup
directions: Saute onion in butter.
Add cream cheese and milk; stir over low heat until cream cheese is melted.
Dissolve bouillon in boiling water; add to cream cheese mixture.
Stir in broccoli, lemon juice and seasonings.
Heat thoroughly.
Top each serving with a little grated Cheddar cheese.

title: beef pot roast
directions: Put half the can of undiluted soup on a double piece of aluminum foil large enough to wrap completely around roast.
Over the soup, sprinkle half the envelope of soup mix.
Place roast on top and cover with remaining soup, sprinkled with remaining onion soup mix.
Wrap roast completely in foil and place in shallow pan. Bake at 300° for 1 hour per pound.
This makes a delicious roast and gravy all in one.

title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: Cook until thick
water,
sugar and cornstarch.
Remove from heat and add
strawberry
jello.
While sauce is cooling, wash and clean fresh
strawberries.
Place
on paper towel and blot dry. When sauce is cool, mix strawberries in mixture and pour in baked pie
shell.
Cut strawberries in half, if large, quarter them. Top with whipped cream.

title: shery's no-fry french fries
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Slice potatoes into thin lengthwise strips.
Coat a baking sheet with cooking oil spray.
Combine egg whites and Cajun spice in a bowl.
Add the potatoes onto the baking sheet and spread into single layer.
Place baking sheet on bottom rack of oven.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes until fries are crispy, turning every 6 to 8 minutes so they brown evenly.

title: art dough for kids
directions: Mix dry ingredients in bowl.
Gradually add water, while mixing.
Knead the dough until stiff.
If dough is too sticky, brush hands with flour.
Mold dough into shapes.
Dough will harden if left out overnight.
It can be painted and food coloring may be added in the warm water stage.

title: green pepper jelly
directions: Place green pepper, jalapenos and vinegar in blender. Pulverize.
Place over high heat in large pot.
Add sugar.
Bring to hard boil.
Add food coloring.
Add Certo.
Skim top if necessary.
Pour into jelly type jars.
Cool and cover with lids. Store in refrigerator or freezer.
Serve with cream cheese and crackers, topped with jelly.

title: perfect corn bread
directions: Sift flour with sugar, baking powder and salt.
Stir in corn meal. Add eggs, milk and oil. Beat until just smooth, about 1 minute. Pour into greased pan. Bake in hot oven at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: bourbon cake
directions: Combine cherries, raisins and bourbon.
Cover and let stand overnight.
Drain fruit, reserving bourbon.
Cream the butter or magarine and sugars together until light.
Add egg yolks and beat well.

title: caramel butter frosting
directions: Melt the butter; add the brown sugar.
Bring to a boil; stir for 1 minute or until slightly thick.
Cool slightly.
Add the milk and beat until smooth.
Beat in the sifted confectioners sugar.
Spread on cake.

title: overnight lasagna
directions: *Mix these ingredients together and let stand.
Brown meat and add spaghetti sauce plus 1 cup water.
Simmer 15 minutes.
Let cool.
To layer all, start with 1 1/2 cups spaghetti sauce, one layer of raw noodles, one layer of Ricotta cheese mix, layer of Mozzarella slices and another layer of sauce.
Continue layering until all is used, ending with sauce on top.
Cover with tinfoil; let stand in refrigerator overnight.
The next day, bake at 350° for about 45 minutes; take tinfoil off until Mozzarella cheese on top is golden brown.

title: special k bars
directions: Bring sugar and syrup to boil until clear.
Remove from heat and add peanut butter and stir until blended.
Add Special K. Put in 10 x 16 pan.
